column6: MY Konjac Sponge All Natural French Red Clay Facial Sponge for Dry or Mature Skin
column14:
I didn't care for this sponge at all. It was the first red clay one I've used and was unimpressed. Not only did it not perform as described, it developed that mildew scent within the first week, despite gently but thoroughly squeezing the water out and hanging it by its string after rinsing. I LOVED the green tea one, so thought I'd try the red clay one, since it was described for maturing skin. The green tea one I got was the full sized one. It was awesome. It never did get the mildew scent and it lasted about 6 weeks with daily use on my face. I treated it (rinsing, squeezing hanging) exactly as I did the little red clay one. So, I'm pretty bummed I wasted my money on the red clay! I'm about to order the green tea one again to make myself feel better. I wanted to try the others, too, like the charcoal one... but, nah, I'm too chicken to waste another 10 bucks... sticking with the green tea!

Also, not sure it makes a difference, but, the red clay and the green tea were different in their packages. The green one was slightly moist, lovely. The red clay was hard as a rock from the pkg. It did soften when wet, but it made me feel like it had been old already, since it went bad in so few days. should the red clay one be a little moist out of the pkg? Not sure.

column6: Face Moisturizer with SPF 30, Face Cream with SPF30 Suits Sensitive Skin with Zinc Oxide 1.7 ounce Jar
column13: I am totally blown away by this stuff
column14: I am over the moon impressed with this product! The packaging is rather unassuming so I didn't really expect much from it, but man it delivers so much! The product is wonderful! I am 28, pale as could be with very sensitive skin- so I have been through a ton of products and I am very picky! This product in no way hurt my sensitive skin which is wonderful. It is a very luxuriously thick cream, but it absorbs into your skin very fast. It  does leave your skin every so slightly tacky, but I like that. The packaging surprisingly nice. It is easy to open and easy to grip so this would be nice for someone who has some issue open tricky cosmetic products. This product works great with my normal makeup routine, which is a big accomplishment. A lot of silicone based foundations (which is most liquids) have a hard time blending with sun screen product and start to separate- this doesn't cause any issues at all. I have tested it with a number of foundations (liquids, mouse and powered) and have had great results. It also works great with many primers on the market. I tried this product with a number of them and found it worked best with an oil free primer, but had great results with pretty much all of them. This product also hydrates you skin sooooo well. I live in dry Colorado and I need  super moisturizer and this product delivers like no other. My skin feels hydrated, but hydrated because the skin it's self is happy and healthy not because a product on top of my skin making it feel hydrated. Each day that I use this product my skin looks brighter and fuller and healthier. Now, the absolute best thing about this product is the Sun protection. I don't play around when it comes to the sun- I am so pale and burn so easy- sun screen is something I am dead serious about and I give this product my strong approval. SPF 30 is a pretty strong benefit coming out of the gate a lot of product will only do about SPF 15, so I liked this was a much higher number. What is best is that the product has Zinc Oxide in it - it is so hard to find a good product that absorbs into your skin and doesn't break down your makeup that has zinc in it. Zine is a barrier- no UVA or UB rays get past it. Other sun screens act like reflectors that the rays go into your skin and then bounce off the product - which technically protects you but when you are very pale or have skin cancer run in your family- its just not a risk you want to take! I have used this product in rather strong sun and it protects- it really does. I was out for about 2 hours and didn't get red and my freckles didn't come out with to me proves I got my harmful rays to my skin. column14: I love this hair product.  It's reliable, covers gray that highlights it rather than covering it up with regular hair dye. column6: Foxbrim Retinol Cream - Advanced Complex Face Moisturizer - Anti-Aging Cream With Natural & Organic Ingredients - 1.7OZ
column13: Easy retinol that doesn't cause sensitivity.
column14:
I have used other Foxbrim products before and found them to be high quality and well packaged, so I was pleased to try the retinol moisturizer. The first thing I like about the product is the ingredients list. The first two (greatest amount) ingredients are organic, as well as others. Several of the ingredients are "wildcrafted" or kosher. I like eating organic because it is "cleaner" and the same goes for the products I put on my skin.
The potency of the retinol is touted on the label, however I find the moisturizer to be very easy on my skin. I'm not saying it should hurt or that i want to experience any of the side-effects retinol can have on the skin (I usually don't much at all) but I wonder to the potency since I have not felt any adjustment to my skin as I have with other retinol treatments I have used. This is a creamy but light moisturizer which absorbs easily and leaves my skin soft, as a moisturizer should. The packaging recommends use morning and/or night but I have only used it as a night cream because I always try to use a cream with sunscreen during the day for protection and I find using retinols at night when my skin is in restorative mode, to be most effective. The pump bottle delivery makes it easy to get just the right amount of product for one, full application on my entire face and down my neck. The cream has a clean, slightly floral smell but nothing perfume-y or skin irritating. I will have to use it for longer to get the full benefits, but this seems like a great retinol for someone with sensitive skin. *Discount given for unbiased opinion. I would recommend the product and order from the seller again.

column6: Power cord, fits electric shavers and electric razors.
column14:
I'd been looking for a straight, not spiral, replacement cord like my original. But Remington discontinued them. At this low price, decided to order this cord. I'm glad I did. The cord works great and the spiral isn't as bad as I'd thought! For the last several years, the original cord on my old Remington 6M2L-1 ladies shaver has been falling off/disconnecting from shaver during use. This new cord has a nice snug fit.

It should be noted, as some people say there are some Remington shavers this cord doesn't fit: I purchased my 6M2L-1 in 1995, after the cord entirely stopped working on a nearly identical Remington I bought in 1982 and was unable to find a replacement cord. (As my 1982 shaver's in storage right now, can't give you model number.) When my 1995 shaver cord started falling out of shaver socket during use, I tried that cord in my older shaver. It fit nice and snug, no falling out during use. But as the 1995 shaver gave an even closer shave than the other, I continued using it--while holding onto the cord to keep it from disconnecting!

So apparently the 1982 shavers have slightly larger connection posts where the cord plugs in. As this new cord I purchased fits snug in my 1995 shaver, it possibly could be difficult to plug into the 1982 shaver. (For me, it's no problem because I plan to use my old 1995 cord for the 1982 shaver.) This might be why some reviewers had problems with this cord fitting their Remington shavers.

column13: Didn't notice a big difference between these and the regular Biore strips
column14:
I have been a long time Biore strip devotee (I've used them all, regular, extra strength, nose and face). Depending on how clogged my pores are at the time I know the results will vary, but like many others I love that feeling of seeing a lot left behind on the strip and knowing you're getting a ton out. When I read the good reviews saying these were even more effective I was really excited to give them a try!

After using 3 of the charcoal strips over a period of 3 weeks, I'm not as impressed as I'd hoped. They do get out some gunk and as I mentioned, sometimes what you get out varies based on factors other than the strip itself, but I just wasn't "wowed" by these. They do give a nice tingly sensation though which feels great.

All in all, these still work, but I don't know that they're any more or less effective as the standard Biore strips.

column6: Azteca Gold Virgin Coconut Oil, Extremely Pure and Natural. Absolutely No Impurities or Pollutants. Simply The Best Coconut Oil Available! Natures Super Food Miracle.
column14:
This oil is really nice, i have been enjoying using it on my hair! It's hand made in Thailand without any chemicals or heat treatment! It comes in a simple squeeze type bottle.

You cant see from any of the pictures that i took, but inside the bottle is a solid product. But, when it comes in contact with your skin, it melts into a oil or liquid form. I noticed that while keeping it in my house, it stayed in a semi sold form. But, if i take it outside for a bit it starts to melt.Since it is in a almost solid form, you do have to put in some effort to get some oil out of the container. I think the packaging could be better and easier to use, but its not that big of a setback.

I love the smell of this! As you can imagine, it smells like coconut and i happen to adore that scent.

I personally love using this for my hair and cuticles the most. For my hair, i just apply it to tame the frizz and add some shine to my hair. Just make sure to only apply this at the ends of your hair. Applying oil to the roots of your hair will just make it look greasy. My hair is much softer and silky-er when i use this product! I use this on my cuticles by massaging it in and that softens them. It makes my nails look and feel better.

There are many other ways that you can use this coconut oil. You can use it as a moisturizer for your skin, and it also provides a SPF of 15 which is fascinating to me. Sunscreens have such harsh chemicals in them, and this has no chemicals its just coconut oil! But it can still protect your face from the sun. You can also use it as a massage oil. Using it in food is another great way to use this product!

Overall, i think that this is such a great natural moisturizer. I am loving how it makes my hair feel, and its a added bonus that it doesn't have any chemicals.

**I was sent this product for free in exchange for my HONEST review!

column6: Maybelline New York The Nudes Eye Shadow Palette, 0.34 oz.
column14: This is going to be a review of The Nudes, The Blushed Nudes, and The Smokes (as all three of them are listed as different color options).  These three palettes have different color schemes, but they're all the same size and have the same "formula" (what's the word used with pressed powder eye shadows? I have no idea). I was super excited when I saw them at my local drugstore, and I picked all three of them up. I really liked the packaging because they're not bulky, and even though they don't have a mirror, I liked the clear plastic window because I could see all the colors in the store. The colors looked so beautiful! Each palette came with two sponge tipped applicators.  The Nudes, of course, has more neutral colors--browns, coppers, a black. The Blushed Nudes is more rosy-toned and has some plum shades. The Smokes is darker, with a navy, silvers, blacks, and grays.  They're all terrible. Every shadow was chalky, not very pigmented, and there are absolutely NO mattes in any of these palettes. I thought there would be some nice matte browns or taupes to use as transition shades, but no, every single shadow has an obnoxious overspray of glitter that actually will pick up when you dip your brush or your finger in them. There is a super glittery black in The Smokes, and whatever, that's for smokey looks, but having glitter in the black shadow in The Nudes? Really?  Some people say that there are mattes in the palettes, and yes, there are definitely shadows that look less glittery than the others. However, just try swatching them on your arm and hold it up to the light--you will see tiny glitters. It makes applying the shadows difficult because it's hard to blend, and the fallout is atrocious. I always use an eye primer because my lids are oily, and even with a primer, these shadows look like they fade throughout the day.  Don't waste your money--this is not a dupe for the Naked palettes...this is not even a dupe for the Wet n Wild Walkin' on Eggshells trio, it's that bad.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column13: In using it I found It adjusts easily to the contours of the face especially the upper ...
column14:
I received this Braun Series 9 9090cc electric shaver for review through BzzAgent a company that coordinates product reviews and reports results back to manufacturers.

This new Braun shaver is their top of the line item with a floating and cross-cutting shaving head. In using it I found It adjusts easily to the contours of the face especially the upper neck and jawline. They have worked extra hard to provide a comfortable hold while shaving with a front thumb cradle and the back side has a no-skid area where your other fingers hold the shaver as you move slowly about your face. This provides a very comfortable experience relaxing your hold and your wrist while shaving. My hand felt relaxed after use and no numbness or anything like that on the hand. The shaver does not need hard pressing, in fact, it wonâ€™t work as well if you press too hard, as I did the first couple of times.. The extra long trimmer is long enough to clear the shaving head with ease.

The Braun Series 9 comes with a charging station which includes a self-cleaning reservoir. The shaver is stored upside down in the slot and quickly recharges automatically and in the same position it can be automatically cleaned by hitting the on button. It also comes with a hard case for travel and a small brush to use on the cutting blades.

THE SKINNY: This shaver is perfect if you have a heavy beard in the morning and rushed out for work. It only works ok on light beards. It won't provide a smooth shave like a great brush-applied lather shave, but there is no electric shaver that will do that. There will also be an an added expense to having to replace the head cleaning solution cartridge every couple of months or sooner.

column6: Emjoi Divine Hair Remover, White/Pink
column14:
I've been using this for about 2 months now and am very happy with the results.
I wanted to wait for a bit before posting, because I knew the first time would be awful (from reading reviews and comments) and I wanted to get the courage to finally epilate my underarms.
My take-away on epilator a is that they are perfect for busy people who just don't want to shave everyday! I haven't worried about my armpit hair in a week! I have 4 kids and a full time job, my body hair needs to be a thing I can maintain on my time, which this epilator has made possible.
Important: get dollar store batteries! I've gone through 4 dollars worth of batteries for 2 months of crazy epilating. I will probably buy the cord eventually.
- Holy moly, prepare yourself before going in the first time. I wouldn't let there be any more than a week of razor stubble, or it will hurt worse.
- Take it easy and slow. I did my lower leg first on one day, then the next day I did my thighs, then I did my arms, then tried out my face, and finally got up the courage to do my armpits. The first day was the worst because I just wasn't used to it yet!
- give your body a couple of hours before you have to go out to get back to normal. For the first couple hours, you'll have little red marks that kind of look like a rash. If you've waxed before you know this!
I'm so happy that having a socially acceptable amount of body hair is no longer something thy I have to stress about when getting dressed. One less thing has made a huge improvement!

column6: Uncle Bills Sliver Gripper Precision Tweezers
column13: Not what they were.  Sketchy company.
column14:
This is what it says on Uncle Bill's website: "Uncle Bill's Sliver Gripper is all about an American success story. We follow Uncle Bill's model of an American made quality tool that is still hand polished and hand sharpened just as Uncle Bill did 30 years ago."

However, when I saw that my new tweezers were nothing like my old ones, I called to get the straight scoop. The guy I talked to told me that twenty years ago, they completely changed how they were made. They guy I spoke with told me that the tweezers would cost "forty bucks each" if they were still made the old way.

The old ones had really sweet precise points. These don't. These are cheaply stamped, poorly finished where it counts, at the tip. They don't work anything like the old ones, unless and until you put a bevel and a point on them.

They can't simultaneously claim that these are made the old way, and also say that they'd cost $40 each if they were. I don't appreciate the cheapening of a beloved survival tool, nor being lied to about it.

I am keeping these under protest, and putting a point and an edge on them myself, which will certainly take me a couple of hours, thus raising the cost of these tweezers to forty bucks a piece, in terms of my time...

So buy these if you must. The guy claimed they hadn't made the metal thinner over the years, but I would almost swear that my old pair was stiffer and less susceptible to sideways deflection. Whatever. Like so many things, these just ain't what they used to be. I would have much preferred that they maintain quality and raise prices as necessary, instead of cheaping out.

I just recently noticed that I have started to get wrinkles on my forehead and I am always looking for a good face moisturizer. So I decided to give this cream a try.
Let's start by the packaging. It comes in an easy push top dispenser that allows you to get the cream mess free. This is great for me because those other type of dispensers always accumulate junk on the top of them.
This cream goes on smoothly and does a great job at moisturizing the face and neck. Does not get greasy or oily and your face feels very soft in the morning.
I just started using it so as far as the anti aging effects I will have to get back here in the future but I can tell you that the few wrinkly spots on my face do feel a lot smoother. So I am pleased with this purchase.

column6: Maybelline New York Color Show Nail Lacquer, 0.23 Ounce
column14: I got "Rich in Ruby" which is a great color, but the lacquer is so thick. If you go over an area more than once while trying to even out the polish on your nail, the brush actually takes off lacquer instead of adding more so you end up with something streaky and uneven.  Because of this, you cannot get away with only doing 1 layer with this polish.  Also, because this polish is so thick, it's easy to develop bubbles which of course looks terrible.  On top of all that, it takes a full 24 hours to set.  I cannot go a full day without accidentally touching something, so I end up with fingerprint patterns and dented polish.  I should have returned it.

column13: High pressure salesmen and overpriced products
column14:
I was leaving the mall and the Adore shop is right by the entrance so I got stopped by a salesman. He offered to show me some of their products and had me sit on a chair. To my surprise, he pulled his chair right in front of mine, effectively boxing me in. Then he launched into a very long sales pitch, and demonstrated (on my wrist) their exfoliating cream, lotion, and toner. The skin didn't feel any softer than the untreated one, though it did tingle unpleasantly, like a sort of chemical burn. He at first tried to sell me a $200 bundle, then offered to give me a 50% discount voucher, but would only get half the bundle (which isn't really a discount? Seeing as I'm paying half and only receiving half).

Basically, very high pressured selling tactics. Their products aren't any different from stuff you can get for much cheaper. They smell nice, but that's about it. I will steer clear of this store next time I visit the mall.

column6: Acure Organics Lemongrass + Moroccan Argan Oil Firming Body Lotion - 8 oz.
column14:
Mmmmm.... so I bought this completely on a whim at Whole Foods one day. I shop at Whole Foods about twice a year, and needed some lotion, and I was in a hurry so I just picked something pretty at eye level. Only when I got it home did I see that it is meant to have "firming" properties. Great, I thought, that means it probably lacks "hydrating" properties. It might even sting. Awesome.

But the lotion hydrated just fine and I got used to using it and forgot about the firming part. Until one day I put on a dress that, when I'd worn it previously, I was a little self-conscious of how much of my less-than-perfectly-smooth thighs were showing. Only this time... the thighs looked okay. Heck, actually, the thighs looked pretty good, considering I'd done not one single lunge or mile on the treadmill since the last time I'd checked them out in this dress. What the - ... and then I remembered I'd been "firming" my legs with this lotion for the better part of a month. Sweet! Buying another bottle post haste.

Why the missing star? I don't like the smell. I mean, it's not horrid or I wouldn't be smearing it on my body every day, but it's not my favorite. Dull citrusy grassy with a funky undertone. Still... WORTH IT.

column6: New Double Edge Safety Razor Satin Black Finish Longer Heavier Package Include 10 Stainless Steel Blades and a Leather Pouch
column14:
I was provided this for free in exchange for an honest review.

First off, it comes in a nice box, with a package of 10 razor blades. It's made of quality materials, and is quite hefty - much more so than the plastic ones I'd been using, so it took a couple minutes to get used tot he weight. The biggest issue I had was that it didn't come with instructions, so I had to figure out how to get the blade on through trial and error. Once it was on though, I didn't have any issues. The handle is a good size for my hands (I'm a woman) and I got a really close shave on my underarms, legs, and bikini line. The top portion is curves, which I found helped me to get a closer shave in the joint. I did nick myself once, going over a scab from an insect bite, but other than that I didn't have any issues. I'd say it's definitely a keeper, especially since it's a bit less wasteful than the disposable razors I'd been using.

column14: For the last ten years or so, my migraines have been so intense and painful, if locking myself in a dark room does not help, I end up having to visit the ER for a shot. There are two different ways to use this: cold or hot. Since it obviously takes longer for something to cool down, I already had this chilling in the freezer for a couple hours. (Be sure to place the Eye Pillow inside a zip lock bag before placing it in the freezer as to no ruin it.) To warm it, simply remove the inner sack from the pillow case and place in the microwave for 20-30 seconds. (The pillow case has a zipper closure and you do NOT want to put metal in the microwave!!) The Eye Pillow itself is made from natural lavender and flaxseed but surprisingly, the smell is NOT overwhelming!! It is more of a relaxing, peaceful aroma that almost immediately helps your body relax and unwind. The pillow case is a very soft, silk that helps the Eye Pillow conform to your facial curves to completely block out light. There are no uncomfortable straps; the pillow will sit comfortably in place. Without the straps, you can also place this on the back of your neck, shoulders, or wherever to help relieve the pressure and tightness of your muscles, too. I noticed that this also helped to reduce the puffiness in my eyes making me look more alert. Weighing a little over six ounces, this is NOT too heavy feeling either. It measures roughly 5 inches by 9 inches, this is long enough to cover both your eyes completely or curve comfortably around the back of your neck. They include a very nice, vinyl like, draw string closure, carry bag to help keep it clean while not in use or to take with you on the go. This is most definitely the BEST Eye Pillow with MANY different uses I have used yet!! I will be keeping this around for a very long time!! column6: Organic Red Henna Leaf Powder l 1b
column13: Walks like a duck, talks like a duck, but can't even float.
column14:
Looks like henna. Smells like henna. But it dyes like a box dye. A pricey, stinky, five-hour box dye. A chestnut brown box dye. To be absolutely clear: I have been using henna on my hair since I was old enough to spell. During that time, it always turned my hair bright, screaming red. I'm talking Mary Jane Watson. I'm talking turn-heads, stop-traffic, can't-lose-me-in-a-store-even-though-I'm-five-foot-four, RED. I'm talking Jessica Rabbit levels here.
So imagine my surprise, imagine my disappointment, and subsequently, my rage, when I mix this henna as always, apply it as always, and sit with it on my head, wrapped up, for five hours, as always, and then go through the usual hell rinsing it out, only to be left with...brown. A reddish brown, I grant, but brown. Just brown. Not even a particularly shiny brown. Not even a brown that covers my dirty-blond roots. They're still dirty blond, just now with a slight auburn tint. For the record, the bag says "RED" henna.
Now, if I were a newbie to henna and didn't know what to expect, I might just be mildly disappointed. But I'm not a stranger to henna. I know what henna is supposed to look like. I know what my hair looks like after five hours steeping in this mud. This? This isn't it.
All in all, the only thing still convincing me that this actually is henna is the smell. My hair smells like henna, but with none of the pretty red to make it worth it. In short, don't.

column13: Great size, soft and absorbs nicely
column14:
It is a very soft and well absorbent hair towel. It is a good size for short and medium hair length. I have heavy and medium hair length. It works perfectly for me.
I used to wrap my hair with a long big regular towel which was so heavy and big for hair. It used to pull my hair from the front just because the towel was sliding towards back. This towel is just perfect size to wrap the hair after shower.
I love how soft, gentle and absorbent the towel is. It is stain and shrink resistant. It comes in a nice packaging with some instructions on the back.
I recommend reading the instructions.
Like you wash other towel before using, wash this hair towel before use. Do not bleach this towel. It is ultra soft so you do not need to use fabric softener for this. The towels come in black, pink and white colors. It is recommended to wash colors one separately. In the machine it does leave its black color so be careful. Do not wash with other light color or white clothes/towels.
The towel stays soft after many washes.
The fabric has great quality. It is not very thick but has good absorbency.
Over all it is a good towel. I would give it 5 stars because it is doing its work perfectly.
I received this as a sample to try and give my honest opinion.

I am very self conscious of my yellow teeth and always try to buy products that can approve their appearance. My teeth are also very sensitive so I have to be careful with the products I use. The CrestÂ® 3D Whiteâ„¢ Brilliance Daily Cleansing & Whitening System is a two step process but is very easy to use -- you brush your teeth with the Deep Cleansing Toothpaste for one minute and then brush on the Whitening Finisher. Unlike other products where you need to leave the whitening substance on for five minutes or longer, this is a very quick and efficient process.

I have been using this system for a month and I have noticed only a very minor difference with the color I have yet to receive any compliments or remarks from others and have also felt some sensitivity when using the Whitening Finisher. column6: Osmosis Catalyst AC-11 Serum, 1 Oz
column13: Way too expensive for snake oil
column14:
Sadly this was the most expensive snake oil I ever purchased. I bought it full price at a Spa $100. I was convinced it would work because I had tried Osmosis' drinkable sunscreen and thought "if that stuff works then anything they make must work!"

This wasn't the case. I used it for one month and emailed the company saying it wasn't working. They said it can take 3 months before you notice a difference . Three MONTHS! They said use it twice a day every day and take a before and after picture.

Well it's three months later and I don't look any different .

The product and person representing the company promised me lighter freckles , smoother complexion, minimize or get rid of skin tags, aid with acne, and minimize fine lines and wrinkles while making the skin produce more collagen.

NONE of this happened.

I have just as much acne, my freckles are the same , my skin is just as rough, my skin tags are the same, bumps on my face still there and my wrinkles are actually worse! Probably from rubbing my skin with this crap for the last 3 months.

Three months is TOO long to wait for something to work and I'm very disappointed that I spent all that time on a product that did nothing for me.

I wish I had my $100 back to invest in something that actually works for me.

column14: I don't typically write reviews but wanted to take the time for this product. I have somewhat deep set eyes so if I wear regular mascara I get raccoon eyes when I smile or laugh. Waterproof mascara cures the raccoon problem but removing it is a task. No matter how thorough I think I've been, I wake up the next morning with mascara residue around my eyes. So tube mascara has been an excellent option. It stays on until I remove it. When I remove it, it comes completely off. I was using Blinc tube mascara but it is expensive and there is a short window when the consistency is just right. The L'Oreal brand has been great. I liberally apply the base then run a lash comb through to remove any clumps then apply the mascara. My lashes are well defined, pretty long and pretty natural looking. The base and mascara dry pretty quick so I've learned to do one eye at a time. I hope this is helpful!

column6: Radha Beauty Tea Tree Essential Oil 4 oz - 100% Pure and Natural
column14:
I purchased this product along with the Radha Peppermint oil. Same size bottle. The prices are amazing, because I've been paying 2-3 times more than this from any other company.

This oil, though, smells quite different from any other brand I've purchased. Sure, it smells... tea tree...ish .... But it smells like tea tree oil PLUS something. Or highly diluted? I can't put my finger on it. The other tea tree oils I've had have all smelled pretty much the same, with slightly varying degrees of potency and purity. Maybe this is a bad batch, or maybe it's a different kind of extraction. I have no idea.

If this is just diluted or a cheaper extraction method, that's better than a chemical additive or something. That would be upsetting, because I put it in lip balms and other skin care products.

I live in a large city where "hippie" and health food products are abundant and are extremely high quality, so I feel like I can tell the difference. I'm not sure I'll order this brand again, unless someone can tell me something I don't know. I see so many 5-star reviews, so I'm open to learning because I really want to like this product - the prices are outstanding!!! But maybe for a reason?

column6: Hot Buns Dark
column13: HELPFUL TIPS + TRICKS FOR MAKING THESE WORK AND HELPING TO MAKE YOUR BUN LOOK PROFESSIONALLY STYLED!
column14:
Firstly, I love that this comes with two sizes: Small + Large. I personally use the large size (I have layered, medium/thick wavy hair), and I use the small size on my 5 year-old daughter (she has layered, super thin curly hair) who gets a kick out of our hairstyles/buns looking the exact same! But I will say that there are two tips/tricks that I personally figured out to getting these to work for both myself and my daughter. Even though we two totally different hair types, these tricks/tips make these buns work for both of us!

1) CUR OFF THE RINGS THAT SURROUND THE MESH - THIS WILL PREVENT DAMAGE FROM OCCURRING TO YOUR HAIR. There are 5 on the large and 4 on the small sizes. I cut these off because I noticed my hair and my daughter's hair were getting snagged in them. This doesn't keep them from working/holding our hair up in the bun any less than when we were using them with the rings, like I originally thought it may. This is most likely because of the next trick/tip I personally discovered...

2) YOU NEED TO BRUSH YOUR HAIR AND/OR STYLE IT INTO A PONYTAIL AND SECURE IT WITH HAIR TIES BEFORE YOU USE THIS. I personally brush may hair back into a taunt slick ponytail. Wherever you have the pony (top of head or lower) this is where your bun will be. I personally like to put the pony at the top of my head for the topknot look. I secure my ponytail in place with two hair ties (I prefer these by Goody http://www.amazon.com/Goody-Ouchless-Metal-Elastics-Large/dp/B001T8W4BK). I then hold the pony up vertically and start wrapping it around as tightly as possible with the "bun" opened up like a hair roller. I then snap it in place at the back, and start spreading the hair around with my fingers so that it fully wraps around the bun. I don't even bother with the built-in pony tail holder because it can break easily, and by creating my own ponytail first, I don't even need to use the built-in ponytail holder. Render it useless if you want to.

3) USE BOBBY PINS FOR EXTRA HOLD IN THE BACK OR EVEN WITHIN THE BUN FOR FLYAWAY LAYERS. I use regular black bobby pins, always flat side outwards to secure my hair in the back as sometimes it can start to fall during the day - especially if you have layered hair like me. This just gives the overall hair some support at the back. Occasionally, a tip of a layer will pop out after I'm done, and bobby pins do the trick for securing these little pop-out pieces as well.

Doing these things definitely made the BIGGEST difference for us, and we now LOVE these! I hope this helps someone out there!/>

column6: Ogilvie Straightener for All Hair Types, 0.89 Pound
column13: Used to make my permed hair straight again
column14:
I permed my hair and I got sick of it (I naturally have stick straight hair). This is the same chemicals used in perms so it's safe to use on permed hair (relaxers aren't I think). So I straightened my hair with this and it's back to being almost as straight as before! I had dyed blonde hair. I waited a month after the original perm and two weeks after dying it before straightening it. I also used deep conditioners containing keratin and coconut oil like 2-4 times a week the month beforehand. I only left the straightener on for about 7 minutes and I immediately followed the treatment with a coconut oil hair mask. My hair looks less damaged than before, but I think straight hair tends to just look like that. It's been about two weeks since I straightened it and it still looks great. I switched to brown non permanent hair dye and I deep condition it about once a week. I flat iron it nearly every day on a very low setting and it takes about 5 minutes to get it all straight. I use this keratin heat resistant spray on it beforehand (along with kahm daily smoothing treatment and lavender oil).

I also cut about four inches off my hair (it wasn't damaged, I just felt like it) before straightening so this probably reduced my risk of split ends. I might also have abnormally resilient hair. All in all, I think this is a great product for getting permed hair straight as long as you make sure to deep condition it often. I highly recommend it.

I added a before and after photo so the blonde hair is BEFORE straightening it.

column6: Braun Series 9 9090cc Men's Electric Foil Shaver / Electric Razor with Cleansing Center, Razors, Shavers, & Cordless Shaving System
column14: Let me start out by saying this shaver is quality.  The Braun Series 9 shaver is a statement on how functionality and form can be brought together in a clever way for such a commonly used product. This may be by far the best product that Braun has produced in a very long time.  The cutting edge technology is assembled in a beautifully crafted product that works as good as it looks. Each part of this shaver is made with aesthetics, comfort and usability in mind â€“ a well-designed user interface, thumb rest and overall grip make using the product a joy. In a nutshell, the Braun Series Shaver offers the following benefits: Improved shaving head â€“ comprised of four cutting elements, two foils and two trimmers. These elements are cleverly combined to deliver the cleanest shave through the sonic technology that adapts to the density of the beard. The Braun Series 9 shaver can mow through a three day beard in a fraction of the time that other shavers do. Secondly, flexible cutting elements â€“ work individually to read the contours of the face for a clean and even shave. Third, efficient â€“ yet comfortable shave devoid of the usual problems of razor burn or cuts. As expected from Braun, the operation of the shaver is intuitive and simple. This shaver is especially useful for people who do not like shaving everyday but skip a day or two. The Braun Series 9 shaver is strong enough to handle overgrown hairs unlike the conventional shavers that can only do so much. The noise levels of this shaver are significantly lower than that of other products of a similar class and the smooth vibrations provide a calming and relaxing feeling to your shave. Overall, this is a good quality shaver that should serve you well for a long time â€“ something that will justify the price that some might find beyond their reach. Overall, fantastic piece of machinery! It does its work quickly and more than well - a clean and flawless shave. Reaching difficult places is a breeze and the result is perfect. The ONLY con I have is the cleaning contraption. One, it is large and it comes with a cartridge containing flammable chemicals which means travelling with it is out of question. Two, the indicator on the shaver requires a cleaning session after EACH shave! In fact I just let the machine run for about 15 seconds in the air, without even touching my skin, and the cleaning indicator went on. And then you are supposed to replace the cleaning fluid at least once every 8 weeks even if not used. Seems suspiciously like a clever way to extract more money from customers. For that I've knocked one star off.  In conclusion, definitely a great shaver and I highly recommend it.perfect. The ONLY con I have is the cleaning contraption. column6: Gold Bond Ultimate Comfort Body Powder 10 oz
column13: Use with caution and good ventilation
column14:
Be careful to use sparingly & in well ventilated room. This powder contains SILCA which is essentiall chalk dust. It's very absorbent but you can breathe it into your lungs and it's really dangerous. I learned the hard way when I was using it one winter and my new forced air furnace ductwork wasn't properly balanced. What was happening was the intake was sucking in the excess powder from the bathroom then what wasn't absorbed by the furnace filter was being blown back into the air inside the house so we were breathing microscopic particles of drying dust. Inside of about a month my dog started going blind from the excess drying of her eyes and I developed a severe cough that took months to get rid of and required inhalation therapy.
I was fortunate because I had an Ionic Breeze air cleaner and when I went to clean it, I discovered it was completely covered with this dry, white dust. It was SILCA from the Gold Bond Body powder. We could have become much sicker if I had t noticed this. I had the furnace fixed as it needed to be properly adjusted and it has worked fine for 5 years now.
I actually loved the product but be careful. Do NOT use this on BABIES or on your bedding as they suggest.

column14:
Ah hah. Here's the scoop on Dove Sensitive Skin bar soap that I learned on Environmental Working Group (EWG.com) website that probably explains the fragrance disparity you all have noticed.

There is "Dove Sensitive Skin Beauty Bar" and it has ZERO fragrance.
There is "Dove Sensitive Skin Beauty Bar Unscented" and it has a masking fragrance. ("Unscented" does not mean fragrance-free.)
There is "Dove Sensitive Skin Bath Bar" and I don't have this one.

So, know what you are getting.

column6: Ralph Lauren Polo Red Intense for Men 4.2 Oz Edp Spray By Ralph Lauren, 4.2 Fluid Ounce
column14:
To anyone who loved Polo Red, but was disappointed in the performance, then believe me when I say the problem was solved with Polo Red Intense. This stuff is truly amazing.
Yes, it's similar to Polo Red, but it's slightly more darker thanks to the coffee notes, and the sillage and longevity are fantastic.
Four sprays lasts me up to 12 hours, and the compliments are endless every time I wear it.
Lots of people loved the Polo Red too, but they were not as enthusiastic as they are about the 'Intense.'
I was only getting about 2 1/2 hours longevity from the original Red, and for the price it just wasn't worth it.
I was a little hesitant about buying the Intense, but now I'm so glad I did.
It's one of the best releases for men in years.

column6: Advanced Dermatology Anti Aging Lilac Stem Cell Face Cream & Moisturizer - With Naturally-Occurring Vitamin C, E, A (Retinol) & Antioxidants - Helps Reduce & Repair Fine Lines, Wrinkles, & Aging Skin
column14:
I like experimenting with new anti aging products. I've found that sometimes changing your usual routine actually helps.. Especially, if adding a serum that truly works!
This serum has a creamy texture. and a cinnamon-y scent, that I personally find pleasant. It isn't greasy and absorbs in less than 30 seconds. I've used it (mainly) as a night time moisturizer. It is soothing to my skin, which has been unusually more sensitive and dry during these summer months. A couple pumps from the airless container, covers my face, neck, and hands. (Tip: always treat your hands~they give your age away. Have you ever noticed a woman with amazing skin, assumed she was younger, until seeing her hands? total giveaway! ;)
I like how soft this makes my skin feel. It seemed to "plump up" my problem areas~ie: around my eyes & mouth, plus brightened my skin.
It's not your usual moisturizer. This might sound odd, but it reminds me of a couple cellulite creams I've tried: similar scent and feel, but definitely not!
All in All? I'm like it, and have seen some improvements in my general appearance. Before I forget to mention, a couple times, I used it in the morning~on days I got little sleep. It helped smooth the bags under my eyes. It also acted as decent "primer", before applying makeup. It's a wonderful multitasking moisturizer.
*i received this product at a reduced price in exchange for my honest, unbiased opinion.

column6: Cool Mist Humidifier,Oak Leaf 1.3L Multi-Color Room Humidifiers Ultrasonic Essential Oil Diffuser,Large Capacity,7 Color LED Lights,Waterless Auto Shut-Off
column13: An otherworldly source of pleasant fragrances
column14:
Upon unpacking this item in its sturdy brown, compartmentalized box with switching AC adapter, 100 ml measuring cup and instructions enclosed, I was immediately reminded of an aesthetically pleasing, oval-shaped, UFO as one might expect to find hovering near the outskirts of Roswell, NM. This first impression was enhanced all the more for me when this 250 ml aromatherapy diffuser was plugged in with its band-like blue light all aglow. Others may take issue with this, but I personally like these optics very much and this larger capacity aromatherapy diffuser has now made a permanent landing in my home where it is being happily used on a regular basis.

I appreciate the tactile, more grippy coating of the oval-shaped main unit itself which opens into two halves for adding the required water and essential oil to the base before operation. However, opening this diffuser could be made noticeably easier by providing a notch or tab of some sort to indicate where the nearly seamless halves of the diffuser can be best separated. As it stands now, finding this â€œsweet spotâ€ for taking the diffuser apart can be something of a challenge.

I am personally using a selection of pure essential oils by Kis Oils readily available here on Amazon.com (Aromatherapy Top 6 100% Pure Therapeutic Grade Basic Sampler Essential Oil Gift Set- 6/10 mL [Lavender, Tea Tree, Eucalyptus, Lemongrass, Orange, Peppermint]) and have been extremely pleased with the results that I have obtained. Only a few drops (3 or 4 works for me) of the essential oil that you prefer are needed for a wonderfully fragrant and pleasing olfactory experience. On the low setting this diffuser needs to be filled to its maximum capacity of 250 ml twice to produce a fragrance that lasts 24 hours; on the high setting three refills are necessary.

The User Manual included is difficult to understand in certain sections due to poor English, but this is not really a problem since the diffuser itself is extremely simple to use and knowing what needs to be done for proper operation will be intuitive to most end users. Note that the manual does reverse the actual locations of the mist and light buttons on the front base of the unit: something that can be determined by trial and error. The advice provided about how much essential oil to use is also inconsistent: 1-2 drops are mentioned at one location in the manual, while 12 drops are mentioned elsewhere. You definitely do not want to use 12 drops which would be overkill! Just a few drops will do, as I mentioned previously. After the aromatherapy diffuser turns off, it is also always a good idea to wipe up the remaining water and essential oil combination with a paper towel before it dries. This is especially important when switching from one fragrance to another for an unadulterated effect.

I have noticed that some reviewers have complained that this diffuser has only a single color of light available, no variety of different colors to scroll through and select a personal favorite or an ongoing alternating light show that can be activated. Personally, this does not bother me in the least. I prefer the notably larger capacity of this diffuser (250 ml versus 100 ml of others) and the single shade of alien, spooky blue that can be turned on or off is perfectly consistent with the otherworldly shape of this device.

Overall, I am extremely pleased with the performance of this aromatherapy diffuser and can recommend it with very few minor reservations (see above). I consider myself lucky to have received a complimentary unit from the manufacturer for this hopefully unbiased review.f is extremely simple to use and knowing what needs to be done for proper operation will be intuitive to most end users. column14: This is perfect for beginner wet shavers. I had another brand of comparable price (actually more expensive) that did not perform nearly as well. column6: Skyroad(TM) Top Quality Exfoliating Scrub Bath Mitten -4 items per package- (Made in Korea)
column13: Been using these for years. Excellent product.
column14:
There's no cleaner showering than one that entails a full body exfoliation.

My Korean girlfriend introduced me to this product, which is feels kind of like a scouring pad for the skin. It's not so rough it damages the skin but just enough to slough off the dead cells. It is something many asians use and is commonplace in public spas in asia.

I like to use soap with this product however my wife uses it in the traditional way, which is without soap, after which she applies moisturizing lotion. She says there's a satisfaction in seeing the dead skin is scoured off your body into rolleds she calls "noodles" . I tried it and I admit it does tell you how dirty was and clean your body is when you're done. I like to use it with soap because I'm just used my Zest smell, plus I don't get the unsightly noodles. She says I don't do it that way I can't tell if I'm clean. Fair enough, honey :)

Anyway I HIGHLY recommend everyone buy the smaller "mittens" (which are just square pockets) for the body, and this one to scrub your back.

column6: 100% Pure USDA Certified Organic Moroccan Argan Oil For Hair, Face, Skin, Nails, Acne scar, Lips, Dry Scalp, Split Ends, Cuticles, Stretch Marks, Beard, Body & Best Moisturizer for Dry Skin
column14:
I had heard so many positive things about Argan oil, but I wasnâ€™t sure what to do with it. I used to think of it as just a hair oil. I got the Argan oil from Eliminer and after doing some research, have been experimenting since the past week. I have not used other brands of Argan oils, and will not be able to compare to other brands. However, this oil seems to be great and very effective.

- Face moisturizer - Before sleeping, after cleansing face, I apply 2 - 3 drop of oil on face and have noticed my face glow in the morning. The oil gets absorbed easily and doesnâ€™t make face greasy.
- Leave-in Hair conditioner / Serum - After shower, I have been using few drop of Argan oil to wet hair before styling. This prevents from hair damage due to heat. Also adds shine and reduced frizz once the hair is dry.
- Hair treatment - Before sleeping, I massage my hair, ends and scalp with Argan oil, wrap it with towel and wash it off the next morning. I have noticed my hair to be soft and silky.
- Face masks - Have also been adding it to store bought face masks. Apply as usual and wash off.
- Lip moistorizer - Apply a drop before sleeping and notice your lips the next morning.
- Nails - Massage a few drops to your nails and notice soft and beautiful nails.

I am very happy with the purchase and would recommend this Argan oil. I received a discount on the Argan oil for my review, however I am completely honest and no way affecting my opinion.

column6: Skyroad(TM) Top Quality Exfoliating Scrub Bath Mitten -8 items per package- (Made in Korea)
column13: Excellent product. Been using these for years.
column14:
There's no cleaner showering than one that entails a full body exfoliation.

My Korean girlfriend introduced me to this product, which is feels kind of like a scouring pad for the skin. It's not so rough it damages the skin but just enough to slough off the dead cells. It is something many asians use and is commonplace in public spas in asia.

I like to use soap with this product however my wife uses it in the traditional way, which is without soap, after which she applies moisturizing lotion. She says there's a satisfaction in seeing the dead skin is scoured off your body into rolleds she calls "noodles" . I tried it and I admit it does tell you how dirty was and clean your body is when you're done. I like to use it with soap because I'm just used my Zest smell, plus I don't get the unsightly noodles. She says I don't do it that way I can't tell if I'm clean. Fair enough, honey :)

Anyway I HIGHLY recommend everyone buy the smaller "mittens" (which are just square pockets) for the body, and this one to scrub your back.

I was a little skeptical that this thing would actually work, but I tried it as soon as I got it and I was pretty impressed that it took the shadow right off a brush with fresh product on it.  The only thing I found with this that is not great is that if you use a sparkly pigment or shadow, it doesn't get all the sparkly particles off the brush and some of that can transfer to your next shadow.  But otherwise, the Colour Switch is impressive and I was surprised at how well it worked with regular shadows.  The tin is also nice since it catches any shadow that trickles through the sponge, it also seems like it will be great to travel with since it won't get make up everywhere if you toss it in a makeup bag.  They do sell refills for the tin, but I think I will just wash the one it came with and see how that works out.  Overall, I am pretty impressed with this brush cleaner and would recommend it to people looking for an easy way to clean your eye brushes between colors.

column6: Temporary Tattoos Metallic Silver Gold - Jewelry Tats - 5 Sheets, 96 Designs
column14:
My daughter likes the look of tattoos, but me being a mom doesn't won't let her until she is 18. But this beauty in a flash Tattoos by SkinGlyph is really cool, where she gets the look of a tattoo and jewelry at the same time.

This set comes with 5 sheets of jewelry tattoos and then it also came with a 5 Jeweled tattoo stickers. What is cool about these is that you can put them in a way to make cool designs. My daughter is really into the Henna Tattoo look and with these you can create that look.

They were really easy to put on. You have to make sure where you are putting them on, that the skin is cleaned and dried. You then cut the design that you want out and remove the film from it. Place the tattoo face down onto the skin and with a damp cloth thoroughly wet the tattoo. Then you gently peel back a corner of the tattoo to ensure that it is on the skin(if not, press down and wet again) then pull it off and let it dry for at least 5 minutes.

This tattoo lasted on her for two days, she had to be very careful in the shower with it. But it stayed on with no problem, after the second day she washed it off. So it probably would have lasted another day. These tattoos are pretty and I highly recommend them.

I did receive this at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased opinion. Compensation of any kind is never accepted in exchange for a positive review. All opinions expressed are my own and not edited by any companies mentioned.

column6: Nair Shower Power Max Women Hair Remover, 11 Ounce
column13: Nair, get rid of that Hair!
column14:
Throughout the years I've always dealt with thick, coarse and excessive hair. This is all thanks to the fact that I deal with PCOS. As a female, of course it had caused me to deal with self-esteem issues as well as the feeling to just never want to get near people, in fear of them judging me for how hairy my arms or my legs would look. After purchasing Nair, for at least the third time now: I finally feel confident in giving a review on this wonderful product.

Nair Shower Power Max works just as directed on the bottle. It's not hard to apply it, although the sponge that comes along with hair remover is quite flimsy: it's still managable. I know it says not to touch it with your fingers, but if you're not afraid (I've done this a couple of times, fingers are still perfectly fine sometimes just left with the scent) you can spread it easier that way. Just be sure you rinse off any extra once you've finished applying the amount to your desired area.

Once it comes time to wash off the formula, and you're not feeling the sponge because let's be honest: it just collects all the hair and breaks apart easily. I'd suggest investing in maybe a hand towel or a shower pouf/loofah (since you can use this in the shower, why not?) to scrub off the hair and the Nair as well. I've done this multiple times (less now though) since my first experience and each time, I find the hairs on my legs take a longer period to grow. I was used to shaving maybe two times a week, or every other week if I was lucky. But with Nair, I was apply to go three or even four weeks until the stubble on my legs became noticeable. And I'm talking my thick coarse hair, is just slowly growing back which is absolutely amazing. This product may not remove every single hair if you don't leave it on for the right amount of time, so I normally leave it on for a few extra minutes (five to ten, and my skin is never harmed by it. Only try this at your own risk!) After removing the Nair, your skin feels completely smooth and it's left smelling fantastic.

I really want to stress that the only faulty thing with this product, the only reason why I won't give it a five star review... is simply because the darn sponge is just so useless. I wish they could've made it with better material, but it is what it is. Other than that, Nair Shower Power Max has worked miracles for me. It's not too expensive, and it's pain free. Hell I've fallen in love with the product so much, that if I really need it to prepare for an event I just hit up a local pharmacy and purchase it there (a couple of dollars more but it's worth every cent.) I'd definitely recommend this to anyone who really has self-esteem issues due to their hair problems. Or those who just can't stand the excess body hair. Once you try it, I promise you'll run around ask all your friends and family to touch your smooth legs, arms or wherever it is you've used Nair Shower Power Max on! :-)eels completely smooth and it's left smelling fantastic.

column6: URPOWER 100ml 7 Color Changing Essential Oil Diffuser
column13: The FIRST STEP in Aromatherapy -- a good diffuser
column14:
Most diffusers work the same way. They use ultrasonic vibration to transform water into cool mist. When you put essential oils into the water, they atomize into the atmosphere, creating a pleasant smell, and allowing the healing qualities of the essential oil to enter us thru our sinuses, skin, and lungs. Basically, you select the diffuser you like, based on the shape, and operating features. The URPOWER diffuser works well, and has features that let you get more enjoyment out of the unit. For starters. you have separate buttons to control the MIST function, and the LED LIGHT. You can have mist and the LED morphing lights, or just the lights as a nightlight, or just the mist. Also, you can select to see morphing colors with the LED, or you can click on the LIGHT button, until you find your favorite color. (Some people use colored light therapy in conjunction with their aromatherapy. For example, green light to relax, matching it with Lavender oil. Red light energizes, match that with some peppermint and orange oil. Violet light is healing, match it with eucalyptus oil during a cold, etc.) With the MIST button, you can select a constant mist, or just intermittent mist, so your diffuser can last longer, between refilling the water tank. The tank holds about 120 ml of water....about a half cup of water. Most of them hold this much. It should run for about 3 hours on continuous function, then when the water tank it empty, the unit will turn off automatically. You have an indicator LED light, to let you know which mode the mist is functioning in. (Green - constant mist. Red - intermittent mist..) The URPOWER diffuser also includes a plastic water container, so you don't have to unplug your diffuser, and take it to the sink to fill with water. All in all, a nice diffuser, produced by a company which has released a lot of quality products for sale on Amazon. When you buy a diffuser, you'll get everything you need to start practicing aromatherapy, except---NO ESSENTIAL OILS INCLUDED. I would suggest either getting one of those 6 bottle starter sets, so you have one of each of the most popular essential oils (Peppermint, Lavender, Orange, Eucalyptus, Tree Tea, and Lemon Grass), or just buy a bottle of a pre-mixed blend of essential oils, that will have a title like Rejuvenate, or Relax. Also, consider buying a favorite oil, so you can use your diffuser like a smokeless incense stick. I use Patchouli oil in my diffuser, or sometimes Myrrh, Around the holidays, you can buy essential oil of Pine, so your whole house can smell like a Christmas tree or Hanukah Bush. Another idea, is to buy essential oil of Citronella, to chase away bugs from a porch. Also, Cedarwood oil is a bug repellent. Consider buying a book on Aromatherapy, if you catch the bug and want to learn more and more, about this fascinating art. Your first step, will be to purchase a diffuser to disperse your essential oils. (You can put oil on your light bulb, and let it burn into the air, but the smell is released too fast that way, plus heat destroys some of the qualities of the carefully produced Essential Oils.) If you're looking for a good quality diffuser at a very reasonable price, you would do well with the URPOWER unit.

column6: Special Effects SFX Hair Color Hair Dye
column14: This stuff is amazing. I don't know what they put in my hair at the salon, but even with only washing my hair in cold, and not every day, it still was fading almost immediately. I mixed just a little of this half and half with conditioner and left it on the pink part of my hair for half an hour, and it boosted the color right up! At first I did that every other week, but right now it's been a good 2 and a half months (and I gave up on cold washes a month ago - I visited Peru where it is winter, and wanted the hot showers!), and while the ends have faded a bit, most of my hair is still vibrant hot pink. I think when I get my roots done I'll just have them bleach it and put this on myself, since it seems to work and stay far better than what they used. Also, there's plenty in this bottle! I only have about a third of my hair pink, but it's long and thick, and I've still only used less than a quarter of a bottle after 3-4 uses. It doesn't need to be full strength to work, in my experience, so I expect this bottle will last a good long time. As with all fun color dyes, this will stain everything! Be careful, wear gloves, put vaseline around your hairline, put a shower cap or something on while you're letting it set, or you'll have pink where you don't want it!  Edit - it's now been over 10 months since I last touched up the color, and 10 months since I gave up taking special care of it. That's nine months of HOT showers, and not doing anything special, just plain shampoo and conditioner as I would usually do. There were parts at the ends that were lighter bright pink with hints of peachiness, but the majority was still a very bright hot pink! Not as dark as freshly dyed, but still very bright and vibrant. I had a ton of roots obviously, but the color was still fantastic. Last night I bleached my roots and re-dyed, and now my hair is even more super vibrant bright pink. I'm very pleased. I've finally got to the bottom of the bottle, so I'm re-ordering. Atomic Pink is mycolor. (Also, highly recommend Manic Panic's Dye Away wipes. They do a great job getting the stray dye spots off your ears and arms, and help a bit with surfaces too.)

column6: Scunci No-slip Grip Auto Clasp Barrettes
column13: Can they make these any harder to get out?
column14:
I picked these up at my local grocery store. Same item number (#17851-A) as what's shown in the picture.

My first problem: the individual pieces of the barrette have shrink-wrap plastic around them. Not the colored outside piece, but the two main metal pieces that make up the barrette. One of those pieces is against the back of the barrette, and I could not find a way to remove the plastic without removing the piece from the barrette. Basically, to get all the plastic off, I had to take the barrettes completely apart (I had 3 separate pieces at the end, for each barrette). I also needed small, sharp scissors (and poked my finger with them once, ouch.) It was really WAY more work than a cheapo barrette warrants, and I can't figure out what the scunci people were thinking. Maybe I just got a weird batch (I'd love to hear if others had this problem), but I've never bought barrettes with individual plastic on the parts before. Really awful and time consuming to get off.

Problem 2: The barrettes are not as big as they look. They don't hold enough hair. The outer, colored edge is the same exact size as several other (similar style) barrettes I own, but the actual clasp is not big enough. This is frustrating, because it's difficult to figure out until you buy it (and remove all the plastic)!

Problem 3: They feel cheap. The pieces seem to fall apart easily. You can get them to stick back together, but I've never had barrettes where the pieces just fall off like this. I'm not impressed.

Back to searching for better barrettes!

column13: A Heavier Cream Than I Expected, But I Like This Kit
column14:
I'm a fan of the Ageless La Cure Phyto 5 line of cosmetics, and I like this kit in general despite the cream portion feeling a bit too heavy/sticky for my tastes. Instead of using this as the manufacturer suggests - applying the face cream in the morning and the serum and face cream at night -- I tend to use the serum by day and both at night for a smooth, supple skin texture.

I love that Ageless La Cure uses natural products to produce their products. The cream does have a pronounced floral scent that I don't mind since I now use it at night, and the serum smells like pleasant astringent. The kit includes two pump bottles (the serum is smaller than the cream one) that equal together 1.5 ounces. It doesn't seem like a lot of product for the price; however, you only need one or two pumps per application.

I like this product, but I don't love it the way I do some of the manufacturer's other products. Still, the results are good, and that's what counts.

-- Debbie Lee Wesselmann

column6: PURA D'OR Anti-Hair Loss Shampoo (Gold Label), Effective Solution for Hair Thinning & Breakage, NEW & IMPROVED PUMPS, 16 Fluid Ounce (Packaging May Vary)
column13: To my delight, I have noticed healthier and more regrowth plus ...
column14: I am an African male almost turning forty and half way through this shampoo. I must be honest; I was very hesitant to write a review until I was certain that I had really noticed hair growth improvement on my scalp. Two years ago I was diagnosed with Androgenetic Alopecia and I have been on Minoxidil, Ketokonazole 2%, 1mg Finpecia tablets, a hair follicle stimulating shampoo and hair growth vitamins. Within the two years my hair loss had lessened and I have noticed hair growth that has slowly been converging onto the center of my scalp where the severe balding is. Three months ago I came across this shampoo on amazon and decided to have a go at it while sidelining my other prescribed hair growth shampoo I had been using prior. To my delight, I have noticed healthier and more regrowth plus less hair loss after just having gone through half the bottle. I am now planning to purchase more and stick to this shampoo. I am very sure that this product has worked for me but I am not guaranteeing that the same results would be obtained by another individual as we all have different responses and metabolisms plus varied hair growth periods. I have not attained the full head I anticipate but the best advice I can give is that only with patience and perseverance will one fulfill hair growth goals. Hair regrowth does not happen like magic. I hope all that want to give this product a try will experience the same positive results I have experienced or even better.

column13: A great towel for thick, curly hair! :) Absorbs water like no other.
column14:
I guess I'm a rebel because even though the directions said to wash this before use, I didn't. Also, even though it says to wash it separately, I didn't. I can't afford to wash a single towel by itself and I wasn't too keen on washing it by hand. So, I used it right out of the packaging and then later washed it with my regular wash load. I don't regret either decision as I didn't have any issues with it being too rough or stiff upon first use. I also didn't notice any bleeding, and it didn't ruin or damage any of the other items I had in the washing machine with it.

I wouldn't say this is the softest towel I've ever felt (because it isn't), but it certainly is the most absorbent. This really cuts down on the drying time of my thick, tightly curled hair. I usually use a t-shirt to dry my hair and even then I still have water dripping down my face and neck for an hour or two (I like to air dry). With this microfiber towel, so much water is absorbed that my hair is already about 75% dry when I take it off.

I like to wrap this towel around my head and leave it on for about 20 - 30 minutes. Surprisingly, it fits my head quite nicely. As I said, my hair is very thick and also puffy, so the fact that it fits nicely around my head is great. It's very easy to secure it on my head and the texture helps to keep it in place (doesn't move around). Water never drips down either when I have this on. I love it!

I received this product complimentary in exchange for my honest, unbiased review. All opinions are 100% mine.

column6: Etre Belle Aloe Vera Ultra Moisturizing Gel 1.36 Fl. Oz. Made in Germany
column13: good moisturizing gel for summer although I don't love the ingredients
column14:
This has been a really good summer moisturizer for me. I prefer to move to gel formulas during summer as they seem to keep my skin from getting greasy, and that is definitely the case here. This absorbs into the skin quickly and doesn't interfere with other products (I use it after cleanser, toner, and serum, but before sunscreen and primer). So far, it has not irritated my skin. And even though it is a gel and dries more quickly than oil-based moisturizers, it is still easy to apply. You don't need to use a ton, so one tube will last a long time.

Here are the ingredients, since I didn't see them on the product page:

Water, Glycerin, Ethoxydiglycol, PEG-7 Glyceryl Cocoate, PEG-40 Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Acrylates/C10-30 Alkyl Acrylate Cross- polymer, Aloe Barbadensis Leaf Juice, Serine, Urea, Allantoin, Pentylene Glycol, Sodium Lactate, Propylene Glycol, Sorbitol, Caprylyl Glycol, Polysorbate 20, Trometha- mine, Sodium Hydroxide, Lactic Acid, Magnesium Nitrate, Sodium Chloride, Magnesium Chloride, Tetrasodium EDTA, Benzyl Alcohol, Methylchloroisothiazo- linone, Methylisothiazolinone, Hexyl Cinnamal, Hydroxycitronellal, Benzyl Salicylate, Geraniol, Linalool, Citronellol, Limonene, CI 42090 [Blue 1], CI 19140 [Yellow 5], Fragrance

This *may* be helping clear up my skin a little. It contains lactic acid (an alpha hydroxy acid), so be sure to use this in combination with a sunscreen product. It certainly isn't doing anything to break me out. (Please note that benzyl salicylate can sometimes cause reactions, and that a person may be sensitized to it over time.) Once again (I feel like I say this frequently), I am not happy with the fragrance and dyes, although they haven't yet caused me problems (I've been using this once a day for maybe two weeks).

I'm inclined to continue using this because it is working for me. My skin gets very oily in summer and I think this cuts down on the oil. However, if a different gel moisturizer with ingredients I like more, comes along, I will probably switch to that instead.sturizer with ingredients I like more, comes along, I will probably switch to that instead.

column6: Pure Body Naturals Purifying Dead Sea Mud Mask Facial Treatment
column13: Curiosity got the best of me due to the glowing reviews and pricing ...
column14:
Curiosity got the best of me due to the glowing reviews and pricing at $17.95 (now it has increased to $19.95). I followed the directions applying to my face, and the first thing I noticed was a slight tingling sensation likely from the salts. It does have a pleasant odor. After washing off in the shower, my skin felt smoother. That's about it, it didn't look any different. However, when I followed through with the rest of my regimen (toning, then placing vitamin C serum, and lastly moisturizer) my skin gave off a healthy glow--not sure if this is placebo or the product. I'll keep using this weekly and may apply on other body parts.

8/30/15 update:
I have been using this mask for nearly a month now. First off, I doubt this mask has any long-term changes to my skin but I do feel a difference in my skin after each use. I follow the directions such as using only once a week and no longer than 15 minutes as suggested on the jar. I have a combination oily skin, large pores on my nose and cheeks, and occasionally will get dry patches but often blotchy after being exposed to water (washing my face, swimming, showering, etc). For the remainder of the day using this product my skin feels smoother and appears more balanced and I notice that my skin is not as blotchy. The pores remain but I do not expect any type of mud mask to reduce pores. In fact, I don't think there are any skin products that can reduce the size of the pores outside of sometime of medical procedure such as laser (although there are products that do reduce or mask the appearance of the pores, however that would be for another review). I will continue to use this product weekly, I would re-rate the product to 4 stars given the relatively reasonable price compared to costly name brand products.

column6: Azfasst Green Tea Skin Care Set
column14: I thought turning 40 this year would be hard.  Who would of thought deeper wrinkles and frequent breakouts would happen almost as the clock hit midnight on my birthday.  I tried so many products: skin tighteners, lifters, hemorrhoid cream ect.  Anything to try and lessen my wrinkles. (Side note: Don't use the hemorrhoid cream.  It REALLY burns)  I hated looking so tired all time.  I was complaining to one of my friends about it and she said she used Azfasst.  She always has such beautiful skin. I figured I had tried everything else, I had nothing to lose.  I received the product very quickly.  I loved the packaging!  I used the eye cream every night.  After a few weeks, I saw that my wrinkles were not as deep.  For my breakouts, I used the gel.  My zits went away at a faster rate than if I did nothing.  And even for the ones I picked (we all are guilty of picking, so don't judge me.), the redness was gone within a couple of days of using the gel. My skin tends to be kind of dry, a little flaky and red spots (God, I sound horrible! LOL! My skin is sensitive, what can I say) The combination of the moisturizer and gel totally evened my skin out.  So here is my conclusion: Azfasst is a worthwhile investment.  A little bit goes a long way, so the bottles will last months!  Right now, I am 6 months past my 40th birthday. Thus far, I have had my first mammogram (not fun!), been told I am a candidate for bifocals, am officially called "Ma'am and not Miss" anymore.  BUT......my skin is now BEAUTIFUL!!!  THANK YOU TO THE MAKERS OF AZFASST!!!!  You made turning 40 a lot less traumatic!

column14: I'm not very picky about my mascara. I wear contact lenses, and when I wore this mascara, my eyes became incredibly dry and uncomfortable throughout the day. I also found this mascara surprisingly difficult to remove using an eye makeup remover. Sadly, this product ended up in the trash after only two days of wear.

column6: Proactiv+ Blackhead Dissolving Gel, 1 Ounce
column14:
I really cannot believe how well this works.

Some background info: I've been prone to blackheads since I was a teenager. Nothing helped. I have super oily skin and they just would get embedded in my nose and cheeks, basically my t-zone. I couldn't help it and while it never looked bad from far away, close up it is noticeable. It didn't help that I worked outside in construction from my late teens to mid 20's.

I would get facials and facialists would recommend super expensive products to help fight the blackheads, but I was told by more than one person the only thing that will rid me of blackheads is going for facials frequently and letting them extract. Which hurts and is extremely unpleasant. And even then the facialist couldn't get them all and the next time I'd go new ones would replace the ones that were removed from the time before. It was like an endless cycle. By the way, in New York (not sure if it's the same in all states) a facial is around $120 for an hour. So getting my hair done, my eyebrows waxed and a facial every month was becoming a $300+ excursion after tips, parking, etc. Ridiculous.

I had heard good and bad things about Proactiv products. Someone told me they were extremely harsh and powerful and she didn't like them. I have never used any other proactiv products before. I ordered the dissolving blackhead gel just to see if it worked. If not, I'm out $36, no big deal.

I've been using the gel now for about 3 weeks. You're only supposed to use it 1-2 times a week and you're supposed to wash it off after 5 minutes. I choose to sleep with it because my blackheads, as I stated above, are really embedded into my skin and a lot of times facialists have a hard time extracting them.

To say this gel is a miracle is an understatement. I cannot believe the difference I'm seeing on my skin. It's really unbelievable. After the first night I could see results but now, there are large patches on my nose thatare just clear. I know I have a long way to go and that there's no guarantee it will remove all my blackheads, but it's the first product that's ever worked for me. Also, it smells pretty nice, not like chemicals and it doesn't feel harsh or sting or anything like that. It doesn't feel like anything, and it's a very thin gel, so it doesn't feel thick and gross on your face. I would hands down recommend this product to anyone who has blackheads. It surprised me how well this stuff works. The downside is that $36 is pricey for the size you're getting. It's only a small 1 oz. tube, but since you're only supposed to use it sparingly and 1-2 times a week, it can last awhile. I'm going to buy myself a few more bottles because it's really working for me. Before I purchased this product, I did look at the reviews and I saw some people saying it doesn't work for them. I guess it works for some people and for some others it doesn't. Maybe skin type matters or maybe it's more geared toward people like me that have an actual problem with a lot of blackheads and not just one or two popping up once in awhile. I'm really not sure. I do know that it's worked for me and I will recommend it to everyone I know. It's worth the price tag and it really is the only product that's ever worked on me.
