column14:
[[VIDEOID:6c9c337b3b10a23f6d5f19af7d3760ea]]DISCLAIMER: I received this product as part of a promotion in order to submit my honest, unbiased review.

Before entrusting these bottles with my products during a trip, I put them to the test:

1. I filled my bottles with four different liquids of increasing viscosity: water, Cetaphil skin cleanser, body wash, and conditioner.

2. I put all four filled bottles in a quart-sized plastic bag, like you would use for travel. (If you are curious, the four bottles pretty much filled the quart-sized bag. I could have tucked a couple of additional small items in the bag as well, but not much else. Refer to my picture.)

3. I kept the bag on my counter, occasionally using products from the bottles.

4. When the bottles were not in use, they were left inside the bag on their sides.

I know this wasn't exactly a scientific experiment, but I did my test for about two days. Here are my findings:

-The wide mouths on the bottles allow you to fill them and clean them easily.

-The bottles have flat lids and flat bottoms, which means you can set them down on either end. Standing them with the lids down can be handy in helping you get every last drop of your product.

-The silicone material is very soft and flexible, which I consider to be an advantage. Compared to travel bottles made of harder plastic, it is easier to squeeze these bottles.

-When the lid is open (open, not unscrewed), none of my bottles released product when simply held upside down.

-The bottles handled all of my products with ease, regardless of how viscous they were. However, the thinner liquids (water and Cetaphil) seemed to be dispensed more precisely than the thicker liquids (body wash and conditioner). When I stopped squeezing the bottles containing the thinner liquids, the bottles stopped dispensing them nearly automatically. With the the thicker liquids, I noticed a little bit of dribble. It really was not an issue at all, but I wanted to point out that the bottles seem to have slightly less control with thicker liquids. Emphasis on slightly. See video for a demonstration.

-Best of all, the bottles did not leak!

Overall, I am very happy with my purchase. I love the look and feel of these bottles, and after testing them out for a couple of days, I feel like I could trust them during travel.

However, it would be nice if the packaging had included some usage instructions. You say, "But these are just bottles. What kind of instructions do you need?" I have used similar containers in the past, and as a result, I know there are some limitations regarding the types of products you can put in silicone bottles. I also believe silicone bottles should be used only for short-term use and should not be used to hold products for months at a time. It would be helpful if information along these lines had been included with my purchase.tles seem to have slightly less control with thicker liquids. Emphasis on slightly. column6: Instant Peel Natural Dead Skin Remover
column14:
*did not buy this from Amazon but used it from a different retailer, so this is simply a review of the product, not the seller*

At first I thought this exfoliation treatment was great, and I was pretty happy with the results. And then one day I decided to take a look at what the ingredients actually were, and I discovered that this is some terrible stuff to be putting on your skin! Now before I go on, understand that I'm not one of those crazy granola-hippie people who scream "chemiKILLS" at everything; I drink diet soda every once in a while, eat processed foods like everyone else, and the like, but I'm going to be more careful with skincare products now.

This product contains parabens, which are used as a preservative, and they are being scrutinized for their link to cancer and endocrine disruption. They are a naturally occurring chemical but putting it on your skin often can cause it to build up in the fat cells underneath. Parabens can also mimic the hormone estrogen (because it's metabolized into a phytoestrogen), which means those who have endocrine problems/imbalance/sensitivity/disorders need to really be careful how often they are using skin products with parabens.

I'm not going to be using this product any longer, even though It worked pretty well. It's not like parabens are horrible, terrible things to avoid at all costs, I'm just saying to be careful and inform yourselves:)

column13: really good performance for a vegan/natural product
column14:
I have been keeping this on my nightstand and using it before I go to sleep. My hands are dry from frequent washing (I have pets...), even during the summer. I can't always remember to use hand cream during the day, but this has definitely been helping.

It absorbs into the skin fairly quickly. It is not the fastest-absorbing hand cream I've ever used, but it is certainly acceptable. It does not leave my hands feeling too oily (granted, this is for use at night; I have not tried to use this directly before typing on a keyboard). I like the scent and find it to be a nice lavender, not at all cloying or artificial. I love that the fragrance comes from lavender oil. (You can see a full ingredients list lower on the product page.)

This is a vegan product and I'm impressed at how many plant-based alternatives for traditionally animal-sourced products they've found (e.g., collagen, hyaluronic acid, etc.). And they're effective -- my hands are nice and soft.

I'm definitely a fan of this hand cream now!

column6: Opalescence PF 35% Teeth Whitening 8pk of Mint flavor syringes (Latest product) (2 tubes each with 4 syringes)
column13: Excellent. \You'll burn your gums off.\" JK, reference to A Christmas Story."
column14:
I have ordered the same product from other sites before. What struck me as strange was that there was no plastic wrap or expiration date. And when I used it (I've been using 35% for many many years) I could tell it was not that potent and I did not get the same results that I got when I bought it from the dentist.

But this order from Amazon came in the origin wrapping WITH instructions and guaranteed freshness. I feel much better about that. It sure beats $15 a tube from the dentist.

Just FYI, I would NOT use this if you haven't had custom trays made professionally from your dentist. And I would start with a lower peroxide % until you practice applying it. It's an art. I believe 35% is the highest potentcy and it will burn your gums off (literally) and leave big white burn marks on your gums that take weeks to heal if you don't apply it to the trays correctly. Especially if you wear them at night.

Lots of dentists give a free whitening kit (including customer trays) to new customers. They'll as show you how to use them. As you get more proficient, then I would increase the % if you like.

column14:
This is a terrific facial moisturizer for the day. It glides on easily and does not feel heavy, so even if you wear on makeup it does not feel like your face is "weighted" down. Some facial lotions have that feeling because they use ingredients to make your skin puffy to fill out your wrinkles and lines. Has a strong fragrance whilst being applied, but it fades away after a couple minutes. The soft silky feeling last all day.

While it probably takes while to see results for making wrinkles and age spots fade or disappear, only time will tell.

Has a 20 SPF protection against UV A and UV B rays. It does state to reapply every 2 hours if you are using it as a protection outdoors in the sun. Active ingredients for sunscreen are Avobenzone 3%. Octisalate 5%, and Octocrylene 5%.

About two pumps is enough to cover my face and throat.

column14:
Iâ€™m always in search of a hair dryer that can blow dry my thick, curly hair as well as my stylist does. (I know â€¦ I know â€¦ itâ€™s the person not the tool.) When she dries it, she barely has to touch it up with a flat iron. When I dry it â€¦ I have to do a little more work to straighten out the wavy stragglers.

This review compares the Revlon 1875W Tourmaline Ionic Ceramic Dryer, Remington Damage Control (DC) Ceramic Hair Dryer, and this one (Remington T|Studio Silk AC Professional Hair Dryer).

Updated 11 Nov 2016: I switched back to this when my main one died. And downgraded it one star. It's just not as hot as the previous or when I first tried this.

All of them have:
* Same wattage
* Three heat settings
* Two speed settings
* Cool shot feature
* Diffuser and concentrator attachments
* Ionic technology
* Ceramic technology
* Hanging loop

The Revlon does not come with a removable filter, the two Remingtons do. (The TStudio doesnâ€™t say it on the box or description. Company website confirms it.) Revlon and Remington Damage Control have tourmaline technology, the TStudio does not.

The Revlonâ€™s concentrator attachment stays on. The Remingtonâ€™s fall off often. If I put the dryer down to adjust my hair, it comes off some of the time. It's hot to put it back on.

All three take about the same time to dry my hair. I may have gotten slightly better results (less wavy) with the Remingtons than with the Revlon. I say â€œmayâ€ because the difference wasnâ€™t large enough to be clear. Some days I do a better job than others. Human error, you know.

The Damage Control felt like it took less effort and the reason is most likely because itâ€™s the lightest of the three. The shell of the DC and Revlon are plastic while the T|Studio uses better quality materials. But it could be the better quality materials that make it heavier.

I can only assume the DC is cheaper than the T|Studio because of its plastic shell even though it has tourmaline technology, which the T|Studio does not.

Iâ€™ve yet to try the diffusers. Whenever I wear my hair curly, I let it dry naturally. Thatâ€™s the whole point of going curly â€“ not having to do any hair drying. As for noise â€“ I canâ€™t answer which one is quietest because Iâ€™m deaf. Itâ€™s not a good idea to wear hearing aids while drying wet hair. :)

The winner? The Remington DC because it takes the least amount of effort to use and produces the same results as the others. The T|Studio is just too heavy and the Revlon doesnâ€™t perform as well as the DC.s cheaper than the T|Studio because of its plastic shell even though it has tourmaline technology, which the T|Studio does not.

As for noise â€“ I canâ€™t answer which one is quietest because Iâ€™m deaf. Itâ€™s not a good idea to wear hearing aids while drying wet hair. :)

The winner? The Remington DC because it takes the least amount of effort to use and produces the same results as the others. The T|Studio is just too heavy and the Revlon doesnâ€™t perform as well as the DC.

column6: Remington PF7500 F5 Comfort Series Foil Shaver, Men's Electric Razor, Electric Shaver
column14:
This is a good dependable razor. I've been using it for a couple of weeks and it does a decent job.

Of course, it doesn't do as good as job as a razor, but no electric razors do. I've used many different types and even though they all claim they do, none of them come close to a razor.

But I am lazy and this electric razor does a fine job of making me ready for work! I still use an old fashioned straight razor for date nights.

My last electric razor was rotary. I really enjoy the rectangle shape of the razor head on this unit. It allows me to get in close around my beard without worrying about shaving off something I don't want to shave off. It also has a pop up trimmer that is good for making clean lines.

This electric razor has replaced the much more expensive electric razor I had been using. This razor is very reasonably priced and performs very well.

Very much recommend it!

column14:
Favorite face block/lotion yet!
Went looking for a new face sunblock when I started getting sunspots and sunglass lines from casual/occasional sun exposure (driving, short outside chores) even while using a drugstore-brand lotion with SPF 30 daily. Have had some in the past that claimed they were specifically for the face, but were either chalky, pasty, or turned into a sticky mess when makeup was applied on top.

I've used The Blue Lizard Daily Face Sunscreen daily for over a week and very happy with it.
- Rubs in quickly, completely disappears. Isn't tacky, chalky or goopy. Goes on like a more expensive face cream.
- Leaves a smooth surface for applying makeup. I use BareMinerals foundation or Complexion Rescue on top of this, and it goes on well, stays on just fine.
- Didn't irritate my skin or eyes (typically I am prone to eye irritation, but don't get many skin irritations)

column14: I got to try this product for free thanks to CrestÂ® and courtesy of BzzAgent. I am always looking for a good whitening product because I have naturally yellow-ish teeth and drink tea quite often. I have had many great experiences with the Crest brand in the past, and this new product is no different! I like that there are 2 steps- the first is a deep cleansing regular toothpaste that tastes great (nice and minty) and the second is a targeted whitening gel. The instructions on the back of the tube say to use each for one minute, but I probably do a little extra with step one and a little less with step two because my teeth have been pretty sensitive to the peroxide in the whitener. Overall, my teeth do feel nice and clean as a result of using this system, but I think the whitening process has been a bit slow- I see some improvement in areas that were very yellow before but it's not getting as white as i hoped. However, I'm sure this is due to my reduced usage of step 2- I wish I could use more but the sensitivity to cold foods is just not worth it! I will continue to use this product

column14:
I liked this better than the Crest Pro-Health stuff I've used in the past. The first step felt grittier, which to some might seem like a bad thing but I felt like it got my teeth cleaner because it was more abrasive.

Step two was comparable to Crest Pro-Health. I do like the two-step process, but it's hard with my electric toothbrush. My toothbrush runs for an exact amount of time, so I have to stop it in the middle (after guessing how long it's been) and then start it up again, whereupon it runs for another two minutes. Thanks, Crest, for giving me a free sample!

column6: Azfasst Green Tea Facial Gel-Sensitive Skin
column14: I thought turning 40 this year would be hard.  Who would of thought deeper wrinkles and frequent breakouts would happen almost as the clock hit midnight on my birthday.  I tried so many products: skin tighteners, lifters, hemorrhoid cream ect.  Anything to try and lessen my wrinkles. (Side note: Don't use the hemorrhoid cream.  It REALLY burns)  I hated looking so tired all time.  I was complaining to one of my friends about it and she said she used Azfasst.  She always has such beautiful skin. I figured I had tried everything else, I had nothing to lose.  I received the product very quickly.  I loved the packaging!  I used the eye cream every night.  After a few weeks, I saw that my wrinkles were not as deep.  For my breakouts, I used the gel.  My zits went away at a faster rate than if I did nothing.  And even for the ones I picked (we all are guilty of picking, so don't judge me.), the redness was gone within a couple of days of using the gel. My skin tends to be kind of dry, a little flaky and red spots (God, I sound horrible! LOL! My skin is sensitive, what can I say) The combination of the moisturizer and gel totally evened my skin out.  So here is my conclusion: Azfasst is a worthwhile investment.  A little bit goes a long way, so the bottles will last months!  Right now, I am 6 months past my 40th birthday. Thus far, I have had my first mammogram (not fun!), been told I am a candidate for bifocals, am officially called "Ma'am and not Miss" anymore.  BUT......my skin is now BEAUTIFUL!!!  THANK YOU TO THE MAKERS OF AZFASST!!!!  You made turning 40 a lot less traumatic!

column6: Braun M90 Mobile Shaver for Precision Trimming, Great for Travel, Black/Silver
column14:
I'm pleasantly surprised by this electric shaver.

I hadn't owned or used an electric shaver since my teens in the late '90s or early 2000's. When I took to shaving my head with disposable razors, it just never made sense to keep an electric razor for my face. And when I took to simply allowing my facial hair to grow out (either as a crazy beard or as reasonably maintained stubble), I never had a need for a razor that would give me a clean-shave,

But I bought this shaver on a whim (perhaps thinking I should try the clean-shaven look to create the appearance that I'm putting in some amount of effort). Given the price, and given that I've strictly used disposable razors for the better part of my adult life, I wasn't expecting much from this shaver.

But it does the job.

I took some old hair clippers (meant to be used on the head) and gave my facial hair a quick buzz without any attachments, just to get the hair as short as possible in preparation for this little shaver. And I found that it gave me a pretty smooth shave. It took longer than I would have expected (perhaps because I have poor technique or an oddly shaped face, or perhaps I just had unreasonable expectations because it's been so long since I shaved with an electric shaver).

And my skin felt irritated in a handful of spots. Though, as I explained, I've been in the habit of never really sporting a clean-shave look... so it makes sense that my skin was unaccustomed to such a close shave after so long with a beard or with scruff of some kind.

Still, I am pleased with the results. With some more attention paid to my technique, and with some more attention paid to my skin (pre- and after-shave skin products of some kind, I imagine), I feel like I would be able to produce a very close shave with minimal effort, time, or discomfort.

column6: Basil (linalool CT) Essential Oil 100% Pure, Undiluted, Therapeutic Grade.
column14:
This is my first experience with Basil Essential Oil. I'm not newbie to Essential Oils but I've never used Basil oil.

This 10 ml bottle of Planet Therapy Basil Essential Oil comes in a small amber colored glass bottle with a black screw on cap. I like that it's marked on the top with a stick on label that shows it's "Basil". The label makes it easy to locate when you acquire as many little amber colored bottles as I have.

The price point on this bottle of oil is reasonable at $8.49. The bottle doesn't carry the "Therapeutic Grade" wording, however the online description states that it is. I always look for that wording on quality oils or seals of approval and there were none of those either. So, it makes me wonder even though the smell seems right.

When you remove the cap there is a eurodropper that releases the oil 1 drop at a time. I like this because these small bottles go fast if you pour too much. With this one and any EO's a little goes a long way.

The first thing I do with all my oils when I receive them is to take a deep sniff. When I open this bottle I am delighted with the pleasant very earthy smell of basil. Very much like the plant I have growing on my patio. This oil has a good quality and doesn't seem to be diluted or altered in any way. When I close my eyes it takes me straight to my favorite Italian Restaurant. So, if you don't want to smell like Italian food don't get too much or any of this on you.

I first tried it in my diffuser and it wasn't one of my favorites for diffusing. After doing a little oil research I believe my next use for it will be to mix it with some of my wintergreen, peppermint and carrier oil in a roller bottle for my aching muscles after workouts.

I will also be making Homemade Bath salts with some of this oil as well using the wintergreen, peppermint and lavender.
Since Basil oil is good for consuming I will also be adding to my next pot of spaghetti. I also read that it's good for anxiety and focus.

I'm giving this oil 5 stars because the price is right and the quality seems right as well.

column6: Lipogel Caffeine Slimming & Slendering System Cream 8 Oz.
column14:
The gel is cooling, with a fresh scent - the scent doesn't last, but when you first open the jar it sort of smells like opening a can of Sprite or 7Up. (The cooling effect is what is supposed to shrink the fat cells down, creating a more smoother, softer looking skin/body. Hence the appearance of inch loss. Whereas the chili or hot slimming products are supposed to 'melt' the fat. Hence the belief of some that a person should use both, to really see 'weight loss' ) As someone who's tried most slimming gels or creams currently on the market, I have to say the cooling effect of this one is a bit like putting on Icy Hot sports rub. It's not as intense as some that I have tried.
As a person who also never works out - bad I know. I tried this product for approx. a week, with no exercise or wrap. And I still saw firming on the areas where I applied this gel. I also spent one day working out with the gel around my midsection, and a thermal wrap over it. (Thermal wrap or any wrap actually already adds heat to the area, causing the covered area to sweat more.) What I found was that I didn't notice how much sweat poured out of me, till I removed the band. Which normally after a 1/2 hour, I'm drenched & really uncomfortable. So, for me, would not use the wrap in future in combination with the gel, but def. after the wrap to tighten what hopefully was melted off. Though have read other's who saw more sweat & results with a wrap then without. (Personally, would recommend a chili oil or heat based product) So, this is where I would recommend people to try it out for themselves as they may receive a different result than mine.
Also bare in mind, there's been no such thing, in my experience, where I've been able to put on a cream/gel or even take a pill, and the next day the jeans I've been unable to fit for so many years, suddenly miraculously fits. It's not a work out in a bottle. (That's coming from a person who doesn't work out mind) But I have lost a cm or so, and will probably end up losing an inch, overall, by the end of the container. Which considering a lot of products that tote the same thing and don't deliver even that much, was very pleased with my purchase.

That means if you need to cover an eye that can still see but needs to be isolated, you're instead going to see tons of light because there is no foam to stop big gaps since these never fit your eye perfectly. It also means it's going to be much less comfortable because you have a rigid edge pressing against your face instead of soft foam.

I have attached a picture to show what I'm talking about. It's a little bit hard to make it out because it's black on black, but my finger is pointing at an eye patch that has foam around the edge. This one is on the left with no foam.

column6: Natural Organic Treatment for Eczema
column13: This made a difference faster than medication did.
column14:
I have two dry spots on either side of my nose that have been consistently peeling for months. I tried prescription medication and that just seemed to exacerbate the situation, made it drier and itchy.

I was offered the opportunity to review ruly Pure Recovery Cream at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased opinion. Before I received it, I received an e-mail from the company...letting me know if I had any questions or skin concerns that I should feel free to write them and they would get back with me. WHen I told them about the dry spots, I was advised to put cream on those two areas two to three time a day, that the perfect PH for skin products is 5.5, and that my cleanser might be one of the causes of this issue. I was also advised they will be coming out with a cleanser soon, and asked if I could take before and after pictures.

I have to apologize for the difference in lighting...I'm not home at the moment...and that's the lighting I'm stuck with. Even with that, you can see there is a major difference. I was peeling pieces off that area almost every morning. I haven't had to do that for the past three days! I just take a tiny dab of this cream in those two spots, and it has seemingly worked a miracle that prescription medication couldn't. It only took a matter of days for this cream to work. I am so excited I am going to start using this as my moisturizer and see if there are any changes in texture. I do plan to ask if i can use this in combination with rosehip oil and vitamin C serum.

I can highly recommend True Pure Recovery cream, and will buy again when I've used the container up.

column13: I love vanilla anyways and so the scent alone will keep ...
column14: I have naturally curly hair. I have never been able to just wake up and walk out the door with my hair natural. It is frizzy, unruly (and possibly scary) hair that I feel will never be tamed :( I tried Silk 18 Natural Conditioner based on reviews by other curly haired women and decided to give it a try. I cannot rave more about the smell! I love vanilla anyways and so the scent alone will keep me using it! It is warm and inviting and very soothing after a long day. As for the conditioning, I have used it 4 times so far. I take a shower before I go to bed and let my hair air dry (I know that this is part of the reason my hair is so unmanageable in the morning, but I like to go to bed clean ;) I normally awaken to a tangled, frizzy mess that looks as if it has more purpose in a birds nest than on my head. After using Silk 18 Natural Conditioner, I notice my hair is exponentially less frizzy! It actually is quite smooth at the top. The ends are still a bit frizzy but again, its probably because I have long hair and go to sleep with it wet. However, though they are frizzy I, I have notice they are less frizzy! I also am able to straighten my hair and style it way easier than normal and it looks healthier!!! It feels so much softer when I run my fingers through it and it seems to keep the style longer. I will definitely be buying this product again. I do wish it came in a bigger bottle.

column6: Remington D3190A Damage Control Ceramic Hair Dryer, Ionic Dryer, Hair Dryer, Purple
column13: Was a winner until the heating element gave out too quickly
column14:
Iâ€™m always in search of a hair dryer that can blow dry my thick, curly hair as well as my stylist does. (I know â€¦ I know â€¦ itâ€™s the person not the tool.) When she dries it, she barely has to touch it up with a flat iron. When I dry it â€¦ I have to do a little more work to straighten out the wavy stragglers.

This review compares the Revlon 1875W Tourmaline Ionic Ceramic Dryer, Remington T|Studio Silk AC Professional Hair Dryer, and this one (Remington Damage Control (DC) Ceramic Hair Dryer).

All of them have:
* Same wattage
* Three heat settings
* Two speed settings
* Cool shot feature
* Diffuser and concentrator attachments
* Ionic technology
* Ceramic technology
* Hanging loop

The Revlon does not come with a removable filter, the two Remingtons do. (The TStudio doesnâ€™t say it on the box or description. Company website confirms it.) Revlon and Remington Damage Control have tourmaline technology, the TStudio does not.

The Revlonâ€™s concentrator attachment stays on. The Remingtonâ€™s fall off often. If I put the dryer down to adjust my hair, it comes off some of the time. It's hot to put it back on.

All three take about the same time to dry my hair. I may have gotten slightly better results (less wavy) with the Remingtons than with the Revlon. I say â€œmayâ€ because the difference wasnâ€™t large enough to be clear. Some days I do a better job than others. Human error, you know.

The Damage Control felt like it took less effort and the reason is most likely because itâ€™s the lightest of the three. The shell of the DC and Revlon are plastic while the T|Studio uses better quality materials. But it could be the better quality materials that make it heavier.

I can only assume the DC is cheaper than the T|Studio because of its plastic shell even though it has tourmaline technology, which the T|Studio does not.

Iâ€™ve yet to try the diffusers. Whenever I wear my hair curly, I let it dry naturally. Thatâ€™s the whole point of going curly â€“ not having to do any hair drying. As for noise â€“ I canâ€™t answer which one is quietest because Iâ€™m deaf. Itâ€™s not a good idea to wear hearing aids while drying wet hair. :)

The winner? The Remington DC because it takes the least amount of effort to use and produces the same results as the others. The T|Studio is just too heavy and the Revlon doesnâ€™t perform as well as the DC.

Update November 16, 2015: I downgraded the dryer from 5 stars to 3 stars because the heating element is giving out. It has been getting as hot in the last couple of weeks. When I switched back to an older dryer, I could see a big difference. Lasted only three months.enever I wear my hair curly, I let it dry naturally. column6: ASDM Beverly Hills 40% Lactic Acid Medical Strength, 1oz
column14: I ordered this product for some very annoying whiteheads and light acne on my chin and around the mouth that I've had since switching my birth control last year. I've tried several different washes and products over the past year and none seemed to help as I keep getting whiteheads that want to hang around for months at a time. I finally decided a chemical peel was my best option and ordered this product after seeing the prices of a professional treatment. I wasn't in any particular hurry to get any acid burns on my face, though. So as a nervous first-time user, I diluted it to 20% strength, allowed it to sit for about 90 seconds, and washed it off under the shower for 30 seconds. While the product is working, there is a slight burning sensation and a "thick" texture that you feel on your skin while washing it off. After blotting with a towel, your skin will feel much smoother and have a "glow". At 20% strength, there was no redness and no downtime. I actually followed up with a emollient wrinkle cream that has a much lower lactic acid content (Pond's brand) and a generous spread of Acnomel (sulfur and resorcinol). I've done this once a week for the past two weeks and it has made a significant difference in lessening my acne and improving the texture of my skin. Zits are healing and all but the more stubborn whiteheads are gone while those remaining are reduced in size. I think I will continue this for another two weeks and then use it once a month for maintenance. Also, I think this product is a good value because you only need 1-2ml of product if applying with a fan brush so you can get 15-30 applications out of one bottle.

column6: Hera UV Mist Cushion - C21 Cool Vanila Cover SPF50
column13: Here I am at work, writing an amazon review and wondering how I'm going to get this product off my face before anyone notices.
column14:
EDIT: Discovered that I was sold a fake product through a Prime seller. For those looking to check, you can look for the metal pin that holds the cushion refill hinge together and see if there's a hole running the length of the pin, making the pin hollow. If so, your product is genuine! If not, it's probably fake. This holds for all Amore Pacific branded cushions. No wonder my product experience was so bad.

When I first apply this cushion it looks great! Fantastic! Good color match, even application. This is going to be a good day!

After an hour, however, it clings to every crack, crevice, flake, and pore on my face. It is truly remarkable how awful this cushion will make your skin look. The final straw was today, when I tried using it during a very mild tretinoin peel - I looked like I had a peeling rash. I looked like a snake mid-shed. I looked like I had Hera-C21-Cushion-Colored glue peeling off from all over my face. All of these are true.

I didn't expect miracles, of course, but no other cushion I own shows skin flaws like the Hera cushion does. I am so disappointed. Even when my skin is GREAT, it still migrates and sits on my pores. I have dry skin and have never experienced this phenomenon with any other product. Here I am at work, looking at my glue-face in my compact mirror, wondering how I'm going to sneak to the bathroom to get this cushion off my face before someone sees and suggests I get to a doctor. Wish me luck, you guys. This is going to be a bad day.

Unless you have PERFECT skin, I would highly suggest you stay away. I always wondered if people posting 1-star reviews were just being vindictive or highly critical. I can assure you, for me this is not the case. I used up almost the entire refill of this product before I finally gave up on this cushion. Also, just in case you were wondering, I ordered this from a Prime seller, so I highly doubt I received a fake product. The only good thing about this product is the case, which is nice to look at. I'll probably use it with a Sulwhasoo refill instead.I'll probably use it with a Sulwhasoo refill instead.

column6: Now Foods Mental Focus Oil Blend 1 oz
column14: I have never written a bad review & i usually love the NOW brand for vitamins & other things.... but my first time using the NOW Food Mental Focus blend 5 drops in a diffuser for maybe 2-3 minutes (diffuser did 30 min on & 30 min off rotation) & i started having a severe allergic reaction. As far as i know, i am not allergic to anything, but this EO mixture inhaled via diffuser caused me to start to feel dizzy, then weak, then started to cause my throat to feel like it was swelling up... all within maybe 3 minutes. Luckily i work with a lot of nurses & i had one take my blood pressure because i felt like i was about to pass out- my BP was 188/110. Then one of my coworkers walked with me outside to try to get some fresh air into my lungs & try to relax. After a bit she checked my BP again & it was 140/90, then after about another 15-20 minutes it went down to 110/60. Even after i calmed down a bit i still felt very week & my throat felt constricted. I felt ok enough to drive home as i figured the symptoms would ease up over the course of the evening.... but the throat pressure/constricted feeling was still there at 10:45pm. I then called my Pharmacist & told him the situation, asked him what i should take- he told me Benadryl, so i took the recommended dosage (2 tabs for adults) & waitied for some signs of relief.... i started to feel a little sleepy & a bit better between 1-2am & went to sleep. I woke up today thinking the Benadryl had cured the weird throat constriction feeling, but it started to come back.... so i am still, as i am typing this, having a really terible case of dry mouth & i still have the throat pressure. I have no idea if i am allergic to the mixture of these oils or one specifically, but i just thought i may want to warn others out there that even a person who has NO known allergies can have a possible allergic reaction to Essential Oils.... just be careful.

column6: Sulwhasoo Evenfair Perfecting Cushion #13 Light Pink (15g*2)
column13: Perfect performance, bad shades. So sad. The search for the perfect cushion continues.
column14:
I like this cushion a lot! It's got great texture, and it seems to last the whole work day. It doesn't migrate! Hooray! It does, however, have this semi-dewy finish that I'm quite fond of. When it's first applied, it looks very dewy, but it dries down after about 15 minutes. Of all the cushions, I prefer this one's performance the most. I experienced no sensitivity from this cushion, and it didn't seem to affect my skin negatively in any way at all. The coverage is firmly medium, but still has a light enough texture that it doesn't feel heavy on the face. It lasts on my skin the whole work day.

I picked it in shade 13 "Light Pink", which actually seems quite dark in comparison to some of my other cushions. It's also quite pinky/orange - when I wear this, it looks as if I put on fake tanner. If you usually wear fair, neutral toned foundations, I'd suggest staying away from this shade. For reference, the Hera shade C21 is a tiiiny bit dark for my skin, but the undertones in the Hera cushion are spot on for my skin shade. I wear Innisfree's shade 21 just fine.

If this cushion came in a shade suitable for my skin tone, I'd stop searching for a cushion and cash out with Sulwhasoo. As it is - 4 stars.

column13: I like the Floxite 10x magnifying mirror
column14: I like the Floxite 10x magnifying mirror.  There is no distortion in the glass, light is bright, and base is stable. It is adjustable up and down but not sideways.  This 10x shows every facial flaw, which is what I was looking for, so I can easily apply makeup or concealer as needed, pluck eyebrows, put on eye liner, etc. without my glasses.  This mirror is not as compact as my previous Floxite 8x with detachable mirror that I used for years, and the 10x is too bulky to try and pack in a suitcase.  The base is also taller and thicker so it takes up more room.  This is not a concern for me, but it might be too big to fit in a small area.  Hopefully, the bulb will last a long time since the replacement price listed is $20 inclusive of shipping. The cost was a bit high for my budget, but I know Floxite makes a good product.  There is a wide variety of Floxite mirror styles available with varying magnification strengths; it's just a matter of finding the one that fits your needs.

column13: Wonderful moisturizer for sensitive skin (and affordable!)

I have extremely sensitive skin that reacts to EVERYTHING, so finding a good, and affordable, moisturizer is a difficult task. In this short time, I've already been able to eliminate all other serums/creams/moisturizers from my daily skincare routine.

While the cream is thick, it feels very light when applied, and absorbs quickly. The mild scent dissipates very quickly. I have noticed a slight film leftover if I apply too much of the product, but scaling back the amount applied resolved that issue immediately. A little really does go a long way.

The friendliness and prompt communication from the company's owner is also a refreshing change of pace from dealing with most vendors/larger companies. If you have any hesitations or doubts about this product, it really is as good as described.

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column13: Try It, I think You'll Like It!
column14:
I actually enjoyed this product and more than likely will be buying it again. I have to honestly say that this is the best tasting toothpaste (the step 1) that I have ever had. I read other reviews that said the taste was disagreeable because of the sweetener, however I LOVED it. The step 2 tastes just like other whitening products, not good, but tolerable (and it isn't like you are swallowing it).

Like other reviews state you use step 1 for one minute, then without rinsing use step 2 for one minute. I found this routine easy to add to my brushing regimen. I love the idea of whitening ALL your teeth and not just the front ones like some whitening kits provide.

I am only giving it 4 stars because I didn't see any HUGE improvements in the whiteness of my teeth but I DID see improvement. I will also be buying this when I run out - I got to try it free from CrestÂ® offered thru BzzAgent and I am glad I did because otherwise I don't think I would have given it a try.

I recommend buying it and giving it a try for yourself!

column6: Old Spice Wild Collection Bearglove Men's Body Wash 16 Fluid Ounce
column13: I Still Can't Repair Military Helicopters, But I Smell Great!
column14:
The advertising for Bearglove Body Wash asks "Can you imagine a powerful, fearsome grizzly bear who can repair military helicopters and also speak confidently about important world affairs?" If you answer affirmatively, then, they say "this is the body wash for you". I do keep up with geopolitics, and I may on occasion be a powerful, fearsome grizzly bear, but that is normally due to a lack of caffeine or sleep. This body wash has not conferred on me the ability to mend military helicopters, however, despite using it daily for several weeks. I'm a bit disappointed by that, but gave it five stars anyway, because it is an excellent product that has a genuinely pleasant, masculine smell: it's not like patchouli, musk, or stoat in any way, but it's pleasant and clean smelling. I bought this on a whim when it was on sale, but when I run out I like it enough to pay full price.

Recommended for male humans or grizzly bears.

column6: Absolute Gold 24K Deep Peeling Gel- 24 KARAT GOLD, PEARL POWDER and GINGER EXTRACT. Excellent for all skin types. 2.04 fl.oz-60 ml. Eliminates the dead skin cells and leaving skin glowing and radiant. (FRAGRANCE FREE, PARABEN FREE, PETROLEUM FREE).
column14:
I decided to give this product a try because I really truly love peeling gels. In case you aren't familiar, they are a quick and simple way to remove dead skin cells from the surface of your skin, and reveal radiance. Also, by removing the dead skin cells so quickly, whatever moisturizing or toning product you then put on, will penetrate better to your skin. Since using peels such as these I have been very pleased with the results.

When I got the chance to try this I was excited, it looked gorgeous, it has flecks of gold suspended throughout the gel, and there is actual science to back up gold being good for skin care. It is said to add radiance and be good for inflammation. Not to mention its just so luxurious! The packaging that this arrives in is lovely, it has a little spoon (that I am sure I will lose, unfortunately) to scoop out the perfect amount of gel, and it comes in a little tub. The box is very pretty as well. I do wish they had invested in a pump instead, I would have preferred it for hygine reasons. Since I know I will lose the spoon, I will eventually end up needing to use my finger to get the gel out of the tub, which isnt the most hygenic.

The company could do to invest in a better type of seal for their little tubs as well, mine was still sealed, but due to the chemicals they use in their peeling gel, it looks as though it had corroded the seal somewhat. I removed the seal and ended up scooping just a bit off the top because it looks as though a tiny bit of the metal seal had melted into my gel, but it was otherwise fine. Once I did all that, I tested it.

I first tested on the back of my hand and on my inner elbow, patch test, of course! I reccomend that to anyone who buys products online! I took a small amount and rubbed it in, let it sit for just a second, and then rubbed it some more, in a circular motion. Dead skin cells began to come right off! It almost looked like when you are erasing with a pencil or something, kinda gross. I then just took a warm washcloth and wiped it off, and my skin felt so soft. At that point, I had to use it on my face, and I had the exact same results, my skin feels great! I really do like this peeling gel, even with the packaging flaws. I hope they fix them in the next run, because thats really my only issue with them, the product itself is fantastic.
I got this product at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.ing, kinda gross. I then just took a warm washcloth and wiped it off, and my skin felt so soft. At that point, I had to use it on my face, and I had the exact same results, my skin feels great! I really do like this peeling gel, even with the packaging flaws. column6: Oral-B Pro 5000 SmartSeries Power Rechargeable Electric Toothbrush with Bluetooth Connectivity Powered by Braun
column14:
The toothbrush itself is fine. Almost. It's the absolutely useless features built (and charged for) in that made me angry and even more so that you have to read the whole manual to understand how to access them because the 5000 doesn't have a display. But Bluetooth. All you need is a smartphone and a waterproof case for it if you brush your teeth under the shower like I do. This is the most ridiculous feature of them all. Run an app on your smartphone to track how you brush your teeth? Really? If you want to track your kids then stand behind them and watch them. Because you can't use the toothbush and track on more than one smartphone. If you want this to be a conversation piece at the next dinner party you probably miss the automated posting of your cleaning pattern on Facebook and the direct video streaming from your gums to Youtube.

If you press too hard (in your toothbrush's opinion) it flashes a red light and reduces speed so you don't hurt your gums. Really? You don't know when you are hurting yourself and need your brush to tell you? Unfortunately the damn thing also kicks in when you press too hard on a tooth. Very annoying. I haven't figured out the polishing and whitening mode (which is why I bought that thing in the first place) because I got irritated after flipping through 20+ pages. For Christs sake I just want to brush my teeth and I decide myself when I'm done. And that is when I covered everyone of my teeth from all sides and not when some timer starts buzzing. And the deep clean mode? It just adds another minute to the timer. If I would go by the timer I would never get to the last quadrant in my mouth. This is a hyped up product full of gadgets that the world doesn't need. I got the Oral-B PRO 1000 instead which cleans almost the same. The 5000 seems to have a little more power but only as long as you don't press on it. Other than that the result (clean teeth) is the same. Only for $31 instead of $101.

column6: Braun
column13: A bitter end to an otherwise nice shaver
column14:
This is a fantastic electric razor. I previously had a Braun 390cc from the mid 2000s and the battery was finally shot. I was able to score a Philips Norelco 9300 on promotion but was hugely disappointed with that shaver. The build quality was subpar for such an expensive shaver and the cleaning station was a disaster (software bugs made it clean endlessly for hours and hours). I returned it and got the Braun 790cc. I should've got this to begin with...

Update: The Braun has taken a turn for the worse. My Series 7 has made two trips to the repair depot because the cleaning station incorrectly senses the fluid level and thinks it's empty, when it is not. It refuses to run a cleaning cycle if it senses the fluid level is empty. Braun service replaces the cleaning station but, based on the numerous complaints online, it is clear to me that this is a fundamental engineering issue with the Series 7 and not an isolated case.

Replacement foils are now very hard to find and prohibitively expensive. I wouldn't even consider investing in a new foil/cutter block because my Series 7 will soon be out of warranty. My feedback for Braun's engineering team would be to go back to basics and get rid of the complex electronic crap that breaks down and the customer won't be able to fix once it's out of warranty. You have lost a loyal customer.and the alcohol based formula leaves the shaver head sanitized and oil-free. I found the fresh lemon scent Braun uses to smell better than the cheap cologne scent Philips uses in the Norelco cartridges. I appreciate that after 10 minutes the lights on the cleaning station turn off.

I expect this shaver to last as long as my old 390cc. Overall I'm very happy and will remain a loyal Braun customer so long as they continue to produce great quality electric shavers.

column6: Blue Lizard Blue Lizard Australian Sunscreen SPF 30+
column14: I have a 3 year old who, if he had his way, would spend every minute of every day outside, and every minute near any body of water in it/ sprayed by it/ playing with it.  The beginning of this summer we were using Babyganics 50+ sunscreen in the pump bottle, and thought I loved it. Was happy to be using a 'natural' product. Then noticed that after even an hour outside in partial sun, without water play, we were both getting some sun and it didn't seem to be working. I was reapplying & reapplying. Then my husband got some Banana Boat Baby (which horrified my somewhat-granola-y preferences - and furthermore, irritated my son's eyes and wouldn't stay on for 10 minutes of splashing around in a baby pool). Have previously tried Honest Co. natural sunblock, but found it greasy. So Googling I go, and find Blue Lizard recommended again and again.  Picked the Sport over the Baby version in attempts to avoid excessive applications on a wet wiggly preschooler.  First test was about 2 hours splashing around the baby pool on our deck which gets a good amount of sun. He didn't get a bit of color or show any skin irritation, and the block stayed on! (I did reapply once to more exposed areas out of habit). I used it on myself as well, and have always been able to feel that exact moment when sunblock stopped working and didn't get that at all.  PROS - Love that it rubs in so quickly and feels nice on your skin. Not chalky, pasty, goopy. More like a nice body lotion. This also makes it quick and easy to apply to wiggly kids. - Excellent water resistance - Nice, very light scent - Has not irritated our eyes  CONS - Zero so far!

column13: Neutrogena's Rosy Blush, Illuminous Illuminating Powder and Bronzed Bronzer
column14:
I tried three different products -- Rosy blush, Bronzed bronzer and Luminous illuminating powder. My skin is light/medium in tone and for me a little goes a long way â€“ I avoid clown-face. So, the Rosy blush was an excellent choice â€“ a reasonably pale peachy/rosy neutral color. For application I used a big blush brush. It picked up the almost matte powder well and distributed it evenly. I had no caking or clumping or loss of an unreasonable amount of powder. No unnatural glitterâ€“ just a little color and subtle glow.

The Luminous illuminating powder is also very subtle â€“ again it fits my preference. Anything in either extreme -- too matte or too glittery â€“ can look harsh and unnatural. But this powder has the barest hint of a glow and I used it on areas around my eyes that can are in shadow and look dark â€“ for example the areas on either side of the bridge of my nose. Too light a powder and you get raccoon eyes â€“ this is the perfect hint of coverage with light reflecting properties.

The Bronzed bronzer is my least favorite of the three products â€“ probably my own fault for never mastering the use of bronzers. I did try it on my eye lids as an eye shadow substitute and although it worked somewhat well, it is not a shade I would normally select.

This brandâ€™s creams and skin care products are always in the sample basket at my dermatologistâ€™s office. She has recommended specific products from the line, and although not cosmetics it does offer some reassurance to me of the basic quality.

column6: Aloe Vera Oil Pure Organic 8 Oz
column13: Aloe Very Oil:  A nice plus for the skin
column14:
I use Shea Butter and combine it with this and coconut oil to make my own "shea loe" foot creme (you can use it anywhere, but my feet get very rough). I add fragrance oils (strong, but synthetic) and/or essential oils (natural, but concentrated) for fragrance.

I put this is little boxes or jars and give them to my friends., and keep a few on hand for myself. In addition, I use this oil and others to make a carrier oil base for natural essential oil bug deterrent. I put those in little blue rollover containers, and keep one in my purse.

If you are wondering why I use both fragrance oils and essential oils, there is a good reason. I have two friends at church, and both are sensitive to chemicals-- after shaves, lotions, perfumes, scented, and even UNSCENTED air fresheners, really bother these people--they break out into rashes.

I travel with one of these people regularly, and in one motel, she had to sleep in the car, the scent (we think it was in the carpet) was so bad. This condition is more common than you might imagine. So I can use these carrier oils with a bit of essential oils, and make pleasant smelling things: lotions, cremes, etc. The fact that it is Aloe Vera oil means it is soothing to the skin, which is a nice plus.

column6: Azfasst Eye Cream
column14: I thought turning 40 this year would be hard.  Who would of thought deeper wrinkles and frequent breakouts would happen almost as the clock hit midnight on my birthday.  I tried so many products: skin tighteners, lifters, hemorrhoid cream ect.  Anything to try and lessen my wrinkles. (Side note: Don't use the hemorrhoid cream.  It REALLY burns)  I hated looking so tired all time.  I was complaining to one of my friends about it and she said she used Azfasst.  She always has such beautiful skin. I figured I had tried everything else, I had nothing to lose.  I received the product very quickly.  I loved the packaging!  I used the eye cream every night.  After a few weeks, I saw that my wrinkles were not as deep.  For my breakouts, I used the gel.  My zits went away at a faster rate than if I did nothing.  And even for the ones I picked (we all are guilty of picking, so don't judge me.), the redness was gone within a couple of days of using the gel. My skin tends to be kind of dry, a little flaky and red spots (God, I sound horrible! LOL! My skin is sensitive, what can I say) The combination of the moisturizer and gel totally evened my skin out.  So here is my conclusion: Azfasst is a worthwhile investment.  A little bit goes a long way, so the bottles will last months!  Right now, I am 6 months past my 40th birthday. Thus far, I have had my first mammogram (not fun!), been told I am a candidate for bifocals, am officially called "Ma'am and not Miss" anymore.  BUT......my skin is now BEAUTIFUL!!!  THANK YOU TO THE MAKERS OF AZFASST!!!!  You made turning 40 a lot less traumatic!

column6: Fogless Shower Mirror - EASY INSTALL - SHATTER PROOF - Includes Razor Hook - Modern - Anti-Fog Nanotechnology - Exclusive To Amazon
column14:
Fogless Shower Mirror - EASY INSTALL - SHATTER PROOF - Includes Razor Hook - Modern - Anti-Fog Nanotechnology - Exclusive To Amazon

The Cassani Fogless Shower mirror is oval and measures 7.5 x 5.7 x 0.1 inches, it comes with two different hooks, mirror, and instructions. Please read the instructions before you begin to unpack your mirror as it contains pertinent information on installation.
Decide where you want your mirror, it is preferable to have it out of running water range so it does not obstruct your view by water splashing on it, although keep it nearer to the shower head. This may require you to stand in your tub to find the perfect height. Once you do clean the area well wipe dry and use rubbing alcohol to clean the surface and apply the first hook, it is the one with only one hook on it. Remove backing and apply the hook to the wall for at least 45 seconds.

Do not remove the covering from the mirror yet, but set it on the hook and find a place to put the second hook which will hold your razor that is why there are two hooks on it. We have found you can put your razor on it across or hang the head through it leaving the metal blades inward or outward whichever you prefer. Again follow the above instructions on how to hand the second hook same as the first. Allow both to adhere for a couple hours, then remove the covering from the mirror and hang it on the first hook, and the razor in the second.

Now you are ready for your shaving experience with your new Fogless Shower Mirror. Cleaning the mirror is not difficult, but do not using cleaning supplies. You can rinse it with water and use your hand to wipe of excess water, or use water and vinegar 50/50 doing the same process by wiping it off with your hand. Cleaning supplies and rubbing it with a towel or cloth will scratch your mirror. These do not last forever and will need to be replaced, but if you take care and follow the instructions you will get your moneys worth out of your product.

I am pleased with this purchase, it also gave use some family time installing the mirror as everyone wanted to try it out. *This review is my 100% honest opinion, I have received this product for testing purposes at a reduced rate or free.
I recommend this product for everyone that shaves in the shower and tired of fogged up mirrors, or hair in the sink.ut of your product.

column6: Beard Balm - All Natural Easy-to-Use Leave-in Beard Conditioner - Handmade in Detroit - Original Scent
column14: Having discovered Beard Balm, a self-described badass product from Detroit (which could totally use everyone's support), I had to get some for my husband to at least try it out, because why not?  It turns out it was more than just a gag gift.  The stuff works.  While I absolutely love my husband's beard (seriously we have an agreement: I keep my hair long and he doesn't go clean shaven), he doesn't always have time for proper grooming and mainenance, so his normally awesome beard can take on that 'just found my way back to civilization after months lost on the Appalacian Trail' look with the texture of steel wool.  But the balm can actually wrangle it back under control and make it cuddlably soft.  The only caveat is that it does have a powerful scent to it (or at least the kind I bought does, which since it doesn't have any special name on it, I am going to assume is original flavor), so I'd advise buying just one at first to see if that's a deal breaker for you.  I acclimated to it, so Beard Balms still one of our go to products, but I feel I should warn you.  Otherwise the stuff is amazing and very amusing if you bother to read the instructions (which we were gloriously not deprived of thanks to my feminine intuition and the fact that I just like to read).

column6: L'OrÃ©al Paris Revitalift Triple Power Day Lotion SPF 20, 1.7 fl. oz. (Packaging May Vary)
column14:
This is a nice, lightweight moisturizer, with a good level of sunscreen. It's a little perfume-y, but not too bad, and the scent fades quickly. It doesn't leave my skin greasy or shiny, but it doesn't make my skin look particularly great either. I am not much of a believer in anti-aging or wrinkle prevention properties, but I do think a good moisturizer should make my skin look nice right away. My favorite Loreal moisturizer is the Youth Code Skin Recharger Day/Night cream, which makes my skin look amazing, right away. But it has no sunscreen, and that tends to reduce the "feel"--even though it's a good idea.

I haven't noticed any fading of spots, but I've had my freckles for many decades and I'd be kind of scared of what might take them out now...

Overall, I think this is a nice daytime cream, and I think it is ideally suited for travel use, since it's below the TSA limit for liquids, and in a nice, lightweight durable plastic bottle.

column14: I have been using OZ Naturals for a couple years and love all the products ( Vit C, Vit A Serum, Toner, Eye Gel and the A Moisturizer.  The Natural Sunscreen is new for me - started using it Spring of 2015.  I love all of the natural ingredients, the antioxidants and especially like the fact that it has two powerful sunscreen agents, Zinc Oxide and Titanium Dioxide. Even with these two sun screen powerhouses this product is not irritating to my sensitive skin.  I will share a secret on the application:  don't rub it in too much or you may get little pilling effects.  I will lightly rub it in and then I gently pat it to finish off.  I saw a review complaining about the pilling and the whitish hue left behind.  You have my remedy on the pilling and the light white hue may be because you put too much on to begin with or, as with me, it fades and I always put foundation over the sunscreen so NO Problem!  I  will share that I did a lot of research on sun screens and now understand that if you want protection zinc oxide and titanium is the way to go ....I am very happy with this product.

column6: InstaNatural Organic Rosehip Seed Oil - 100% Pure & Unrefined Virgin Oil - Natural Moisturizer for Face, Skin, Hair, Stretch Marks, Scars, Wrinkles & Fine Lines - Omega 6, Vitamin A & C - 4 Oz
column13: but decided to try this one due to the good reviews. However
column14:
Unlike most reviewers here, I purchased this product with my own money. I have used many rosehip seed oils from different brands, but decided to try this one due to the good reviews. However, this one by Instanatural is nothing like the rosehip seed oil I know and love.

Firstly, I received the bottle in a dented, scuffed up box, which I thought nothing of - perhaps just a rough postal journey. Next, I pumped the oil into my palms, I noticed the color was very different to every other rosehip seed oil I've tried - it was brown, rather than light yellow/orange. And lastly, the smell of the product hit me. A lot of people complain in general about the smell of rosehip seed oil. It has an earthy, natural smell to it that isn't the most appealing to many. However, this one smells exactly like SOY SAUCE. I'm not being over dramatic for the sake of an interesting review..ha it just really smells like soy sauce. Either this product isn't rosehip seed oil or it is rancid. In my honest opinion, I would look at other brands if you want to buy facial oils, as it looks like Instanatural gives out a lot of free/discounted product for good reviews.

column14:
This is my favorite natural deodorant. A lot of people try natural deodorants with natural soap. This may seem totally obvious to some but I have realized that you have to get your pits 100% clean before putting deodorant on in the first place. Meaning: If you use "natural soap" or not strong enough soap and are not getting your pits clean enough - NO natural deodorant is going to cover up that stink.

This is not like 24 - 48 hour antiperspirants that are clogging your pores and you do not stink for days. This lasts on my body for a good 12 - 24 hours, depending on my activity. I love and use the Vanilla-Grapefruit scent. I bought my 11 year old daughter the plain vanilla small size duo. So far, it is perfect for her. I use raw shea butter to make homemade body butter for my skin condition. I use it in conjunction with essential oils to treat my skin and I have found that my own home made recipe works best for me. This shea butter was sufficient to do that.
The only reason I give it 4 stars is because of the nature of the product itself that I just don't like. Shea butter is a natural product, derived from shea nuts. that being said, it has a waxy and oily consistency at the same time. I do not like how it mixes unless it's melted first. So when purchasing shea butter, keep in mind your mixtures (unless using it straight from the jar) will be "sandy" or "gritty" when being applied until your body heat melts it. For most people, this isn't a problem, it melts and then can be spread on the skin. For people like me with eczema and sensitive skin, just having to pull these gritty beads of shea butter across my skin irritate it and causes more harm than good. I find that taking an extra step and using a double boiler style method of heating the shea butter works better for me but changes the texture a bit. So watch out for that sensitive skin sufferers.

column6: WHIPPEDPARENT
column14:
This is a 16 oz jar of whipped pure raw African shea butter. I bought this for use on my dry skin. The older I get, the drier my skin gets. I bought a block of Shea Butter last week and it smelled buttery, more like coco butter. This is a thick butter that smells more like the plant than the cocoa smell a lot of butters have. It's not bad smelling. It just took me by surprise. I think it would appeal more to someone who likes totally natural smells. Like leaves, brushes, sages, and other unsweetened aromas.
I suggest using a tiny bit. It goes further than I expected. When I opened it, I scooped about a nickel sized amount on my finger and it was enough to do both arms. I would recommend using less the first time, in order to get use to the smell. I donâ€™t mind the smell. I get monthly fair trade product subscriptions and get products from all over the world. There are vegan products, superfood snacks, etc. that have have tastes and smells my other family members donâ€™t like, but I am fine with. I happen to like products with less perfumes dyes, etc.
It moisturizes very well. I think it would be good for use in the shower, right before you dry off, in order to hold in moisture. Since it is a naturally unscented, I'm going to play around with it and mix it with some beeswax, coconut oil, and essential oils to create an entirely unique body butter.

column6: Dead Sea Mud Mask For Face And Body - Natural Dead Sea Minerals Dead Sea Mud Mask - For Clear, Smooth, Radiant, Younger-Looking And Unblemished Natural Skin Health.
column14:
This has to be one of the more painful masks Iâ€™ve triedâ€“Iâ€™m assuming because of the salt that is found in this mud mask. After all, the dead sea is known for its high salt content. I made the mistake of putting this mask on when I had a small scrape on my face, and man did it sting!

Anyways, regarding the mask itself, itâ€™s a mud-like brown mixture which you put on your face for 5-20 minutes. You only need to apply a very thin layer, so a single bottle should last you a decent amount of time. It dries after the first couple of minutes, and it could sting a bit for those using it the first time. I actually think itâ€™s pretty effective, especially for those with acne. I had a pimple which dried up really quickly after application of the mask (most likely due to the salt). I like to put on some moisturizer afterwards, because it does tend to dry the face a little.

This was my first time trying out a mud mask from the dead sea, and Iâ€™m pretty impressed with its pimple-drying abilities. Overall, I liked it even though it stung a bit. Its effectiveness even surpasses some of the pimple spot treatment creams Iâ€™ve tried (though you do have to leave it on for a while).

Finally, you do look like a mud monster with this on, so if you wanna wear it out for Halloween or something, thatâ€™s not a bad idea :P

==The Good==
+ Saw pretty immediate effects with pimples
+ You can scare people with it on?

==The Bad==
- Does sting a bit
- Not sure how well it nourishes the face like it claims to do

4.5/5

column6: Stainless Steel INOX Pedicure Nail Nippers by Erbe. Made in Solingen, Germany
column14: This tool is exactly what I was hoping for: sturdy, precision made, and easy to use. Before I ordered it, I was perplexed by the mixture of very good and very bad reviews on Amazon. I went ahead and ordered it because I thought a reputable manufacturer in Solingen would not make junk. The two cutting edges line up perfectly, with zero discernible offset, and the wobble-free precision pivot keeps them that way. There is a spring mechanism attached to one of the two handles. When you flip it forward, a tiny wheel on its end rolls against the opposite handle to cause the jaws to open when you relax your squeeze. You flip the mechanism backward if you do not want this spring action, or when you put it in its storage pouch. The springs in other brands of nippers can not be disengaged in this way.

I started to research products with benzoyl peroxide and came across Beauty Facial Extreme  line of products. I  bought the 5% wash, acne spot treatment and clay mint healing mask. It is working out so perfectly. I am so satisfied. I have no new acne coming out, it is around that time of the month for me and my fingers are crossed, but nothing so far..I have some acne marks that I am hoping will fade with time but that is it. I also use a night cream to help with the dryness..I will totally recommend this product to anyone who is not allergic to benzoyl peroxide. column6: GranNaturals Boar Bristle Paddle Hair Brush
column13: but they feel great on my scalp
column14: The bristles on this brush are a bit more rigid than other boar bristle brushes I've owned, but they feel great on my scalp. I've seen other reviews that said the bristles aren't natural- I assure you, my brush is natural. There is a slight chemical odor to the brush, it comes from the mesh used to anchor the bristles. I imagine after a few washes the smell will fade- but even if it doesn't, it's not transferring to my hair...and since I don't particularly enjoy sniffing my hair brush I'm not too worried about this. I think the thing to remember is that although this cost a little more than a standard drugstore hairbrush- this is a boar bristle brush. You could easily drop $250 on a hand crafted boar bristle brush that is perfect in every way. Or... You can spend $13 on a boar bristle brush that has a faint odor. I've had several brushes in this price range and I assure you, none have been perfect and this one is just as good if not better than the others I've used.

column6: Qtica Intense Lip Therapy Balm
column14:
I live in the Sonoran Desert. It is so dry here, you can watch rain falling from the sky evaporate before it hits the earth. Due to the extreme dryness, I have to keep my lips moisturized 24 hours a day. I have tried every chap stick/lip balm I could find. This is the ONLY one that keeps my lips moisturized throughout the night. Until I found this product, my lips would dry out and wake me up in the middle of the night in discomfort. So every night of sleep was interrupted, just because I couldn't find decent lip balm.

Yes, Qtica costs more than a tube of Chapstick, but it's thicker, creamier, and stays where you put it. And for me, being able to sleep through the night, it's worth every penny!

column13: Passes The High Altitude Mountain Sun Test!
column14: My Andre Lorent Sunscreen arrived just in time for me to take it on vacation with me.  I put it to the test over three days at high altitude to see if it was as good as it was advertised.  It was!  I spent three days at a mountain resort hiking, ziplining and just hanging out, all in the high mountain sunshine.  I had perfect protection from the intense sun rays with an initial application in the morning, and a touch up reapplication in the afternoon.  It stayed on, even with activity that might have made it necessary to reapply with other sunscreens.  It went on smooth and silky, not greasy or heavy feeling, and I never had any skin reaction or burning in my eyes like I have had happen with sunscreens in the past.  The fragrance is minimal, so it didn't interfere with any other fragrance was using.  I will be starting a half marathon training program soon and will be using it to protect from the California sun during my long morning runs.  I would highly recommend Andre Lorent's Sport Sunscreen, especially for any outdoor activities.

column14: I tried Secret Outlast Completely Clean Scent, after receiving a travel size sample from BzzAgent on behalf of Secret. It claims to work 48 hours, and I did not believe that was going to happen. I was pleasantly surprised to find it lasted as long as it claimed. Please keep in mind that each person is different, and sweats a different amount, or has different kinds of scents in response to heat and activity. I live in a hot humid environment, so I feel that this antiperspirant was put to the test. I usually use a solid that goes on clear. I liked that this gel dried fast, it had a pleasant scent that appears unisex, as I felt it smelled nice for a girl to wear and my husband thought it was manly. So pleasing to both sides. Recap: This deodorant smells great, dries quick, lasts 48 hours, feels clean (from drying quickly and keeping you dry) and feels fresh (from the nice scent). I find that I can use this deodorant once in heavy activity, where I have to use my old deodorant a few times. So I prefer this one.

column6: Anti Cellulite Hot Cream From Uptown Cosmeceuticals Reduces Appearance of Cellulite, Promotes Supple & Toned Skin, Muscle Relaxer, Great Alternatives to Expansive Treatment, 4 Fl. Oz
column13: No burning sensation like the others I've tried, just a minty tingle! 87% organic and over 20 different essential oils!
column14: This is the second cellulite treatment gel I've tried recently. I cannot say yet whether this will be effective in reducing my cellulite as I've only been using it about a week so far but i can say that this is much much nicer to apply than the other one I tried by Perfect Curves. That gel BURNED like nothing I've ever felt before.I have sensitive skin and knew using something like this would be a gamble but my self-consciousness won out and I thought I'd give it another shot with Uptowns formula. I am extremely happy so far. While that one felt like someone doused my legs in gasoline and set them on fire in death valley this one actually had just a minty tingle. I rub it in well on the back of my thighs and buttocks and once it absorbs in (just a couple minutes) I massage the area to kind of wake everything up. (I don't know but the directions I've read online for cellulite brands always say to massage the area with a cellulite massager after application. I don't have a massager like that so I just use my fingers.) I like that it leaves my skin feeling soft and the smell isn't too overpowering. It's very strong, yes, but not like vapor rub strong. It also smells sweeter and more citrus-y than regular menthol based creams and rubs I've used. I do think it helps with tight and overworked muscles, I did notice some relief the day after leg day when I used it. That was nice all in itself. I primarily bought this for its cellulite reduction properties but it's good to know that if that doesn't pan out like I hope then I haven't completely wasted my time and money lol. I am a huge fan of essential oils, I use them daily on my body and in my diffuser as well so the fact that this formula is packed with some of the greatest is a big win in my book. The fact that it's almost completely organic is great too because like I mentioned before I have EXTREMELY sensitive skin and have to stay pretty natural or deal with breakouts and rashes. Not fun. column6: Rembrandt Deeply White + Peroxide
column14:
I've used the Rembrandt trays many, many times. I use half a tube in each tray per application and I usually only do two applications consecutively. It has always worked very well and lasts at least a month for me. But it's easy to maintain as I can just do an occasional application if all the coffee I drink starts to stain. One of the big benefits of trays is I can control the amount of peroxide I am applying.
All whitening treatments are just different concentrations of hydrogen peroxide and slightly different methods of holding it against your teeth. Crest white strips worked ok but always made my teeth very sensitive for days afterward even though I also never did the full application with them either and they are actually a lower concentration of H2O2. The two-hour strips weren't really any better, which are, once again, just a different concentration of H2O2 and very expensive. If you are getting very sensitive teeth or are burning your gums or lips then you aren't using the product correctly. You aren't supposed to fill the tray until it overflows onto your gums when you put it on your teeth and I can't believe people are complaining about the taste. It's bleach! It will burn tissue and it will not taste good. It's not toothpaste. Plus we are not all the same. You don't have to use the method on the box. If it's making your teeth too sensitive then don't do a full treatment in one sitting, spread it out.

column13: My family no longer complains about the smells of shoes and feet!,
column14:
I can't smell. And most of the time, that's a good thing. But my family can smell and they often complain about the smell of the shoes. I wouldn't know except for their comments, so I thought, at least for those I love, I should look into doing something about it. Because essential oils seem to be the new fad around town (and especially around this household), I looked into blends and decided upon this one when a few of my friends recommended it and knowing how happy I have been with Plant Therapy products in the past.

It came in an attractive bottle, professional looking and minimalistic. The labeling is thorough and clear. I threw the diffuser in the front room with this oil in it for a few hours no one commented one way or another. Of course, I can't smell, so I was hoping for something more substantial. I tried it again a few days later and pointedly asked my family about it then and they said, "now that you mention it.....!" And to their accounts, they didn't smell anything unpleasant, hence why they didn't say anything. I brought them individually to the front room and asked them then. And they said it smelled rather nice, actually, now that they thought about it. Light and fresh. My family likes it and while I can't smell, now that it saves me from listening to the complaints of my family, I like it immensely too!

I received this at a discount in exchange for a genuine critique.

column13: Excellent product.  Been using them for years!
column14:
There's no cleaner showering than one that entails a full body exfoliation.

My Korean girlfriend introduced me to this product, which is feels kind of like a scouring pad for the skin. It's not so rough it damages the skin but just enough to slough off the dead cells. It is something many asians use and is commonplace in public spas in asia.

I like to use soap with this product however my wife uses it in the traditional way, which is without soap, after which she applies moisturizing lotion. She says there's a satisfaction in seeing the dead skin is scoured off your body into rolleds she calls "noodles" . I tried it and I admit it does tell you how dirty was and clean your body is when you're done. I like to use it with soap because I'm just used my Zest smell, plus I don't get the unsightly noodles. She says I don't do it that way I can't tell if I'm clean. Fair enough, honey :)

Anyway I HIGHLY recommend everyone buy the smaller "mittens" (which are just square pockets) for the body, and this one to scrub your back.
