column6: Wahl Professional Super Taper Ii Hair Clipper - Model # 8470-500 - Silver/black Clipper For Men
column14:
After a year of having barbers and hairdressers not cutting my hair the way I wanted it to be cut, I decided to purchase hair clippers and cut my own hair. I am glad that I ended up choosing this model. The Wahl Super Taper 2 is a professional-quality clipper (the successor to the original Super Taper and a lower-power, non-metal version of the Senior)with the v5000 electromagnetic motor and an adjustable blade. This product comes with a small operating booklet, 5 mL of clipper oil, 8 guards (1/8 inch - 1 inch), a blade guard, a cleaning brush and a white comb. Shipping was faster than expected; I am very satisfied. Out of the package, everything included was in good condition and the blades smelled freshly oiled. The sound of the clipper turning on is really something special to hear...

The clipper was cutting just a tad longer than what the 000 position should cut at, so I zero-gapped the clipper (check out youtube for tutorial videos)by loosening the blade screws slightly and pushing the bottom blade closer to the cutting blade. If you do this, make sure that the two blades aren't actually touching each other, and the cutting blade should never pass in front of the bottom blade. Make sure there is a slight gap between the blades that isn't visible from a distance. When you're satisfied with the adjustment, firmly hold the bottom blade by its sides and carefully tighten the screws. If the blades are zero-gapped but misaligned (the far left tooth of the cutting blade should overlap with the 2nd tooth of the bottom blade), try this procedure again. Turn on the clipper for a few seconds and then turn it off and check to make sure the blades are aligned. If they are not, adjust the power screw until the cutting blade is properly adjusted. By performing these steps, I was able to zero-gap the clipper and align the blades. Needless to say, it cuts through hair like butter now; the length is also closer to a true 000. Be careful with a zero-gapped clipper: if you don't press the blade flat against your scalp and use the teeth instead, you'll get a minor cut.

So far, I've only done one haircut with these clippers (a high-and-tight variation with a #2 on top, bangs in the front, a #0 everywhere else and #1 blend between the crown and temples) and it turned out great. If you're cutting your own hair, you have to be careful and slow, especially when it comes to tapering (don't use the clipper for too long though). The Super Taper 2 does not pull hair when it cuts and it cuts evenly. With proper adjustment, it is not too loud. The taper lever can allow you to blend from #000 (closed, up) to #1 (open, down) in length if the clipper is zero-gapped. The guards are of decent quality. When you're cutting your own hair, use at least two mirrors to see the back of your head and feel to make sure everything is proper. Ideally, get someone to make sure you are cutting the back accurately.

If you are cutting the hair of multiple people, I recommend purchasing clipper disinfectant spray such as Clippercide. This will prevent the spread of blood-borne illnesses. Also, once you are running low on oil, buy a large bottle of Wahl clipper oil; they last a long time. If you don't oil your blades, your clippers will perform like junk. Oiling your clippers is not necessary after every cut, but maybe after several (clean the hair off the blades too!). If the clippers are behaving strangely, you may have to oil them, adjust the blades or fine-tune the power screw.

Make sure the guards snap onto your clipper; many people find their guards detaching in the middle of a cut. Make sure the blade doesn't chew the guard and don't use the clipper too roughly during a haircut. When the clipper is not in use, keep it unplugged and away from moisture while leaving the blade guard on. If you receive a damaged or defective product, contact Wahl; the clipper has a one-year warranty and customer service is great. Do not drop these clippers; the frame is plastic. If you want more durable clippers, get the Wahl Senior or another metal-body clipper.

Finally, if you are interested in cutting your own hair or someone else's, or if you are a barber, these are great clippers to purchase. They will last a long time with proper maintenance and are a great step between cheap clippers and expensive, powerful clippers. I recommend this product to anyone who is interested in hair cutting or simply needs an affordable, reliable clipper. Wahl makes universal electromagnetic clippers that will serve you well.se clippers; the frame is plastic. If you want more durable clippers, get the Wahl Senior or another metal-body clipper.

column6: Primal Pit Paste All Natural Deodorant Stick, Aluminum Free, Paraben Free, No Added Fragrances
column14:
I bought four scents of Primal Pit Paste stick and spray sight unseen from the manufacturer's website. As a man, I don't want to smell like a woman. The Lavender isn't for men and makes me smell like a floral bouquet. The Thyme and Lemongrass scent is simply awful and causes stains on all my shirts that will not come out in the wash or at the dry cleaners. The Royal and Rogue is fine for men (thus, I recommend for men), but it also stains clothes. The Primal Spice scent is also nice for men and seems to stain clothes less than the other scents.

All products eliminated underarm odor well; hence, a three star rating. The Thyme and Lemongrass scent seems to overpower everything so it may simply mask scent rather than eliminate it. I didn't break-out with a rash like others on here and tolerated the product well. My hope is the manufacturer reads these reviews and changes the formulary to not stain clothes (minus one star for the staining). The price point is also high compared to other products on the market which, in my opinion, deducts another star from the rating.

PS - I can use the spray on "other areas" of the body to eliminate odor and can report the product works well without presenting a skin rash.

column14:
I was looking for an oil that's similar to what they use for professional massages. I was looking for something that wasn't sticky afterwards and didn't smell. I guess I could have asked my massage therapist where she gets her oil, but I've been too embarrassed, so I just ordered a few oils on Amazon that looked like professional massage oils.

And, this massage oil is great, and I'm sure that a ton of professional massage therapists use this oil. It works well, but doesn't leave you sticky and oily and greasy after you use it. Also, it doesn't smell at all. Well, there are always trace smells to anything, but compared to all of the other oils I've used, even the unscented ones, this one is great for having a very neutral smell that I can't smell at all.

column6: Cremo Shave Cream, Astonishingly Superior Shaving Cream for Men
column13: Don't Know How, But It Works Great
column14:
Surprisingly great shave cream.

I've been shaving with Cremo for a few weeks now and I have to say I'll not go back to gels. It took me several shaves to figure this stuff out but now that I have, it provides a silky smooth, close shave.

What I discovered was to rub Cremo between my hands a little bit before applying to my face. Initially, I was squeezing the small amount on my fingertips and applying directly to my beard then rubbing it in. For some reason, I seemed to feel razor tugs with that method but now that I get the cream activated in my hands, then rub into my beard, it works fantastic! If it helps, I shave religiously with a Gillette Fusion Powered Proglide and the addition of Cremo makes my shave that much more enjoyable.

It is a bizarre product, because you don't need much. In fact, I feel I often use too much. Give it a try.

column14:
Three weeks post dye, I was looking for a pick me up for my faded to orange color and this was it! I used "Cool Brunette" on my medium brown to auburn hair and I'm really pleased with the results.

The only downsides, the product could use more pigment. More pigment could have toned the brassiness in my hair further. I'm hoping repeat applications will help.
Not a con for me, but could be for the others, lots of fragrance.

The steps I followed:
Wash hair with clarifying shampoo.
Apply product, wait 10 minutes.
Put conditioner over (without rinsing)
Shower.
Rinse everything out at the end of the shower. Approximately 10 more minutes later.

Both pictures are post Glosser results on air-dried hair. (with and without flash)

column6: Banila Clean It Zero Sherbet Cleanser, 100ml
column14: So, I purchased this item based on a review by a Youtuber. I was extremely excited because I trust this Youtuber and any product I purchased based on her review has been pretty good so far! Regarding this product, I do have to say it does not come with instructions--- mainly because it's a Korean product, so don't expect to be taught when it you have it! Even so, it's pretty basic. It smells pretty good, which is a great positive on my end. I hate products that smell chemically. Warning: don't rub into eyes. I wasn't 100% sure on how to use it, since it was just your basic massage kind of technique. I've always used make up wipes, and I would rub them on my eye lids for a complete clean. With Clean it Zero, I recommend being careful around the eyes. The product doesn't burn one bit, which is great! However, it momentarily disrupted my vision when I tried to check if all my eye make up was gone. All it did was kind of put this transparent film over my vision? Blur might be an effect, but I have blurry vision anyway so I wouldn't be able to tell. Moral of the review, be careful on the first couple of times using this product. I do think it takes practice, especially if you're not use to oil cleansers. Other than that, it removed my make up and gave a brief second 'fresh' feeling. Just because I like a good, deep clean, I went in with my Glam Glow product afterwards. I'm not in love with this product, but I do like it! It's something I'll have to get use to, and I find nothing wrong with that. I find it as an experience to learn and practice different types of skin care.

column6: NaturOli Soap Nut / Soapberry Shampoo Normal to Dry 16oz. All Natural Hair Care Sulfate Free! EXTREME Hair is made with USDA organic soap nuts / soap berries! Gluten free. Vegan.
column13: Brings out your TRUE natural hair
column14:
I love this shampoo. It doesn't leave much of a scent in your hair, but that's what a natural shampoo is. I bought mine in January, and I use about a penny sized amount every day (sometimes every other). I am only halfway through the bottle. A little goes a long way. I have fine hair, but a lot of it. My hair length is about halfway down my back. I wanted to switch to an all natural shampoo, so I made my own. I used soap nuts to make mine, but I didn't like the results, and it was annoying to keep my shampoo as ice cubes in the freezer. I found this and decided to try it. It's been GREAT! Just know, if you haven't detoxed your hair away from chemical products prior to using this shampoo (I did it with my own homemade shampoo) then your hair will get greasy. My hair went through the detox stage for a couple of weeks. Basically, commercial shampoos strip away your natural oils, so when you stop using them, your hair overproduces your natural oils. It takes a little time to adjust.

I am very pleased with this shampoo. I use the conditioner too, but honestly don't even need to use it. I use it if I want extra soft hair. My hair was slightly naturally wavy before, but it always seemed weighed down. My waves weren't consistent enough to wear it natural. I would blow dry it straighter. Now, my waves look great! I can wear my hair natural without needing to do anything besides brush it. I never really used products in my hair, so I don't use them now. With this shampoo, a little goes a long way. You don't need a lot. It's not going to foam like a store bought shampoo, but if you rub it in for a while, it does slightly foam. Soap nuts have a natural foam that comes out of them, so that's probably what the foam is from. But, it is VERY minimal. This washes out easily, and my hair is never greasy. I definitely recommend this if you are looking for an easy, all-natural shampoo.

column13: Stopped being as effective a few months in
column14: If I wrote this back when I originally bought it, I would give it five stars hands down.  The product does exactly what it's supposed to and I really like the company. However, it's been a few months of me using this product and I think my body has gotten used to it or something? It used to last all day and now I start smelling and perspiring at about midway point through out the day.  It should also be noted that once you use this product, if you don't use it for any reason, your armpits somehow stink more than they did before you were using the product.  Again, I have no idea what's happening or if my body has just gotten used to the product but I may be switching products to something that lasts a bit longer and doesn't seem to cause more stink.  The OTHER thing is DO NOT USE IT IMMEDIATELY AFTER YOU SHAVE YOUR ARMPITS, ESPECIALLY IF YOU HAVE SENSITIVE SKIN.  It would irritate my armpits a lot whenever I would do this so I would wait a few hours or more.  Sometimes it would just randomly irritate it but mostly is after I shave.

column6: Gillette Venus Swirl Women's Razor with 1 Razor Blade Refill, Womens Razors / Blades
column14:
I didn't think I'd like a ball forcing the head side-to-side, but I'm amazed at the control you have with this razor, even over tough spots (like ankles and knees), as well as more "delicate" areas. This is my 3rd handle/bundle purchase (this one for travel), and I've been through probably a dozen of the heads... not one nick (yet), but I also use a good shaving cream, NOT soap, and don't rush the job!

The handle allows movement "just enough" to the side to avoid nicks and cuts, and because it only moves side-to-side, it allows you to apply the right amount of pressure to ensure a smooth shave. The 5-blade heads really make quick work of stubble in a single pass, and you can usually go an extra day between shaves (as compared to twin or triple-head razors (even the original Venus). The handle is also less slippery than the Body handle or Original Venus handle. These 5-blad heads also fit other Gillette handles, and the 3 and 4-blade heads fit this ball handle too.

Some comments have been harsh about the lube-strips "melting" on the heads, but honestly, I've not seen this issue, but I also don't leave the razor face-down in a puddle after use... it hangs upright to dry (or lays blade-up on the shelf) after use.

The heads cost a bit more, but I look for coupons and sales, and the heads do last considerably longer than the triple-blade versions, so cost per head sort of works out in the wash... If you're looking for a new razor for the shower, give this one a try, and I think you'll be pleasantly surprised... I was!

column6: ABSOLUTE GOLD 24K Lifting Facial Serum - 24 Karat Gold, SILK PEPTIDES and HYALURONIC Acid. Excellent for all skin types. 2 fl.oz-60 ml (FRAGRANCE FREE, CRUELTY FREE, PARABEN FREE, PETROLEUM FREE).
column14:
As a product tester I compare dozens of skin care products, and I've arrived at a list of key considerations from fragrance to long-term results. I hope these are helpful to you!

~ Fragrance: Virtually none
~ Color and texture: Clear, very thick gel with fine gold flakes suspended in a central DNA-like spiral pattern as well as larger ones throughout the gel. No mica listed in ingredients, so that's actually the gold you're seeing.
~ Feel during application: Thick, slightly gummy, fading to pleasantly wet and slippery once you've spread it across a larger area.
~ Feel after absorption: Slightly sticky, probably thanks to glycerine being the second ingredient. You might want to use this as a primer for powder makeup. Or, AS makeup; the parts of the gel with fine gold particles give your skin a pleasing sheen like a "veil" powder.
~ Is it best for a certain skin type?: Should be okay for all EXCEPT if you have an allergy to gold in which case it can cause contact dermatitis. This kind of allergy is rare, but if there's any question you should try a small test area.
~ Is it tested on animals?: No.
~ Packaging: Outer cardboard display box contains the bottle and a plastic scoop. Gel is in a 2.04oz (60ml) clear plastic container, wide mouth with screw top.
~ Immediate cosmetic effects:* Makes skin a bit glittery and bright, reduces fine lines under eyes.
~ Potential long-term effectiveness:* From putting gold on your face? None. Google the NYT article "Gold Face Cream: A Costly Leap of Faith." The active ingredients that might actually help your skin are amino acids, wheat protein, silk peptides, ginseng, hyaluronic acid, and vitamin E. If these are present in sufficient quantity, they make this a beneficial if not comprehensive serum.
~ Other notes: I admire this for being an affordable gold skin care product; it's certainly as good as astronomically priced equivalents. The upscale packaging, truly delightful DNA spiral pattern in the gold, and the fun shimmer and wrinkle reduction it gives the skin makes this an affordable luxury and would be a great gift. It's not a world-beating formula, but it's a decent one - don't make this your only anti-aging product, but by all means treat yourself.

*Know the difference between cosmetic and long-term effects: Cosmetic effects are immediate and only present when the product has been applied recently - just like makeup. Long-term effects take longer to see and should remain when you stop using the product (but don't when you find something effective - your skin needs continuing support). The ideal product would be both cosmetically and long-term effective, but it's more realistic to expect a formula to tilt towards one or the other.

column6: Vitamin C Serum for face 25% - Moisturizer - Vitamin C + E + Hyaluronic Acid Serum. Ultimate Anti Aging Anti Wrinkle Serum Help Combat Wrinkles, Fine Lines, Dark Circles, Age Spots, and Boost Collagen (1 oz) - High Potency Serum - By Sieva Skincare
column13: Barnacles be gone!!! - THE perfect sunscreen base!!!!!
column14:
Can I say miracle serum? I'd been using a 20% solution every day through the winter and decided to kick it up to 25% with this particular brand. One pump for the face, one pump for the neck and back of hands. Makes my skin glow such that I hardly need any powder foundation, eliminated my dry spots, and I see a definite improvement in those fine lines and wrinkles around the eyes and mouth - even the forehead!!! There is no scent, this glides on smoothly and really makes your skin feel so soft. The first few times it tingled. Your skin has to get used to the Vitamin C so go slowly at first. BUT here's the most amazing and miraculous part - I received this only a week before a Florida vacation. Used it each morning and evening like I would any other moisturizer. While in Florida, I applied this first to my face and neck, then sunscreen. After sunning and washing off, I'd apply some of this to my shoulders, chest and arms because I figured the Vitamin C would be good after being in that hot sun. Three days into our vacation, we were in the Gulf hanging out and chatting for over 3 hours - without re-applying sunscreen. Not one of my more intelligent choices. I dreaded being fried and ruining the rest of the vacation. Miraculously, neither my face nor neck burned whatsoever. My shoulders and chest got really red, but never peeled!!! I believe this serum prevented what could have been a devastating sunburn!!!! I'll never use anything else!!!!

UPDATED REVIEW :: Having used this serum for 3 months, I can't stop raving about it. I'm on my second bottle. My 50 year old face looks at least ten years younger, with the disappearance of the fine lines and wrinkles - specifically, my smile/laugh lines above my eyebrows and crows feet, and the tiny ones that began above my upper lip. They're gone!!! More amazingly, my skin is fresh and bright, and the "barnacles" which the dermatologist said to watch closely (for future skin cancers) are slowly disappearing as well. My skin is rejuvenated and has tightened noticeably under my chin. What a miracle serum. I am SO pleased that I finally have found something to stick with for as long as it's manufactured. I use one squirt on my neck and another for my face. I encourage anyone to use this and be amazed! Please note, this updated review is a completely honest review in exchange for receiving my second bottle at a discount.

It leaves a thin film, but doesn't feel greasy like sun screen/moisturizer products. The label recommends preparing your skin first with [[ASIN:B00LHZC4PG EB5 Cleanser]] and [[ASIN:B00P8F3MRK EB5 Toner]] (a step that I skipped).

EB5 Facial Cream does fill in fine lines and wrinkles, as does any reasonably effective skin moisturizer. This product is marketed as an anti-aging cream (impossible to test). Because it's odorless, hypo-allergenic, and works reasonably well even without the companion products, I rate EB5 Facial Cream it at 4 stars (\\\I like it\\\\\" on the official Amazon scale)."

column6: UV LED Nail Dryer, Liberex 24W Curing Lamp with Timer (30S, 60S, 99S) Auto Detection for Fingernail Toenail Gel Polish
column14:
I am really enjoying this professional-grade 54 watt UV light. It comes with 6-9 watt bulbs which are easy to insert. There are 2 tabs to press on the bottom of the unit which opens the light so you can peel off the blue plastic and insert the 6 UV bulbs. Then plug it in, turn it on with a toggle switch located on the back of the unit, and you are all set.

When you are ready to place your manicured hands or feet inside the unit all you need to do is press a button, located on top of the unit, to time your cure anywhere from 60 seconds on up to 300 seconds (1-5 minutes), depending on your needs. It also has a button on top to turn on an internal fan, if desired. When I am done using it I turn the fan off, then I turn the unit off with the back toggle switch, and lastly, I unplug it. (I'm weird about leaving electrical appliances plugged in...your call).

I considered rating this 4 not 5 stars because it arrived with one bulb broken, but I called Amazon, they found me a replacement bulb at no charge and I had it within a few days. It is my opinion that this UV light deserves all 5 stars. I have used it many times and couldn't be more pleased. If you are considering this purchase, I would suggest snapping it up before this seller is out of stock again and the price (from other sellers) jumps back up to over $100! If you are familiar with how to give yourself and others a beautiful, long lasting gel manicure or pedicure, you can stop reading here. Otherwise, if interested read on!
ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…ðŸ’…
1st I wash my hands and under my fingernails well, using soap, water and a nail brush, then dry. If you are happy with your nail length and shape, all you do is push back the cuticles and gently rough up the surface of your nails with a fine grit nail file until you have taken all the natural "shine" away.

Next, use a gel cleanser or rubbing alcohol on a lint free wipe to further clean the oils from each nail. I use the highest % I can find, like 92% rubbing alcohol. Sometimes I use those tiny pre-packaged alcohol wipes. Amazon sells them at a good price. Then I clean my gel brush with rubbing alcohol and dry it, making sure there are no particles, dust or lab puppy hairs on it. ðŸ• You can simplify by just using the brush that comes with your gel polishes if you wish. The next thing I do is lightly brush on a dehydrate product (I use IBD's) and place my hand under the UV light for 10-20 seconds. A bonder is next; I lightly brush on OPI's "Bond Aid", avoiding the cuticles and sidewalls. Now you're ready for the fun part.

If you are lucky enough to have nice strong fingernails and do not need to lengthen, shape or repair them, you are ready for a gel base coat. Brush on slowly and evenly avoiding contact with cuticles or sidewalls. Clean up any areas of gel on skin with an orangestick, then place your hand under your beautiful, new UV light (cure it) for 1 minute. The internal fan is optional. Next, brush on your gel color coat and cure for 2 minutes. I usually like 2 coats of color, so repeat last step, cure. Then brush on your gel topcoat and cure for 2 minutes. Use your gel cleanser or rubbing alcohol on a lint-free wipe and clean the tacky layer that is left on your fingernails. Clean your gel brush again too, if using one. Last of all, gently massage cuticle oil onto your cuticles and surrounding skin. You now have a beautiful, shiny, durable manicure which will last 2-3 weeks! I use the cuticle oil every night before bed to keep them healthy.

Check out YouTube video tutorials for more information on gel manicures including how to lengthen, strengthen, shape, stamp, do french tips, decorate and remove them. I hope this helps! column6: Philips Norelco S9311/87, Shaver 9300
column13: Daily shaves for my sensitive face.
column14:
Without writing a hundred-page review, as others have done, I can say that this razor has rescued my face. I have very sensitive skin, and I have never found a razor, manual or electric, that I can shave with daily. I always just shaved twice or maybe three times a week, which I hated, since I don't like to look scruffy at the office. Years ago, I tried other electric razors, including a cheaper Norelco. They always left my face raw and burned.

This razor is a daily shaver for me. It leaves a little bit of a raw feeling once in a while, but nowhere near what I was used to before. With the right aftershave, I'm totally fine. I'm also surprised at how close it cuts. I can get a shave that looks as close as a real razor shave. It still feels the slightest bit rough, but looks great. I have used this in the shower and also dry. Both work very well. I just do whatever is more convenient for me on different days.

column13: Hands down...BEST hair dryer I've ever used.
column14:
A hair dryer is not something I generally replace until I need it. Mine is still working, but I had been saying for a while that I needed a new one. I've always just looked at it as something that blows air and that they are all pretty much the same. After using this one a few times, I will never say that again. This hair dryer is awesome. I had already switched my curling irons to ionic ceramic and could tell a big difference, but I didn't realize that it would also make a difference in a hair dryer. Not only does it dry my hair faster, but it leaves it looking much more healthy. I have very long hair and even though I take good care of it, I had noticed that it was looking dull and dry. The first time I used this dryer, I could tell a difference. I don't know all the "how" or "why" reasons, but I do know that my hair didn't look or feel like all the moisture had been stripped from it. I had even started to air dry my hair because I could see what was happening to it, but that takes a long time with thick , long hair. I will still air dry when I have the time, but now I feel like I can dry my hair quickly (and this dryer does it VERY quick), and not be damaging it. I don't use the high heat on this one because it's very hot and my fine hair wouldn't like that, but I like knowing that the option is there if needed. The air flow with this is massive.....really powerful... When on high, I can dry my hair in a few minutes, but that's only when I'm just drying it to put in a ponytail. Medium is more than enough airflow to dry and style it, and I love the cool setting. When I used a round brush to curl, I finished with the cool setting and it made all the difference. It's not a small dryer, but it's not at all heavy , especially considering the power that it contains.

column6: L'Oreal Paris Youth Code Skin Illuminator SPF 20, Tinted All-in-1 Facial Mo
column13: Over time I liked the product more and more
column14:
It's difficult for a product to do one thing, let alone three at the same time. This product wants to be a moisturizer, sunscreen, and light make-up. If you only have money for one product, want to have less clutter on the vanity table, or want one bottle for travel, this is a good product to buy. Over the weeks I have now used this it does seem to do these things as well as buying three separate products. What I like best is the light color/glow it gives my skin.

As a light make up/skin illuminator:
It gives me a dewy glow. Definitely not a matte finish like the make-up I normally use year round. It is a golden yellow base, not a rose base in case that helps you decide. I see this being something light you can even use at the beach or pool. I have used it over the summer on a daily basis. At first having this much dewy glow looks like you have a slight sheen on your face. However, It does eventually subside/absorb into your skin. My skin is fair, except I have a little bit of tan right now, as it is summer as I am writing this. The Youth Code Illuminator provided coverage for my skin better than no make up, but is not dark enough to completely cover any but the smallest of blemishes. It certainly is not strong enough like they claim to cover redness, dark spots, and dark circles. That is why I gave it 4 instead of 5 stars. I will give them imperfections as there was some smoothing and covering of my skin during use. It does say that your skin improves over time and use of the product (immediately vs 8 hours vs 1 month). I have now given it over a month. My skin does immediately look "fresher" (what I call the dewy glow) when I use it, but hard to tell if it did those other things due to other products I use on my face to reduce redness and smooth my skin or that this product significantly helped. Cat least it didn't hurt it by making me break out. When you first put it on - 2 hours later and the glow is still there. I tested the claim you need to do every 2 hours. I put another layer on just to see if any difference in coverage. It looks fresher like it did immediately after putting on the first time, but it is not covering the redness any better than it did earlier today. So if you are mainly using as makeup another layer is not necessary.

As a moisturizer:
When I try new products I am most worried about breaking out in pimples. I have sensitive combination skin. If the moisture is too much for my skin, I will break out. I didn't immediately have a bad reaction (instant redness and/or tightness) which has happened with some products. Over the time I used it, I did not see pimples due to this product which is a relief. It definitely feels like the moisturizer is there working, when I touch my face and it is softer.

As a sunscreen, I was concerned that it recommended using other sunscreens at the same time. Not a good sign L'Oréal. It says on the container that this is SPF 20, but use with other products of at least SPF 15. Why, if your products works so well, would you say that? Unless what they mean is to use other sunscreens on other parts of your body to be fully covered? I think they need to clarify that or the confusion might cause people to think the product is not good like I have seen on other reviews. I don't think I ever got burned on my face since using this so I would say it works as a suntan lotion.

Overall, I recommend the product.d the claim you need to do every 2 hours. I put another layer on just to see if any difference in coverage. It looks fresher like it did immediately after putting on the first time, but it is not covering the redness any better than it did earlier today. So if you are mainly using as makeup another layer is not necessary.

As a moisturizer:
When I try new products I am most worried about breaking out in pimples. I have sensitive combination skin. If the moisture is too much for my skin, I will break out. I didn't immediately have a bad reaction (instant redness and/or tightness) which has happened with some products. Over the time I used it, I did not see pimples due to this product which is a relief. It definitely feels like the moisturizer is there working, when I touch my face and it is softer.

As a sunscreen, I was concerned that it recommended using other sunscreens at the same time. Not a good sign L'Oréal. It says on the container that this is SPF 20, but use with other products of at least SPF 15. Why, if your products works so well, would you say that? Unless what they mean is to use other sunscreens on other parts of your body to be fully covered? I think they need to clarify that or the confusion might cause people to think the product is not good like I have seen on other reviews. I don't think I ever got burned on my face since using this so I would say it works as a suntan lotion.

Overall, I recommend the product.

column6: FlexiNail Fingernail Conditioner (2 Bottles - 3 month+ supply)
column14:
Give it time, use it, and you will see results. I have had a problem with ridges developing the length of my nails in recent years. Some of them are quite pronounced and some seem to have weak areas that cause splitting and slowed the overall growth of the nail. All of my nails have some ridging and I tried a multitude of products from cover ups to fillers to strengtheners. Nothing seemed to work after a few hours to a couple of days by covering up the ridges. I read about this product on the professional guitar site and it had a link to the product but I was reluctant to pay this much for a product on an unknown referred site. I looked and I found the product here on and Amazon so I took a chance. Over the past couple of months 7 of 10 nails are MUCH improved, stronger and thicker and no breakage, I am clipping them to the desired length for the first time in a few years. Two of the nails, the pinky, on both hands continue to have pronounced ridges but are strengthening and growing but at a slower rate. My left ring finger has a very high pronounced ridge that appears braided, it continues to split at the ridge as it grows out but the rest of the nail is getting stronger. 9 out of 10 nails is pretty good compared to what I have been going through with other products, and I hope the last one will improve with more time.

One bottle has lasted quite a long time, it's not half gone with a second new bottle waiting, so the price is not out of line compared to other products I paid for that didn't work. It is an oil that does have a strong herbal or woodsy type scent, it isn't as strong now as it was when the bottle was first opened. I paint it onto my nails, leave it on for 20-30 minutes, massage it into each nail and then wash my hands with soap and water, there is no lingering odor or any evidence it was ever there after hand washing.

This is a great product. The brush looks tiny but it's actually the perfect size to create the perfect amount of coverage without being too heavy and wasting the product. I have medium skin tone, and this shade was perfect on me. It has light to medium coverage. Bare Minerals definitely has a leg up on it's competitors, such as Ocean Mist. This foundation has about 3X as much coverage as any other brand that I have found so far. It has the ability to create the perfect amount of coverage without giving your face that heavy makeup feeling.

column6: Razorock Mudder Focker Shave Soap
column13: Don't delay--you need to own this soap
column14:
There are a number of products you didn't actually know you needed until you purchased them, but once you had them, you simply cannot live without them anymore. For example, you had no idea you needed a blanket with sleeves, but now you have a Snuggie for every room of the house. You might not realize that you need this awesome shaving soap, but you do!

Mudder Focker is a perfect shaving product. The soap lathers easily, and the fuller's earth in the mix makes the lather extra slick. It will seem like the razor isn't touching your face at all. When the shave is over, you won't believe how nourished and hydrated your face is.

The scent is pretty amazing--a blend of vanilla, tobacco, and what seems like a hint of vetiver and anise. It's a very complex, manly, cologne-type scent. Seriously, this stuff is the goods. I love it, and my wife loved it even more. Just do yourself a favor and go ahead and order the matching aftershave from Razorock.

This soap is an amazing product and an amazing price. Try it and you won't be disappointed.

column6: Herbal Essences Naked Volume
column14:
I have tried so many different shampoos, looking for one that can handle my extremely thick, long, and frizzy hair. Add to that the fact that my hair tends to be rather greasy and is multi-textured (I have strands of straight, fine hair interspersed with thicker, coarser, wavy strands.) This shampoo is everything a shampoo should be: Just a shampoo. There are no bells and whistles here. Although a clear shampoo, this is not a clarifying shampoo, and should not be mistaken as such. It is not harsh on the hair, but does not add the buildup that most shampoos these days do.

The only thing I don't like is how minty smelling it is (I prefer warmer and fruity scents like vanilla and mango), but the smell is light and goes away quickly. However, the scent also means that it is a great unisex shampoo. Guys should be able to use this and not be accused of shopping at Victoria's Secret.

Bottom line: I have been using this shampoo for several weeks now (the point at which I quit using most shampoos), and it is still making my hair feel baby soft with no buildup. I see no reason that I won't be using this full-time for as long as it's sold. I use this on my roots in combination with Garnier Fructis' Brazilian Smooth conditioner (in the dark green bottle) on the ends, and my hair has never been healthier or less frizzy. Highly recommend!

column6: SweatBlock Antiperspirant - Clinical Strength - Reduce Sweat up to 7-days per Use
column13: Sweat Block truly gave my daughter her life back
column14: My daughter developed hyperhydrosis in middle school and got to the point where she was socially extremely self conscious and avoided friends and many social events and had to change clothes so many times a day.  Within minutes of dressing each morning, her clothes were saturated and we used every product imaginable to get the odor out of her clothes and nothing worked.  By entering high school, the odor in her clothes was so offensive and no prescription product the pediatrician had her use worked.  We went to a dermatologist who offered very expensive Botox injections at $1000/3 months that insurance would not pay for - so not an option.  Finally she offered a Rx pill that acted in a way that dried out her entire body and that worked - but she had a very extreme reaction and lost 80 pounds due to this drug causing a shut down of her digestive system and 5 doctors could not figure out that this drug was the culprit until we found the right doctor who immediately realized what the problem was.  She was taken off of this obviously and then we were totally desperate and felt that there were no other options other than a risky surgery and that would have its own set of negative drawbacks.  Then we found Sweat Block.  I was completely in doubt that it would work since nothing else ever had.  With the first application, my daughter noticed a substantial reduction in her sweat.  That first week she used the second one a little sooner than a week apart as directed.  Now, she has been using it for about 18 months and only needs to use it every 7 days!!  Her sweating is totally under control.  There is no more odor in her clothes whatsoever and she socially has her life back.  I am amazed at how well this has worked and so thankful that we found it.  It is so good, in fact, that we tell everyone we know who has a loved one with this embarrassing issue about the product and they love it as well.

column6: Bodishape Cellulite Cream With Retinol and Caffeine - Guaranteed Fast Acting Body Firming Treatment
column14:
Happy Happy Happy Happy! I've always heard that there is nothing you can do for cellulite short of lipo. Well, let me be the first to say that THIS has helped my cellulite. I used this on my outer thighs daily and I've been using this for about 6 weeks now and I SEE RESULTS. I took before and after picture just so I could see a side by side comparison for myself and I definitely see a BIG difference. I wore a bathing suit WITHOUT a wrap for the first time in years! I am so ecstatic!

Like I said I used this daily, I used the BodiSure Cellulite Massager in the shower to prepare for the cream. I rubbed the massager in a circular motion for roughly 2-3 minutes. After drying off I rubbed this cream into my skin in a circular motion as well. And that's it!

Initially I didn't see results, as a matter of fact my 9 year old made it a point to tell me daily that it wasn't working! Well around the 4 week mark I saw a difference - even my daughter said WOW it's working! At the 6 week mark it was a huge difference to me!

The picture is before (on the left) and after (on the right). The before picture is a little red because I decided to take the picture after my first session doing this. I honestly don't know how they did it, and I'm big on researching ingredients and I see there are tons of ingredients in this that are known to help with cellulite. My cellulite isn't completely gone, but I do love what I see so far! I definitely feel more confident wearing shorts and swimsuits than I have in years!!!

This is the link for the BodiSure Cellulite Massager:
http://www.amazon.com/BodiSure-Cellulite-Massager-Circulation-Abrasions/dp/B00P8P0KVQ/ref=pd_sim_194_3?ie=UTF8&refRID=1WFC238FYAPM3JJHTSV0

My only fear is I don't know if the cellulite will come back if I stop using it! Hopefully the results are permanent, but I plan on keeping this up!

column13: which is feels kind of like a scouring pad for the skin
column14:
There's no cleaner showering than one that entails a full body exfoliation.

My Korean girlfriend introduced me to this product, which is feels kind of like a scouring pad for the skin. It's not so rough it damages the skin but just enough to slough off the dead cells. It is something many asians use and is commonplace in public spas in asia.

I like to use soap with this product however my wife uses it in the traditional way, which is without soap, after which she applies moisturizing lotion. She says there's a satisfaction in seeing the dead skin is scoured off your body into rolleds she calls "noodles" . I tried it and I admit it does tell you how dirty was and clean your body is when you're done. I like to use it with soap because I'm just used my Zest smell, plus I don't get the unsightly noodles. She says I don't do it that way I can't tell if I'm clean. Fair enough, honey :)

Anyway I HIGHLY recommend everyone buy the smaller "mittens" (which are just square pockets) for the body, and this one to scrub your back.

column6: Significant Beauty Anti Aging Clear Skin Facial Serum with 20% Vitamin C - 1 Oz. BEST NATURAL serum â€“ Better than face, neck & eye creams or moisturizers for your blemishes, dark spots & wrinkles. For day, night, men & women - With Retinol, B3, MSM.
column14:
This vitamin C skin serum is slightly milky with the fresh scent of witch hazel. The cobalt blue glass bottle has a dropper cap.

The serum moisturizes and protects the skin and will improve its appearance with regular use over time by increasing hydration, reducing the visual effect of fine wrinkles, and removing dead skin cells. It also minimizes the appearance of enlarged pores and decreases shininess in oily areas. It is intended for use on the face, but is also effective on problem areas like elbows and knees.

The mostly botanical formula has ingredients known to benefit the skin such as vitamin C, vegetarian hyaluronic acid, aloe, jojoba oil, and glycerin. There are many well-designed scientific studies that demonstrate that topical vitamin C significantly reverses the damage done to the skin by the sun when used for several months. The hyaluronic acid may help repair and replace damaged protein structures in the skin.

Ingredients: Organic Aloe barbadensis leaf (aloe), sodium ascorbyl phosphate (vitamin C), methylsulfonylmethane (MSM), Cassia angustifolia seed polysaccharide (plant-derived hyaluronic acid), niacinamide (vitamin B3), retinol, olive oil squalene, capryloyl salicylic acid, organic Rosa canina (rosehip seed oil), carbomer, (2S)-2-amino-5-guanidinopentanoic acid, Melaleuca alternifolia (tea tree essential oil), Lavandula angustifolia (lavender essential oil), ylang ylang essential oil, phenoxyethanol, ethyl hexyl glycerin, organic aloe vera, organic gotu kola, organic horsetail, organic geranium, organic dandelion.

Significant Beauty provided serum for evaluation and review.

column13: Great hair dryer for the price but lasted barely more than a year
column14:
Iâ€™m always in search of a hair dryer that can blow dry my thick, curly hair as well as my stylist does. (I know â€¦ I know â€¦ itâ€™s the person not the tool.) When she dries it, she barely has to touch it up with a flat iron. When I dry it â€¦ I have to do a little more work to straighten out the wavy stragglers.

This review compares the Remington Damage Control (DC) Ceramic Hair Dryer, Remington T|Studio Silk AC Professional Hair Dryer, and this one (Revlon 1875W Tourmaline Ionic Ceramic Dryer,).

All of them have:
* Same wattage
* Three heat settings
* Two speed settings
* Cool shot feature
* Diffuser and concentrator attachments
* Ionic technology
* Ceramic technology
* Hanging loop

The Revlon does not come with a removable filter, the two Remingtons do. (The TStudio doesnâ€™t say it on the box or description. Company website confirms it.) Revlon and Remington Damage Control have tourmaline technology, the TStudio does not.

The Revlonâ€™s concentrator attachment stays on. The Remingtonâ€™s fall off often. If I put the dryer down to adjust my hair, it comes off some of the time. It's hot to put it back on.

All three take about the same time to dry my hair. I may have gotten slightly better results (less wavy) with the Remingtons than with the Revlon. I say â€œmayâ€ because the difference wasnâ€™t large enough to be clear. Some days I do a better job than others. Human error, you know.

The Damage Control felt like it took less effort and the reason is most likely because itâ€™s the lightest of the three. The shell of the DC and Revlon are plastic while the T|Studio uses better quality materials. But it could be the better quality materials that make it heavier.

I can only assume the DC is cheaper than the T|Studio because of its plastic shell even though it has tourmaline technology, which the T|Studio does not.

Iâ€™ve yet to try the diffusers. Whenever I wear my hair curly, I let it dry naturally. Thatâ€™s the whole point of going curly â€“ not having to do any hair drying. As for noise â€“ I canâ€™t answer which one is quietest because Iâ€™m deaf. Itâ€™s not a good idea to wear hearing aids while drying wet hair. :)

The winner? The Remington DC because it takes the least amount of effort to use and produces the same results as the others. The T|Studio is just too heavy and the Revlon doesnâ€™t perform as well as the DC.

Updated 29 Nov 2016: This is the second hairdryer as the first one lasted only eight months. The company replaced it. And now the second one died within two years. (Warranty is 24 months.) column6: Dial Complete Antibacterial Foaming Hand Soap Refill, Spring Water, 32 Fluid Ounces
column14:
This soap is way better than some reviewers may lead one to believe. As a veteran Amazon customer (I just passed 400 orders since 'finding Amazon in 2007), I have learned to check out the worst reviews first. I am consistently amazed at how some people assess some products on this site. The 'watered down' claims lead me to believe that this product is not being used properly; that is, it is being poured into a standard liquid soap dispenser. The bottle clearly indicates (in the lower left of the bottle) that it be used "Only with the COMPLETE FOAM Pump". Like a mister or atomizer or even a car's carburetor, liquid must pass through a particular mechanism to achieve the desired property for effective use. Also, be sure to apply it with dry hands, as directed, to get the best results. Yes, I sound condescending here, but it still holds true: some reviewers just don't know what they're talking about, for whatever reason.

As for the product itself, I like the scent (not too strong and similar to what it says it is) and little soap is wasted like the gelled kind can be, where some literally goes from hand to sink in an instant. There is also a version of this exact same scent in gel. I like that one, too, but prefer the coverage and lesser wastefulness of the foam variety. The price here is terrible (I bought the same product for four bucks at Walmart.com), but that's more of a seller issue and did not play a part in my rating. It's a good product that I like; hence, the four stars.

column14: I received a sample of this product as a Buzz Agent.  So I was happy to give it a try!  I have very simple criteria that I take into account when buying deodorant: It needs to take less than 5 seconds to apply, it needs to keep me dry & smelling clean, and it should not irritate my skin. Unfortunately, the Secret Outlast Clear Gel failed on all of these. Upon first glances, the packaging is pretty. For a week, I used this every morning and again after working out/showering. I apply 1 "click" of product to each under arm. I then have to fan each armpit for about 20 seconds each to get the gel to dry. This is 35 seconds longer than I would like to worry about deodorant application. Of course that is silly, but if the deodorant actually worked, I think I would have happily continued fanning away. Throughout my day, I constantly noticed a lot of smells. I do not sweat much, so the peculiar mix of deodorant and sweat was distracting. I was self conscious wearing this. Without worrying about smelling of body odor, the scent of the deodorant was stronger than I prefer. To add insult to injury, at the end of the week the product started irritating my armpits. They were itchy. I was unhappy. I decided to keep this Secret to myself at that point.

column6: Guardian Envoy 480 Deluxe Rolling Walker - Blue
column13: A Comparison of the Two Rollators I Own
column14: The Envoy is a robust unit with very little assembly required. The larger wheels, which are 8", have a little more difficulty swiveling around in tight spaces than another model with the smaller 6" wheels that I was able to try out for a couple of weeks. But when I went on a paved forest path, the smaller wheel model just couldn't cut it. The Envoy 8" wheel model is much better on rougher terrain because of those larger wheels. The basket is in front, which I find useful. The seat is fairly comfortable and made with a durable material. The Envoy is also several pounds heavier than the smaller wheel models.  All in all, 4 stars for the tight spaces and and additional weight. I used a scale and the Guardian Envoy 480 Deluxe Rolling Walker weights in at 19 pounds. As age and disability is an issue in placing the walker in a vehicle, I found the Super Light Rollator Lightweight Aluminum Loop Brake Folding Walker Adult W/height Adjustable Seat By Healthline, weighing in at 13.2 pounds to be much more acceptable. There are differences of course. Seat size is somewhat smaller, and tends to flop around a little when removing the rollator from the vehicle and the carrying pouch is underneath the seat rather than in front of it. An additional amount of assembly is required. But nothing serious. I found that the weight and maneuverability factors outweighed the minor inconveniences by a large margin. And  It was also less expensive. I own both. I love the Super Light because it is lighter and more manuverable. However, if you are a large person, the Guardian Envoy 480 may be your ticket to increased mobility. Good Luck!

column14:
I don't usually write reviews, but if this can help anyone with hair damage, I'll write it.
My hair has been through highlights and hair color before and was fine I've never had breakage in my life; but one day my hair stylist called out & another stylist highlighted my hair with BLEACH!! Left it on my hair 2 long and my hair started breaking off as soon as I got home. Every time I combed my hair, brushed my hair, washed my hair, even touched my hair, large pieces of hair would break off. The breakage was REAL y'all.

I had no idea what to do, nothing was working. No amount of deep conditioning, keratin, or oils were helping me. Even the Aphogee 2 minute miracle treatment did little to nothing.

When I you this product stopped my breakage in it's tracks; I mean it made all my breakage stop completely.
Don't use it for another 6 weeks, because it'll be 2 harsh on your hair, but my gawd this treatment is seriously a life savor.

I use the Aphogee 2 minute miracle after every wash as a substitute in between my 6 week periods (you might want to purchase that too).
My hair is growing back stronger & healthier, & it's able to maintain it's length because of this product.

I plan cut my hair later to even out all the breakage, but this seriously is a miracle product. I just had to review!

column6: Jamila Henna Powder, 100 grams
column13: I do not shampoo until at least 48 hours later but I'm sure 36 hours is fine, too
column14: I add about 2 tablespoons of apple cider vinegar to 1 package and then enough water to make an applesauce consistency. I let it set for about 3 hours. I then apply it to my whole head, put on a plastic shower cap and go about my day as it sets for about six hours. It doesn't stain my forehead or face but it sure as heck will stain your hands and fingernails, so wear gloves. It will also stain fabric and carpet so be careful. Afterward, I rinse well, rub a ton of cleansing conditioner in my hair to release the henna and rinse well, rubbing my scalp until the water is completely clear. I do not shampoo until at least 48 hours later but I'm sure 36 hours is fine, too. My light brown hair becomes a wonderful bright, shiny copper!!

column6: 3D Fiber Lash Mascara, 300X Fiber Mascara by Lash Factory - Our Best 3D Fiber Lashes - Waterproof, Smudge-Proof, No Clump, Long Lasting, 3D Mascara
column14:
This is a fun product to try out that will give you longer lashes for the day. It comes with two tubes - the gel and the fibers. First, you apply some mascara, then gel, then fibers...to add length and volume, continue to add coats of gel alternating with fiber. I find that with any makeup, it's easy to overdo it. I like it to look natural and just apply 1-2 coats.

If I could change the design on the tube a bit - notice how it says "300x" in big writing on each tube. Instead, I'd rather it say "gel" or "fiber" in big writing. As it is, I can barely make out the writing below the "300x." Since you're going back and forth between tubes, it would be easier if it's clearly labeled. I just try to remember the fibers are in the shorter tube. Once you use this for a while though, everything starts getting mixed. The fibers end up in the gel and the gel in the fibers. That's just inevitable when you're alternating like that. With sensitivity, I haven't personally had a problem but I know some that have. It may be because I only apply 1 or 2 coats. Also, I would make sure not to sleep with it on.

Overall, I like this product. Although, my expectations weren't that high. I just thought it'd be nice to have longer lashes than I had without it, and the 300x does help to make them noticeably longer in minutes. Product provided at a promotional price for testing and review purposes, but all opinions are honest and my own.

The blue/green/purple colors of the files reminds me of sea glass. Everyone who has seen them has commented on how pretty they are, and using them makes me feel very sophisticated and fancy. column13: Stylet not long enough? Try this.
column14: I can tell from a few reviews that a few people are having trouble with the stylet not being long enough. I showed the unit to my professional Electrologist and she wants me to be able to get rid of my hair any way I can, whether or not I'm paying her for it. She immediately notices the stylet is not long enough.  After using it, I realized, she was indeed correct. So what I did, was remove the end cap off where the stylet feeds through, and using a 120 grain (a 260 would be better) filed that little metal guide almost down to the plastic. Now it's working like a charm.

column6: Azfasst Green Tea Moisturizer
column14: I thought turning 40 this year would be hard.  Who would of thought deeper wrinkles and frequent breakouts would happen almost as the clock hit midnight on my birthday.  I tried so many products: skin tighteners, lifters, hemorrhoid cream ect.  Anything to try and lessen my wrinkles. (Side note: Don't use the hemorrhoid cream.  It REALLY burns)  I hated looking so tired all time.  I was complaining to one of my friends about it and she said she used Azfasst.  She always has such beautiful skin. I figured I had tried everything else, I had nothing to lose.  I received the product very quickly.  I loved the packaging!  I used the eye cream every night.  After a few weeks, I saw that my wrinkles were not as deep.  For my breakouts, I used the gel.  My zits went away at a faster rate than if I did nothing.  And even for the ones I picked (we all are guilty of picking, so don't judge me.), the redness was gone within a couple of days of using the gel. My skin tends to be kind of dry, a little flaky and red spots (God, I sound horrible! LOL! My skin is sensitive, what can I say) The combination of the moisturizer and gel totally evened my skin out.  So here is my conclusion: Azfasst is a worthwhile investment.  A little bit goes a long way, so the bottles will last months!  Right now, I am 6 months past my 40th birthday. Thus far, I have had my first mammogram (not fun!), been told I am a candidate for bifocals, am officially called "Ma'am and not Miss" anymore.  BUT......my skin is now BEAUTIFUL!!!  THANK YOU TO THE MAKERS OF AZFASST!!!!  You made turning 40 a lot less traumatic!

column6: Rose Geranium Pure Therapeutic Grade Essential Oil
column13: A Step by Step Honest Review of How This Product Did NOT Work For Me
column14: I purchased this product a couple of months ago and finally had a friend bring it to me here in the Caribbean where I live with my wife and four dogs. I was turned on to it by the website Primallyinspired and could not have been more excited about a natural solution to the tick problems we experience. Count me as another advocate of natural solutions who refuses to use products such as Frontline, not only for lack of desire to inject harsh chemicals with side effects into my pups, but the price of monthly injections is outrageous.  Before applying the rose geranium oil, I bathed my dogs with a flea and tick shampoo and checked them over thoroughly to ensure a clean start. Since then I have consistently applied the Edenâ€™s Garden Rose Geranium drops DAILY as instructed on the aforementioned website for a week, and I can tell you, it has had no effect whatsoever.  In fact, I just pulled out 7 blood-engorged ticks within a three inch radius of where the product was applied on one of my dogs, and 4 ticks in the same area of another.  As an experiment in reaction to my disappointment, I placed the ticks near a drop of the oil I applied to a napkin, and the ticks made no motion to retreat.  Again, I am an outspoken advocate for all natural solutions to all ailments (I don't even take aspirin or Tylenol), and I am in no way endorsing Frontline for the reasons I mentioned already.  The painful reality, though, is that you can be duped by what you believe to be an honest, benign natural products manufacturerâ€™s scheme just as easily as if it were a fly-by-night companyâ€”even more easily because these manufacturers cannot legally claim their products effectiveness in any use.  Itâ€™s very easy and inexpensive for a company to have its employees, friends, and the hired hands of writers buy hundreds or thousands of its products and write glowing reviews. (Donâ€™t tell me you havenâ€™t noticed, and I know how much time youâ€™ve wasted away trying to distinguish whatâ€™s realand whatâ€™s invented.) Five star reviews, real or invented, pay off handsomely in the end.  Thankfully, there are plenty of  manufacturers of natural products you can rely on, and perhaps rose geranium oil is effective in other applications, but in my experience, elimination of ticks is definitely not one of them. I hope you can see Iâ€™ve introduced no bias, nor have I endorsed alternative products in this review. I can say that I actually like the productâ€™s smell.  So buy it for that reason (if you think 10ml of any essential oil is worth nearly $30.00 shipped at the time of this writing), but donâ€™t buy it for tick prevention.

column6: Neutrogena Rainbath Moisture Rich Shower and Bath Gel, 32 Fluid Ounce
column13: Wonderful product! See full review for differences in fragrance by name and color
column14:
I love all Rainbath body washes, they are wonderful for a few reasons: Large bottle size with pump so this is really easy to place in the shower and use without having to worry about refilling too often or worrying about bar soap getting gross, and no bottle cap to lose or constantly open/close. (It's the little things!) All of their body washes work well, and a bonus is that there are so many scents to choose from, (again..it's the little things that make this product even better.)
Ocean Mist - light blue (not to be confused with the darker blue color of the Moisture Rich) Ocean Mist is my favorite, it is light and refreshing - does not smell too fruity/girly or manly.
Pear - light green, also a wonderful scent, light enough that you can't smell the fruit scent too much after your shower (if concerned about the after effects)
Pomegranate - dark red, another good scent but a little stronger smell & a more fruity smell than Pear
Moisture Rich - darker blue, a good scent that smells good but a little too on the manly side for me. Not offensive or cologne overkill smell, but a stronger scent I would associate to be more masculine
Original - darker amber color, definitely more masculine scent. Really is not one of my favorites at all. Still a good body wash but I find the smell to be a little harsh especially compared to the other options.

Price Point - It's definitely a more expensive body wash, but volume wise it is worth the expense since a little does go a long way. And again not many products come in a array of scents in this volume and the convenient pump. Amazon has good deals on this, but you can also find it in some brand name stores, or bulk warehouse stores - however their options for scent and volume tend to fluctuate so coming back to Amazon is always a nice option if those fail.

Overall, a wonderful product that is worth it.

column14: I thought turning 40 this year would be hard.  Who would of thought deeper wrinkles and frequent breakouts would happen almost as the clock hit midnight on my birthday.  I tried so many products: skin tighteners, lifters, hemorrhoid cream ect.  Anything to try and lessen my wrinkles. (Side note: Don't use the hemorrhoid cream.  It REALLY burns)  I hated looking so tired all time.  I was complaining to one of my friends about it and she said she used Azfasst.  She always has such beautiful skin. I figured I had tried everything else, I had nothing to lose.  I received the product very quickly.  I loved the packaging!  I used the eye cream every night.  After a few weeks, I saw that my wrinkles were not as deep.  For my breakouts, I used the gel.  My zits went away at a faster rate than if I did nothing.  And even for the ones I picked (we all are guilty of picking, so don't judge me.), the redness was gone within a couple of days of using the gel. My skin tends to be kind of dry, a little flaky and red spots (God, I sound horrible! LOL! My skin is sensitive, what can I say) The combination of the moisturizer and gel totally evened my skin out.  So here is my conclusion: Azfasst is a worthwhile investment.  A little bit goes a long way, so the bottles will last months!  Right now, I am 6 months past my 40th birthday. Thus far, I have had my first mammogram (not fun!), been told I am a candidate for bifocals, am officially called "Ma'am and not Miss" anymore.  BUT......my skin is now BEAUTIFUL!!!  THANK YOU TO THE MAKERS OF AZFASST!!!!  You made turning 40 a lot less traumatic!

column14: This stuff  is great. I'm pretty clumsy at putting on polish AND I lack the patience to let it dry fully. These products help With both problems. I waited a couple of minutes and used the Zoya fast drying drops, then went to bed pretty soon thereafter (within 30 minutes). I woke up with perfectly beautiful fingers and toes. column6: Razorock Mudder Focker Shave Soap
column14:
Buy this soap my friends.

I used this soap for my first ever DE shave. Â Thanks to the gentle prodding of a close friend I endeavored to shed my un-kept banner of the modern day hipster. Â Fearing the onslaught of comments from my community of hairy (though admittedly stylish) friends, I decided that the goatee would be a practical middle ground. Â To accomplish this without serious discomfort and blunt-steel drudgery, I was steered towards Italian Barber. Â With a Mission razor, an Omega brush, and a sampler of blades, I was determined to be economical. Â 

One tends to be drawn to the elegant and stately creams of yore, but I was on a budget. Â So after much deliberation, I picked Mudder Focker. Â Amusing name, seemingly mystical ingredients, and a fantastic price. Â I thought that perhaps later I would purchase some higher ends creams to augment my status in the shaving world and step up towards a better product. Â I have never been so wrong. Â Struck immediately by the elegant scent that was overwhelming in its depth, I knew my attempt at frugality had paid dividends.

Â I am never sure how to describe the scent; it is not a strength of mine. Â I get a sweet, earthy, grounded scent. Â Artisan vanilla cola and a light musky cologne. Â This does not do it justice, but it must suffice. Â I never knew before this time that shaving could be enjoyable. Â I managed to whip up a tremendous lather on my first attempt, and have yet to find a soap that builds a lather this easily and with such a wide margin for hydration. Â It always left my skin feeling great, and aftershaves were generally simply an excuse to experiment with more product. They were rarely a necessity.

Â Since then I have tried to bring into the wet shaving fold as many cartridge enslaved gents as I could. Â Â I gave a good friend my Gillette Canadian Tech, and decided there was only one soap of quality that could go with it. Â My tub of Mudder Focker. Â Dearly parted but hopefully well given. Â I have since tried dozens of soaps and many manufacturers, including SMdF and other razorock products, but my latest purchase was nevertheless another Mudder Focker. I have never before ordered the same soap twice. Cheers Joe for my first and still most treasured soap.

column13: Ideal if you use a lot of different matte and shimmer colours or if you are a trainee makeup artist
column14:
Sent for review, this product is available in 2 versions and the version that I picked was SP180.

The product itself is very well presented in an outer black box and is surrounded by a significant amount of thick bubble wrap.

The quality is very good for the price point and whilst the kit set is heavy, the size is large.

The design is modern, classic and retro and inside the box you get 4 layers, 6 trays in total with 30 colours on each tray. That's an incredible 180 colours in total.

To access the trays you just slide them left and right but the bottom 2 trays are different though as you need to pick up the top tray to get to the bottom one.

The mirror on this is a very good size, about the same size as a CD cover in length and width and it's definitely a mirror that I like.

I liked the fact that there are so many colours to choose from and how easy and quickly they are to access.

In use I found them to be very good and having both the matte and shimmer was a bonus as its usually one or the other.

If you use a significant amount of different coloured makeup then these would be ideal. If not, they would make a good gift (as long as the recipient used a lot of different coloured make up) and also for a trainee makeup artist who is looking for a complete set that won't break the bank.

column6: GoodSense Minoxidil Topical Solution 5% Hair Regrowth Treatment
column14:
I have a problem with slick baldness on the top and front of my head. I do not use it every day, nor in the full amount suggested. I use it infrequently, sometimes one to three times a week, and sometimes I forget to use it weekly at all. The product is working for me, as there has appeared healthy plugs of hair at the front and top of my head. There is also a thin fuzzy growth overall. I have had hair loss in this area for years, and I am using this product as a last resort, very cautiously. I personally do not believe in one size fits all, and using the smallest amount that I can to be safe. The label on the product says the effect of the product will last for only three years. I got a six month supply, which at the slow cautious rate that I am using it, should last a long time. I started using the product in late march of 2015, the results have been gradually occurring over time.
Obviously, I do not know if the end of using this product will result in complete restoration of my hair, only time will tell.

column13: One of the very best for this 59 year old!
column14: I noticed my skin becoming drab and wrinkly when I was 58 years old and knew I needed a killer sunscreen. It smooths out my complexion giving it a youthful look without a pasty appearance, lasting at least 12 hours. It is slightly thick but with practice I have been able to blend it to a bit thinner coverage that looks very natural, and without having to use any other products except moisturizer, also with sunscreen and blush. After I ran out I decided to try other products hoping something a little less expensive would do as well but have never found it. Even their BB cream universal color doesn't compare so I snatch this one up especially when the price is lower. This has been my "saving face" for an aging woman who hates looking older!

column6: Conair Styling Essentials Ultimate Updo Clip Strong & Lightweight 1 ea
column14: This little guy has changed my life!  I wear my hair up every day now, which is great for hot, humid weather.  Start with a mid pony tail, twist up, tuck the twisted pony tail at the top back down and hide under the first part of the twist.  Take the clip and poke it into the top of the bun/French twist you have just made, at a perpendicular angle, to secure it into the hair next to your head.  Then tilt the clip up and push it down through the twist, close to your head.  Voila, secure all day, and you can't even feel that it's there.  My hair is a bit past shoulder length.  I dry my roots and leave the ends of my hair damp; this seems to help the updo stay put.

column6: EmaxDesign Makeup Brushes 10+1 Pieces Makeup Brush Set, 10 Pieces Professional Foundation Blending Blush Eye Face Liquid Powder Cream Cosmetics Brushes & 1 Piece Black Beauty Sponge Blender With Bag
column13: Amazing set of unique brushes -- At an amazing price
column14:
I love trying new makeup brushes because with every set I discover at least one new design that I fall in love with. But some times the price of the brushes shock me. I'm a firm believer in the better the tools, the better the outcome but why would I pay over $100 for makeup brushes?? So when I was able to review these I was super excited but the price is SO low I half expected cheap brushes. Now I have nothing against cheap brushes but there is a big problem when they are cheaply made.
These brushes are neither cheap quality or cheaply made. The bristles are a very nice quality fibers and the feel great when I apply my makeup. They are soft but stiff enough to hold/apply powder with little/none falling off all over my face or clothing. The bristles are securely in place with a gold metal material band. They do not fall out when I'[m using them.
The brush handles are well made and will not fall apart in a few days. I really have had a few do that!! There is a card that tells what each brush is used but I'm a rule breaker/bender. So I use the brush for the intended purpose first. If I like it awesome, if I don't I use it for something else. You never know what a brush can do until you try.
The handles for both the short brushes and tall brushes are comfortable to hold. They are just long enough to grab and move smoothly with the contours of my face/eyes. The bristles/brushes are very uniquely shaped and can get into the corners very easily.
I received this product complimentary in exchange for my honest opinion but the opinion expressed is all my own.

column6: Lipogaine Big 3 Premium Hair Loss Prevention shampoo for Men and Women (2 in 1 formula)- 8 oz
column13: Great when paired with other products
column14:
I started my hair loss regimen (minoxidil and finasteride) about 10 years ago as a way to preempt any hair loss, and as the years ticked on, I had been very happy with my results. Full head of hair despite a strong genetic predisposition toward it. I'd been wanting to supplement my treatment with a shampoo. I researched a number of products designed to counter hair loss. My criteria were: a) a shampoo that contained clinically proven ingredients that combat DHT and stimulate hair regrowth, and b) a shampoo that actually worked like a quality shampoo (volumized hair, smelled nice, foamed up, etc.). A number of shampoos were recommended, which I tried, but it was this Lipogaine brand and formula that were consistently referenced by many experienced guys in the same boat.

Combined with a regimen of other products I use, this shampoo has all the qualities of a nice shampoo, and I've been using it for about two years. Every guy is different, and I can't speak for men who are at a more advanced stage of hair loss, or who tried combatting hair loss much later than I chose to, so again, I'm mainly speaking as a guy who, with a full head of hair, chose to preempt the loss. The process ain't broke, so until something better comes along, this is the gold standard I'm sticking to. Use it as directed, and I strongly recommend pairing it with a daily treatment of minoxidil and finasteride (doctor prescribed for the latter). Hope this helps!

column13: Been using these for years.  Excellent product!
column14:
There's no cleaner showering than one that entails a full body exfoliation.

My Korean girlfriend introduced me to this product, which is feels kind of like a scouring pad for the skin. It's not so rough it damages the skin but just enough to slough off the dead cells. It is something many asians use and is commonplace in public spas in asia.

I like to use soap with this product however my wife uses it in the traditional way, which is without soap, after which she applies moisturizing lotion. She says there's a satisfaction in seeing the dead skin is scoured off your body into rolleds she calls "noodles" . I tried it and I admit it does tell you how dirty was and clean your body is when you're done. I like to use it with soap because I'm just used my Zest smell, plus I don't get the unsightly noodles. She says I don't do it that way I can't tell if I'm clean. Fair enough, honey :)

Anyway I HIGHLY recommend everyone buy the smaller "mittens" (which are just square pockets) for the body, and this one to scrub your back.

column14: I was in search for a cheap, department store makeup that was non-comedogenic (won't clog pores) and would last. I ended up trying this one and have already bought and used 3 tubes. I dab it on my wrist and use a stipple brush to sweep and apply where needed. It find it blends well, and sticks all day. The color matches well for me and I usually put it on top of my foundation. Maybe it blends better with foundation? My only qualm is after you've had the product for a while, you can see if develops a different shade on the bottom on the tube. It hasn't effected the color when I apply it, it still matches- I only end up just taking a q-tip and mixing it up in the tube when that happens, which may only be once or twice. column13: I get super angry whenever my husband shaves his head and hair ...
column14: Ok I will be honest.....I get super angry whenever my husband shaves his head and hair goes EVERYWHERE!!!  This product has literally saved my marriage.  This haircut cape is essentially an umbrella (without the metal wires) that has been turned upside down. The product states that it is for kids, but like I said earlier I really purchased this product for my husband, and it fits him just fine (without velcroing the neck part, but it still worked!) Would recommend this to anyone with kids....or husbands that can't seem to not make a mess at hair cut time.
