column6: Belletto Studio Ultimate Airbrush System Skin Secrets Foundation Set
column13: Lacking customer service and a product that's just okay
column14:
I've had my machine for about 2 weeks now, and have been trying all kinds of different makeup look combinations. Prior to my purchase direct from Belletto, I researched airbrush makeup how-to's and what not to do, how to clean the machine, how to apply the makeup, etc. When I received my "ultimate airbrush system", I went with the "light combination" foundation, and opt'd for the extra $50 package, which supposed gave 2 more foundation color choices, lustre drops, an additional blush and primer. Sounds great right...but my package was missing the primer drops. So I know you're asking what does that have to do with the machine's performance...it's actually not the machine that's really lacking, but the actual company that sells the machine. And, if you purchase this machine brand, it's the same stinky customer service you'll have to deal with. When I contacted them via email, it was nearly a week before anyone bothered to respond...and the email demanded a photo copy of everything from the box it was shipped in, a copy of their packing slip, the invoice listing everything I'd purchased, pictures of the box's contents, a picture of all the contents with their packaging tops open, etc....with no promise they would help with anything. Hmmm, not exactly the customer oriented company they tout themselves to be.

Okay, enough of that, and onto the actual products review. The compressor is fairly quiet and has the ability to be dialed up high or low (a plus); the foundations are just okay...in the time period I received no response from Belletto, I purchased a different brand of airbrush foundations to use because the Belletto brand is somewhat drying and with no lustre drops, extremely matte. The blush colors are really pigmented, so spray sparingly or you'll end up looking like a clown. Also, a real negative is there are no instructions that come with the package. Instead, they comment that a video is available on YouTube, only they don't provide any web address at all...so the customer is left to figure it out themselves. Overall, if I could do a "do over" regarding the machine I purchased, I would likely go with another brand like Dinar.

Hope this helps in your search for an airbrush system and product. I will try and post another review later for the new foundations, blush and eye shadow products I bought from a different supplier.on't provide any web address at all...so the customer is left to figure it out themselves. Overall, if I could do a "do over" regarding the machine I purchased, I would likely go with another brand like Dinar.

Hope this helps in your search for an airbrush system and product. I will try and post another review later for the new foundations, blush and eye shadow products I bought from a different supplier.

column6: Skyroad(TM) Top Quality Exfoliating Scrub -4 items per package- (Made in Korea)
column13: Excellent product. Been using for years. Must have for my shower.
column14:
There's no cleaner showering than one that entails a full body exfoliation.

My Korean girlfriend introduced me to this product, which is feels kind of like a scouring pad for the skin. It's not so rough it damages the skin but just enough to slough off the dead cells. It is something many asians use and is commonplace in public spas in asia.

I like to use soap with this product however my wife uses it in the traditional way, which is without soap, after which she applies moisturizing lotion. She says there's a satisfaction in seeing the dead skin is scoured off your body into rolleds she calls "noodles" . I tried it and I admit it does tell you how dirty was and clean your body is when you're done. I like to use it with soap because I'm just used my Zest smell, plus I don't get the unsightly noodles. She says I don't do it that way I can't tell if I'm clean. Fair enough, honey :)

Anyway I HIGHLY recommend everyone buy the smaller "mittens" (which are just square pockets) for the body, and this one to scrub your back.

column14: I feel the same way about what I put on my face as I do about what I put in my body...the "cleaner" the better. My favorite thing about Puristica's retinol serum is the ingredient list which is full of organic and vegan ingredients and an effective 2.5% retinol. I can't say i always eat well, but I can always put the best ingredients on my body to absorb into my skin. Like other serums, the process is:wash, tone, serum, moisturizer and that's how I use this serum. The generous 2oz bottle holds a serum with good viscosity. This may seem funny to say, but I have tried other serums in dropper-delivery bottles and found them to be runny or watery. Puristica's serum is thick but melts to disperse easily across my face and absorbs quickly. There is little wait time for the serum to dry before moisturizer application. I have only used the product for a short time now so i can't speak to long-term results, but I do notice significantly more moisturized skin when I use this serum as part of my routine. My skin looks immediately plumped and refreshed in the morning, which is huge. I chose a retinol to stimulate the production of collagen and elastin so I am looking forward to the results from this natural, high potency product! * Discount given for unbiased opinion. I would recommend the product and order from the seller again.

I wasn't crazy about the price but after searching local stores and health stores to no avail, I decided to bite the bullet.  Well yesterday afternoon my Sweat Block was delivered. I put it on before bed. Rubbed it on the parts of my body that I mentioned above. Got up and off to work. I did shower as I do everyday.  The weather was a bit on the muggy side which would normally cause me to sweat. Happy to report I had a sweat proof day.  Wow.  I am sold.  I will update this post and let you know if it continues to keep me dry for 5-7 days.  I am golfing this Sunday and it is supposed to be humid so this will be the true test.  Hoping it continues to do what it claims to do.  BTW I have been a Prime member for a few years and constantly purchase here, however this is the first review I have ever written!

I received really fast. 2015-08-13 US 122664 R2G4058NIPM5MJ B00336EUTK 53434614 Crest 3D White Professional Effects Whitestrips Dental Teeth Whitening Strips Kit, 20 Treatments - Lasts 12 Months & Beyond Beauty 4 0 0 N N Surprisingly effective, some gum irritation I had been vaguely interested in tooth whitening in the past, but not enough to pay my dentist to do it. I was skeptical that the various "strip" type products on the market would work, so I was eager to try the Crest 3D Whitestrips. I had never used such a product before.

The first thing I noticed was how well they stuck to my teeth. The first couple of times, being unfamiliar with the process, I didn't get things lined up properly, but eventually I figured it out. I never had an issue with the strip loosening before its time was up.

In one week I might pull a 12 hour day shift and then 2 days later a night shift, so my under eyes are always puffy and now I am noticing bags and dark circles.

I've bought a few products off Amazon before, none of which were anything to write home about or even write a review about so when I came across this one I decided to take a proactive approach before purchasing. I actually took the ingredient list to my dermatologist and she approved. With her approval, I purchased with confidence.

After about 10 days of using the product, I started to notice a difference, nothing huge, I just felt "more awake" like my eyes looked less tired. Now that Iâ€™ve been using it for 3 months, I went from having bags under my eyes to only having slight imperfections that only I notice.

The only down side is that you have to keep using it but I think it is well worth it. It's worth mentioning that with any product that you use, you will have to maintain so that's not an "issue" per se.

column6: Dark Spot Corrector â€“ Age Spot Remover - Clinically Proven â€“ Visibly Reduce & Fades Dark Spots, Age Spots & Traces of Past Acne Scars â€“ 4 Times Stronger Than Outdated Hydroquinone â€“ Organic Compound with Niacinamide (Vitamin B) to Expedite Spot and Pigment Correction - Certified USA Facilities â€“ Extremely Effective Skin Lightening or Your Money Back!
column14: I have brown sun stains on my face from years of being outside without sunscreen.  The spots cover my cheeks and under my eyes - not attractive. I didn't expect PureLx to be a medical miracle but I read all the reviews and it sounded like people were pleasantly surprised by its effectivness.  I bought the larger size for $35. and used it for 3 days and nights.  Now my face looks like I've been stung by a dozen bees!  It started to get a lumpy appearance after my second application, but I thought...$35 bucks - I gotta give it a chance.  Now, after 3 days, friends are asking me with Horror "What Happened to Your Face!"  I was going to my towns fair tonight, but now don't want to be seen in public!  There were no written instructions inside or outside the box for use so I used as directed on their website.  You can believe me when I say No One paid me for this review and I paid full price for the product and shipping.  Brown spots or Lumps...you decide! OK...now it's 2 days after my last post...My face is looking even more red and swollen, even though I haven't used the product in 2 days.  Monday I'll have to visit my Dr.  I hope anyone thinking of ordering this product will think again.  As another reviewer stated, "I have chemical burns from this product."  I wish I'd read more reviews before I ordered it!

column6: Gold Plated 18k Elvish Script Tungsten Carbide Unisex Laser-etched Wedding Ring Band- 7mm
column14:
This is 'My Precious!' I have now worn this every day for three months. I badly bent my 20 yr old wedding band and this was a runner-up replacent; having lost a different tungsten ring after one day, I told my wife to try this.
I decided I would not be getting emotionally attached to my ring from this point on, maybe swooping them out each year for fun. The ring is comfort fit on the inside, gold plated, then etched somehow 'magically'. The elvish writing is obvious to me, and I can see it when I'm wearing, but it's so subtle that not one person noticed the etching in 3 months. I was able to hide the inner nerd. The ring is heavy and has not scratched at all even when I've felt like it took a few hits, no sign of wear. The gold has held up great! I could box it up and it would appear new.
Can't find anything wrong with it except it doesn't turn me invisible.

column6: King Will TYRE 8mm Black Brushed Matte Finish Tungsten Carbide Ring Domed Engagement Wedding Band Comfort Fit
column14: This ring excites my inner nerd. I bought this for wearing to work and the golf course so that I don't lose or damage my expensive wedding band. When I purchased this I was expecting a lightweight ring that would scratch up pretty easily and end up broken or dingy looking quickly. None of these things have happened yet, I am legally blind and use my hands to help me see my way around. I have ran this ring into every single corner a few walls and doors still zero scratches. This ring with the weight and quality to it looks and feels like I just got done spending $300-$400 on a band. The metal is very Shiney and slick looking, the art work around the center looks like one of those mazes with the little metal ball. The ring looks like it would be a spinner ring but it is just fashioned with an edge. I think this makes this gives it a very high end tough. I would recommend this very good weighted and sturdy ring to every guy I know, this is a perfect wedding band, thumb ring or just casual ring to look good.  I received this item at a discount in exchange for an honest review.

column6: King Will 8mm Step Edge High Polished Celtic Design Dragon Knot Wedding Band Tungsten Ring
column14:
This tungsten ring is so much nicer than the images show. It has a Celtic design in a dragon knot around the band.

Width: 8mm
Finish: Step Edge which is eye catching
Shine: High Polished
Sizing: Accurate

This is an impressive ring. Even the packaging is high quality.

Tungsten is becoming a popular alternative to gold in wedding bands. I used to think that these were more for men because they are so tough and don't show wearing. But I have been proven wrong.. This is a gender neutral band that would make a beautiful matching wedding set.

Care for this ring is simple, just wash while wearing. The inlay is covered so dirt and debris doesn't get in or around the etching around the band.

column14: Absolutely love this Qalo band!  My husband has a job where he is constantly using his hands in tight spaces. In fact, a few years back he got his original wedding band stuck while repairing a pipe and had to have someone help him to get it off. Scary, I know. When I learned of these Qalo bands, I didn't think twice about replacing his old band with this one for work. It is so comfortable that he actually prefers this band to his wedding band now. I don't mind, as I feel safe with him wearing this one. We ordered the black and it runs true to size. Fits great and as rough as my husband is on it, it still looks perfect months later.  I would definitely recommend to anyone, whether you work with your hands a lot, or not. Very safe and comfortable!

column6: King Will 8mm Mens Tungsten Carbide High Polished Celtic Laser Etched Ring
column14: What a pretty ring. I bought this for wearing to work and the golf course so that I don't lose or damage my expensive wedding band. When I purchased this I was expecting a lightweight ring that would scratch up pretty easily and end up broken or dingy looking quickly.  None of these things have happened yet, I am legally blind and use my hands to help me see my way around. I have ran this ring into every single corner a few walls and doors still zero scratches. This ring with the weight and quality to it looks and feels like I just got done spending $300-$400 on a band. The metal is very Shiney and slick looking, the art work around the center is a really cool and interesting touch. I would recommend this very good weighted and sturdy ring to every guy I know, this is a perfect thumb ring, wedding band, or just casual ring to look good.

column6: Pair of 20g 3/8\ Surgical Steel Horseshoe Earrings"
column13: Standard earring gauge, good size for earlobes.
column14:
These are quite nice! They're about the standard earring gauge, which is what I needed. (I knew 18 would be too thick for my piercings, but these fit perfectly and comfortably.) As for diameter, these are a nice size for earlobes. I'd suspect they might be a bit big for upper cartilage, but I needed them for the second holes in my earlobes, and they're perfect for that. They seem quite sturdy, too, didn't bend out of shape when I was trying to get the cones unscrewed... I was concerned that being so thin they'd bend, but they didn't.
I honestly only got them because one of the piercings, after 20 years, got infected - I had gone a while wearing nothing in them, and after putting in a new pair of earrings, one didn't seem to like them much even though they were 14k gold. I knew they'd heal way faster with hoops and salt soaks, but the infinity hoops I had were the impossible-to-fasten kind with the wire that has to go into the tube, so after a day or two of annoyance I ordered these. They arrived quickly as expected, and were in perfect shape. They were inside a small cellophane bag, inside a thick plastic pouch with a card in it, but the outer shipping envelope was huge! It was a 9x12 bubble mailer! Way bigger than needed, but it arrived safely and not bent, so I'm happy.
I will say if you've not dealt with this kind of earring before, the cones are TEENY. Seriously teeny. And I found them a little hard to get loose at first. I'd have preferred balls actually, but I didn't find any of those with Prime shipping, so I got the cones. They're cute, but I managed to lose one little cone the very first time I put these in. My fault, of course, it slipped as I was trying to screw it back on. I'm hoping it'll magically show back up though I searched the whole floor and never found it. In the meantime I grabbed a pair of fish-hook style earrings with the little rubber stoppers, and put the stopper on the back side of the one missing a cone. Not as cute, but at least the earring will stay in. All in all, I'm pleased!

The Swarovski Elements Crystal heart is a light lavender shade. The heart measures about 5/8 x 5/8\\\\\". The heart & transparent Swarovski crystals sparkle. Very pretty.
I like the large size of the pendant.

The necklace is 16.5\\\\\" long & is made from 18K white gold plated alloy. The 1/4\\\\\" lobster claw clasp is great quality, but a little small for me to fasten. I added an extension which makes the necklace longer & easier for me to put on.

I don't know how to explain it, but I think the large sized pendant is trendy & I feel the designer has a great eye for proportion & knows what looks good.

The necklace is nicely packaged in a white gift box. Included is a circular hand mirror & a microfiber cleaning cloth embedded with the Fancydeli icon. Great for gift giving or treat yourself.

From Amazon's Product Description:
â˜…â˜…Fancydeli offers a 60 day 100% money back guarantee.
â˜…â˜… If you're not COMPLETELY SATISFIED with our product, you will get a COMPLETE REFUND. PERIOD!

The necklace arrived quickly & was purchased for a reduced price & provided by Fancydeli for evaluation purposes."

column14:
At first, I was delighted to find this necklace for super cheap on Amazon. I purchased it for only $43 versus the $187 MSRP if you buy it directly from Luv AJ's website. Unfortunately, I will be returning it, as I found the quality of the product to be seriously lacking.

It's clear that the links of the necklace's chain are made by pouring molten metal into a mold -- the edges of most of the chain were pretty rough and/or sharp on the necklace I received. Also, the center "pendant" of the chain is obviously made of gold-coated plastic. It's awkwardly lightweight in the middle. I think the necklace may have been made this way in order not to weigh down the way the necklace hangs on the wearer; however, it's obvious that the finish on this part of the necklace would show wear in a different way than the metal parts. I think with only a few wears, the necklace would look very obviously costume and cheap.

Definitely worth it to buy this from Amazon for the better price and return policy, but only if you feel that $43 is a reasonable price for cheaply made jewelry.

column6: 10k Gold Polished Hoop Earrings, (1.1\ Diameter)"
column14: I've had this pair of hoops on my Wish List for about a year, and they have fluctuated in price from $58 to $39. When they hit $39, I bought them. As a $39 pair of 10K hoops, they're fine. However, I wouldn't pay any more for these. One hoop needed bending to form a circle that matched the other earring, and the other hoop, the prongs for the snap-bar closure needed tightening so it would snap into place. I prefer 10K as it's stronger than 14K so they withstood my tampering :).  Due to their hollow tubing, they are very light-weight and comfortable to wear. So 4 stars...you can't expect a thick 1" hoop with the price of gold being what it is these days.

column6: Spoil Cupid Rhodium-Plated Sterling Silver Plain and Smooth Round Bead Ball-Shape Stud Earrings
column14:
We just got these cute little 3MM earrings today. I was going to wear them in my second ear hole but decided that they were more for my 15 year old daughter. They are VERY small and petite. My daughter decided to put them in her very top hole, on the top of her ear. The are actually perfect for that hole. I believe these would be perfect for a small girls first ear piercing or as a third or fourth hole on the ear. These (3MM) are NOT ideal for an adult first hole. I would recommend these (larger sizes) for anyone that wants a stud earring that is not too flashy.
I received this product at a discount/free for my honest review. The opinions are 100% mine.

column14:
This tungsten ring is simply beautiful.

The design is simple but striking. It has smooth clean lines. The inlay is offset which is eye catching. The edges are smooth and the ceramic center inlay is flush so it stays clean.

This would be a nice ring to wear by either gender. My engagement ring slips right up against it so it would make a nice wedding band if you wanted matching rings.

Tungsten is becoming a popular alternative to gold and it is certainly less expensive. We have had several tungsten rings over the years and I like that they do not show wear.

column6: COI Jewelry Ceramic Ring With Shell Inlays (From US3.5 to US16)
column14:
The ring is substantial and comfortable with a smooth and sturdy beveled edge. However, the product description and photo are misleading. The central band is the cobalt-chrome referred to in the description, but in the photo it can be misinterpreted as a continuation of the white ceramic band; the effect is garish. Similarly (and this is much more important,) the darker blue bands and inlay are NOT mother-of-pearl but some kind of cheap reflective foil, which is nowhere mentioned in the item description. The genuine shell inlay is dull and unattractive--cheap cross-sections of the shell rather than smooth and lustrous. You can see that in the photo, but the photo does not convey how dull and charmless the actual inlay is. NOT worth the asking price by any stretch of the imagination.

Also, do an internet search for "COI Jewelry" before you buy from these people. I didn't, and I wish I had.

column6: ZLYC Women Lady Fashion Elegant Green Crystal Statement Bib Choker Necklace
column13: This is very beautiful, classy, and unique!
column14:
This is an absolutely stunning necklace! The green is so vibrant and absolutely beautiful! The leaf shape that all of the main stones are in R just perfection. There's really no other way to describe it. When I opened the box, I was blown away, and after I took a couple of pictures had to immediately put it on.

Even the backside of the necklace is pretty, whenever I turned the necklace around, I was very happy about the fact that it wasn't super boring and plain. It was beautiful.

The length is perfect, it's about 17 to 19 inches, and it is not necessarily a choker, but it's just because I have kind of a skinny neck. But it lays perfectly. One of my biggest issues with buying a choker is that they usually have a tendency to spend, and after wearing this for a couple of hours, I did not how to turn it in at all, not once. That's a huge thing, especially if I'm going out for the evening. The last thing that I want to do is have to worry about whether or not my necklace is it going to be spun.

I love that this has its own unique and beautiful markings. I definitely don't want to wear the same thing that 5 million other people are wearing, so that part makes me very very happy. It's just so beautiful and vibrant.

I would definitely tell anyone who's looking for a piece of jewelry that was unique that this is definitely one to be purchased. You cannot go wrong with this expecially considering the price! You won't find anything of this quality, and that is as well made for this price!

I received this product at a discounted rate for an honest review.

column6: Sterling Silver Oval Created Opal and Round Created Pink Sapphire Flower Ring, Size 8
column13: Super pretty, but band feels cheap.
column14:
Cons: The band feels like a bit cheap plastic - I think the sterling silver it claims to have is simply painted on. It doesn't feel metal at all. I am worried over time about the prongs becoming lose/breaking, but it seems strong enough thus far. I will ensure I update this if anything negative happens, as the band is the biggest thing I am worried about somehow breaking over time.

Pros: The fire in the ring is gorgeous. In the sunlight, it is dazzling - almost blindingly so, and that's no exaggeration. However, it's primarily reds, yellows/oranges, with some sparse spots of green and even lesser so blips of blue [which blue is my favourite]. The blues are subdued most entirely and just rest in the background without much of a spark. Even so, the highlighted colours are so pretty it's ridiculous in a good way.
The pink sapphire is a lot less purple as it looks in the given Amazon photo, but it still definitely is a pink-purple mix. They catch the light well, and far better than the white sapphire [which I really think helps to pull the eye to the opal and sapphire which hold the most colour pigment].
The opal gemstone is.. decently sized. A bit smaller than what I expected, but if you like the smaller sized stones, this is for you. It's not too small, though, but on the smaller-medium, I think.
Additionally, the opal isn't a small disc in size. It's got a decent width to it what really helps it look a lot more realistic as the colours look like they come from inside the ring to shine out, and the glow of the amethyst when it catches any light is immediately eye-catching. The way the opal is elevated above the amethyst and white sapphire works well to ensure it's the focal point.

All in all, for the $24 price I purchased it at, it's worth the money [minus, potentially, if the band does break as I am worried about due to how lacking strength/durability it feels]. It's got a shimmer like no other ring I've seen has, the design is gorgeous, and it looks a lot more expensive than it really was [minus, again, the cheap feeling band]. I'd say it's worth buying if it remains in the $20-$35 range. It'd be a five star rating if the band felt sturdier/was made out of real metal, or at least actually felt like it was made out of real metal.
I'll be sure to update later if any issues arise.pensive than it really was [minus, again, the cheap feeling band]. I'd say it's worth buying if it remains in the $20-$35 range. column13: Cute, sparkly disco balls that seem to be well made; more vivid than they appear in the photos
column14: These were just what I was looking for -- cute "disco ball' earrings for all occasions. Actually, I found some cute charms at a crafts store that I wanted to "convert" into earrings, and so I just layer them on behind the disco balls -- it works perfectly. The black earrings look super with some black Day of the Dead charms behind them; the red earrings match well with some cherry charms (the earrings are cherry red rather than the coral color they appear in the photo), and the multi-colored crystals look good with crystal-studded Eiffel tower charms. The disco ball earrings are cute and seem to be well made. They have the usual inexpensive costume-jewelry findings -- nothing bad or good about the silver parts. The colored parts are lovely. The colors are vivid and deeper than they seem to be in the photos on my computer screen -- and the balls are very shiny and sparkly. As far as durability, I cannot really say, because I haven't had them for very long, but so far, so good. I ordered these using Amazon Prime and was thrilled to get them just two days after ordering them. I spent about an hour comparing similar earrings online, and for the selection, looks, and price, I don't think you can go wrong with this set of earrings.

column14:
My new bracelet came today, and, as is usual for cz's, it sparkles like crazy. I ordered this one because the product details stated that the setting was made of brass (plated silver-color to look like white gold), and brass is a harder metal than silver is. Since each stone is 1/2 carat, the bracelet feels a little heavy, and the pricey look of it out-classes my one carat diamond engagement ring. Therefore, I feel a little regretful that I did not order something with smaller stones. Nevertheless, the quality seems really good and the price is certainly right.

I bought size 6 1/2 inches, which seems perfect for my thin-ish wrists. I did not find it difficult to put on, and I would not expect this type of clasp to fail.

column13: The Picture Doesn't Do These Pretty Earrings Justice-I Love Them!
column14: From the picture, I thought the yellow gold color might be too strong, and the hoops might be gaudy. But not at all!  These are so feminine and pretty, and the silver with diamond accents contrasts with the yellow gold color perfectly. I will wear these so much because I absolutely love the way they look on and they are so versatile - perfect for day or night, or to wear with casual or dressy attire. I love that these earrings have some sparkle, but it's subtle and not overdone. These are about the size of a nickel - so they are big enough to show even with long hair, but they aren't gaudy or distracting. The closure is sturdy as the stems are solid and thick enough to snap closed securely. The inside of the hoops bears the 925 stamp (confirming these are sterling silver) and shows these are made in China. These earrings are good quality jewelry at a reasonable price point, they arrive nicely presented in a regal black gift box and they would be a gift that would make any woman with pierced ears happy!

Not quite what I was expecting after looking at the item picture and trying it on myself. It's tungsten, so it has a noticeable amount of weight to it--definitely would get better the longer it's worn. The blue undertone is more of a "glinting accent" than a main feature of the ring. Another reviewer explained it very well regarding the light conditions. The carbon weave is what you mainly see, with the blue being more of a small glint depending on movement and light source. Sunlight will make the blue stand out much, much more, compared to being indoors.

The pictures I've uploaded seem to show more blue than what I see with the naked eye, but that could just be timing I guess. I've been calling it the 'Champagne' ring because it looks like a riot of bubbles around your finger.
Slightly quirky, and most definitely unique, it can go from formal to casual. In certain light, the CZs sparkle, in other light they look more understated.

Included is a very nice traditional leather like ring box with gold embossing. Inside, the ring rests in black velvet padding which shows off the highly polished silver.

column13: Will Not Fade, Tarnish, Rust, or Bend!! Unbeatable Quality!
column14: To say that I was stunned when this ring arrived, would be an understatement! I was honestly taken back at how beautiful it looked. At first, I was definitely skeptical about buying a cheap ring off amazon, but I could not have made a better decision. I would have been honored if my husband would have proposed to me with this ring. In fact, I have actually taken off my wedding ring and replaced it with this one. He didn't mind of course, because, like myself, he was very impressed with this ring as well. The clarity of the stone is beautiful and the ring is very well made. No scratches or knicks. The ring is a little big on me, but that's obviously my own fault because I have no idea what size ring I wear. And of course, I was so anxious for the moment I would take this ring off and have my finger turned green. But... jokes on me! It didn't happen!!! In fact, I have worn this ring everyday all day long for over a week and the ring has not faded, tarnished, worn, rusted.... nothing! And I am constantly using my hands either at work or around the house. So I do believe it is safe to say that this ring is HIGH QUALITY, the stone is BEAUTIFUL, and you (or your lady) will be EXTREMELY PLEASED. I have also soaked this ring in jewelry cleaner overnight (just to test) and it did not damage the ring at all. You will not be disappointed. Do not waste your money buying expensive rings at the jewelry store, when you can have this one delivered! I was graciously provided a discount on this product in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. All opinions are my own.

column14:
[[VIDEOID:7e1af157152866661eed06cceaabbe2b]]This review is for the JoinMe Women's Wedding Bridal Clear Crystal Butterfly Cream Simulated Pearl Hair Comb Silver-Tone.

This is a beautiful hair comb that is perfect for a bride or prom outfit. The crystals are clear and faceted and hit the light at every angle. They are truly beautiful and will be the highlight of your hair and makeup, and garner looks from everyone in the room.

The hair comb is ultra comfortable in my hair when I put it back. The combs are made from metal so they won't chip or break as the plastic ones usually do. I love that he hair comb is hooked with loops so it can curve to the shape of your head. Some hair combs I tried are stiff and only lay straight across. The ones forms perfectly and lays flat against your up do. It really completes the look of a fancy hair style.

The pearls are gorgeous, luminous and cream color. They accent the butterfly design. There are 3 butterflies with sprays of crystals across the top. The crystals are numerous and in an asymmetrical formation. 5/5 stars for design, bling, and materials.

If you have any questions please post below and I would be happy to answer! I received a free promotional sample of this item for my honest and unbiased review.

column13: first time titanium jewelery. also fairly new to wrist jewelery
column14:
First time handling titanium bracelet. At first was dissapointed about the weight and way it swings a little on the hinges left to right. Felt sorta like plastic and not like metal. It's comfortable and definitely looks heavier than it actually is. I have 2 and love the added benefit of therapeutic value though I have no need for it whatsoever. I had to take 3 links off each bracelet so there is no looseness when worn. I am medium-large sized wrists. Moves about 4 inches when worn. Linked together forms 16 inches and I use it as a choker to good effect (primarily bought for this purpose.) And it is definitely not that great around the neck but gets the job done. I like wearing them on the wrists in public.

I hear this stuff can get scratched easily. But it's common to buff these types of metal anyways so it's not the end of the world if you happen to scratch it. I find myself more aware of when my hands are leaning on surfaces now, which is a plus. I don't plan on having to get these buffed.

The tool works great, very simple to use but requires a steady hand.
